title: pumpkin roll
directions: Mix flour and spices.
Beat eggs; add sugar, pumpkin and vanilla.
Stir in flour mixture.
Spread on greased jelly roll pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 375°.
Loosen and turn out on linen towel covered with powdered sugar.
Roll and put in freezer to cool. While cake is cooling, mix ingredients for frosting.

title: turkey 'n hash brown casserole
directions: Thaw hash browns.
Pour into an ungreased casserole dish. Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Place turkey and mushrooms over potatoes.
Mix turkey stock, soup, sour cream, instant bouillon, onion and garlic; pour over all ingredients in a casserole dish. Top with cheese and bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: lemon tarts
directions: Combine flour and salt; cut in margarine with a pastry blender until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Add egg and stir until well blended.
Refrigerate dough 2 hours.

title: hot water cornbread
directions: Heat cooking oil in an iron skillet.
Mix boiling water and 1/4 cup oil to dry ingredients.
Dip hands in cold water.
Form mixture into pones.
Cook until golden brown on both sides.

title: chicken lasagna
directions: Mix all ingredients together in bowl, all but cheese.
Cook lasagna noodles and butter casserole dish.
Layer noodles, meat mixture, cheese, noodles, meat mixture, cheese (last layer should be cheese).
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pound cake
directions: Beat butter and sugar until creamy.
Add one egg at a time; continue beating.
When creamy, fold in flour with spoon. Spread in buttered and floured loaf pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: snickerdoodle cookies
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Cream shortening and sugar together.
Add eggs and vanilla. Beat well.
Add dry ingredients. Blend well.
Chill dough until easy to handle.
Roll dough in small balls and dip in cinnamon and sugar mixture.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.
Don't overcook!

title: broccoli and cheese soup
directions: Saute
onion
in
butter
for
3 minutes in large Dutch oven. Add water and bouillon cubes; bring to a boil.
Add egg noodles; boil 3 minutes.
Add broccoli and garlic salt;
cook 4
minutes. Slowly add milk and cheese; stir constantly until cheese
melts. To
thicken:
Mix
tablespoons flour into a small
amount
of melted margarine.
Add to flour mixture the boiling liquid from pot, then add to soup.

title: easy macaroni and cheese
directions: Melt oleo in 2-quart casserole.
Add macaroni and stir.
Grate cheese and add to mixture.
Add milk and stir.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: ho ho cake
directions: Bake the cake mix in jelly roll pan. Cool.
Cook the flour and milk in a double boiler until thick and cool.
Mix and beat until fluffy the sugar, 1 stick oleo and Crisco. Add to flour and milk mixture. Top cake and let set in refrigerator.

title: hasty tasty butter cake
directions: Mix together cake mix, oleo, and 2 eggs.
Pour into greased 9x13-inch cake pan.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease cookie sheets.
Into large bowl, mix all ingredients except chocolate chips.
With mixture at medium speed, beat until well mixed, scraping bowl.
Add chocolate chips and mix well.
Place by rounded teaspoonfuls 2 inches apart on greased sheets.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes until cookies are lightly browned.
With pancake turner or spatula, remove cookies and allow to cool.

title: pritikinish broccoli soup
directions: Bring water to a boil.
It should be salted and include garlic.
Add chopped broccoli.
Boil for about 7 minutes and remove broccoli so it doesn't soften too much.
Boil spaghetti in the same water for about 10 minutes.
When spaghetti is tender, add the broccoli.
Make sure you can taste the salt or salt substitute.
Serve in soup bowls covered with a layer of Parmesan cheese.
Serve with hot bread and a salad.

title: buttermilk dressing
directions: Mix ingredients in a tightly covered jar.
Refrigerate 2 hours. Shake before serving.
Makes 1 1/4 cups dressing.

title: fried cauliflower
directions: Soak cauliflower in cold water for one hour.
Boil in 1/4 cup milk and water until tender.
Divide into pieces and cool.

title: crispy oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream margarine; gradually add sugars, beating at medium speed of an electric mixer until light and fluffy.
Add egg substitute and vanilla; beat well.

title: macaroni soup
directions: Cook and drain the macaroni according to the package directions.
Pour the undiluted tomato soup over the cooked and drained macaroni.
Stir until the macaroni is coated with the soup (mixture will be thick).
Serve hot as a soup or as a side dish. Tastes better after being refrigerated and reheated.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Cream together shortening, sugar and eggs until smooth.
Sift together all dry ingredients and add to the creamed mixture.
Add nuts and apples.
Pour into well oiled and slightly floured tube pan.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: swingin' summer salad
directions: Prepare dinner as directed on package.
Add remaining ingredients lightly.
Chill.

title: meat potato pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together, but use 1/2 cup catsup to mix. Seasonings are salt, pepper, garlic powder or salt, Accent or whatever your choice.
You can use cracker, oatmeal or bread crumbs to make up the meat like meat loaf.
Cook for an hour.
Drain grease when done.
While it's baking, cook potatoes (instant or fresh) to make mashed potatoes.
When meat is done, cover with potatoes.
Add the remaining cheese with milk over the potatoes. Place back in oven for 1/2 hour or until cheese is melted, then it's done.
Oven should be at 350°.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Dissolve thoroughly the sugar, salt and vinegar.
Slice very thin the pretzels, onion and green pepper.
Put all ingredients together and put in the refrigerator.
These are no cook pickles and after 24 hours, you can eat.

title: zalabee(fried dough)
directions: Dissolve yeast cake in a small amount of water.
Add sugar and set aside until bubbly.
Mix flour and salt.
Add dissolved yeast cake and oil.
Use enough water to leave mixture soft and stringy. Set until dough rises (approximately 1 hour).
Take pinches or strips of dough and fry in hot oil until golden brown.
These may be eaten plain or sprinkled with powdered sugar or dipped in cool syrup.

title: "1800" comforts
directions: Mix in order.
Drop from spoon into hot Crisco and fry to a light brown.
Serve plain or sprinkle with cinnamon or confectioners powdered sugar.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 2 cups boiling water.
Mix pie filling and pineapple into the Jell-O; let jell or set.
After jelled or set, top with a mixture of cream cheese, sour cream and sugar, then top with chopped nuts.

title: buttered pecan ice cream dessert
directions: Melt butter.
Add sugar, coconut and Rice Krispies.
Line bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan with 1/2 mixture.
Soften ice cream enough to spread over top.
Cover with remaining mixture. Sprinkle chopped toasted pecans over this.
Keep in freezer until serving time.
Cut in squares.
Serves 12.
Can be frozen for several weeks.

title: cheese potatoes
directions: Pat butter on top of cooked potatoes.
Mix Cheez Whiz and mushroom soup.
Spread over potatoes and cook 30 minutes at 350°.

title: lemon pudding cake
directions: Blend in large bowl and beat for 2 minutes at medium speed. Bake in a greased and floured pan, 10-inch tube pan.
Bake for 55 to 60 minutes at 350°.
Cool in pan for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: pinto beans
directions: Let ham knuckles cook for an hour.
Add pinto beans, pepper, vinegar, sugar, green pepper and onions.
Let cook until done.

title: honey-mustard dressing
directions: Start with 1/4 cup each of honey and mustard.
Taste and adjust.
If it tastes too sweet, add more mustard.	If not sweet enough, add more honey.
Keep an accurate record of the adjustments in order to duplicate the recipe later.

title: pineapple ambrosia
directions: Mix evaporated milk and sugar in a large bowl.
Pour marshmallows in, stir to coat.
Cover bowl and refrigerate overnight.
The next day, pour pineapple into marshmallows.
Beat whipping cream into marshmallows.
Beat whipping cream in another bowl until whipped and fluffy.
Fold into marshmallows.
If desired, quarter or halve maraschino cherries and mix in.

title: apricot tarts
directions: Beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Gradually add milk; blend well.
Add lemon juice and orange extract.
Pour into shells.
Put a slice of apricot on top.
In saucepan, mix sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Stir in orange and apricot juice.
Cook until thick and clear.
Cool and spoon on top of tarts.
Chill for several hours.

title: hugs and kisses bon bons
directions: Melt together chocolate chips and butter. Remove from heat and stir in milk, flour and vanilla. Wrap one tablespoon of dough around either the Hershey's Hugs or Kisses. Bake at 350 degrees for 6 to 8 minutes. Cookies will appear soft and shiny. Cool completely.

title: ham loaf
directions: Combine egg, milk, cracker crumbs, onion and dash of pepper. Add ground ham and ground pork.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Add Mustard Glaze last 1/2 hour.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: *I use a little more than 1/2 cup cheese.

title: pickled beets
directions: Combine mustard, sugar, salt, cloves and garlic.
Slowly stir in vinegar and water.
When smooth, pour over beets.
Refrigerate until well chilled.
Remove garlic.
Makes 6 servings.
(If desired, may add sliced onions and/or hard-boiled eggs prior to refrigeration.)

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Drain Veg-All and chestnuts and mix all ingredients.
Put in 2-quart casserole.
Melt 1/2 stick butter.
Add 12 crumbled saltine crackers and saute.
Spread over top of vegetable mixture. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: the hill twin's trail mix
directions: Add or subtract any of the ingredients, depending on what your children like or what you want them to have.
Mix your chosen ingredients in a large bowl.
Children love to help with this.
Put 1/2 to 1 cup of mixture in individual serving containers.
Store leftovers in an airtight container for a treat on another day.

title: surprise pie
directions: Bake pie shell (let cool).
Mix milk, lemon juice and Cool Whip well.
Fold in strawberries.
Pour into pie shell. Refrigerate 2 to 3 hours before serving.

title: pina colada pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325 degrees. Grease and flour a tube or Bundt pan. Cream together the butter, shortening, and sugar.

Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Add vanilla extract and coconut flavoring and mix. Combine all-purpose flour and self-rising flour. Stir to mix. Add to the creamed mixture alternately with the pina colada mixer, starting and ending with the flour. Stir in the drained crushed pineapple and the coconut. Pour into the prepared pan and bake for about 1 hour 20 minutes or until a toothpick comes out clean when inserted into center of cake. Turn out of pan immediately and wrap in aluminum foil.

title: veggie squares
directions: Take Pillsbury croissants and press on large cookie sheet (lightly greased).
Press dough up around edges Bake as directed on package.
Cream together the cream cheese, mayonnaise and Ranch dressing.
After crust cools, spread mix on crust with a wet knife. Cut and shred up vegetables and sprinkle on top.
Sprinkle cheese on last.

title: amish snickerdoodles
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and beat well.
Sift together flour, cream of tartar, soda and salt.
Gradually stir into creamed mixture.
Chill dough 2 hours or more.
Form into balls the size of walnuts.
Roll each ball in a mixture of 2 tablespoons sugar and 2 teaspoons cinnamon.
Bake at 400° for about 10 minutes.

title: shells apple pie
directions: Cut shortening into flour.
Add water, 3 tablespoons at a time, until moistened.
Divide in half.
Form ball with each half; roll onto floured surface to fit pan.

title: sweet pickle sticks
directions: Wash and cut cucumbers into sticks.
Pour boiling water over them; let stand overnight.
Next morning, pack in jars.
Fix solution made of remaining ingredients.
Boil for 5 minutes.
Pour over cucumbers and process for 5 minutes in boiling water.
Be sure and drain water off after packing in jars, before pouring solution over them.

title: stir-fry
directions: Cut or chop vegetables to suitable size.
Cut boneless, skinless chicken breast into 1/2 to 1-inch cubes.
Heat oil on high.
Stir-fry chicken; add vegetables.
Fry for 1 to 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add 2 tablespoons soy sauce and simmer on medium heat.
While simmering, season with cumin, curry and pepper to taste.
Simmer until desired crispness or tenderness of vegetables.
Add more soy sauce as necessary.

title: pumpkin pudding(a vegetable dish)
directions: Melt margarine in a 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Mix all ingredients together and pour into melted margarine.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chocolate heaven
directions: Mix flour and margarine together.
Use 9 x 13 x 2-inch or 10-inch Corning Ware dish.
Pat out in bottom of pan.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup pecans over crust. Pat in.
Bake 10 minutes at 350° and cool.

title: never fail jelly roll
directions: Cream sugar and egg yolks.
Add vanilla.
Add flour and baking powder.
Whip egg whites with salt.
Fold them lightly into cake batter.
Line
15 x 10-inch pan with heavy buttered paper.	Spread dough
on	it.
Bake
13 minutes in 375° oven. While
hot, invert
cake
onto sheet of waxed paper sprinkled with
powdered sugar.
Cut off hard edges.
Spread with jelly and roll.

title: art's homemade fudge
directions: Microwave chocolate and milk on High for 1 minute.
Stir. Microwave another minute.
Stir until chocolate is smooth and completely melted.
Stir in vanilla, salt and nuts.
Spread onto lightly greased pan 8 x 8-inch.
Refrigerate until firm.
Cut into squares.

title: chess pie
directions: Mix butter and sugar.
Slowly add eggs and vinegar then vanilla.
Beat thoroughly.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Mix shortening, sugar and eggs thoroughly.
Sift together flour, cream of tartar, soda and salt and stir in.
Form dough into balls, the size of walnuts.
Roll into a mixture of sugar and cinnamon.
Place 2-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 7 to 8 minutes at 350°.
Do not overbake.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix sugar, flour and soda. Add eggs and fruit cocktail.
Pour into greased and floured long pan.
Mix together chopped nuts and brown sugar.
Pour over batter in pan.
Place pan in oven that has been preheated to 350° and bake for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: old fashioned crisp oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars; add eggs and vanilla.
Beat well. Sift dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture.
Add oats and nuts and mix well.
Shape into rolls; wrap in waxed paper and chill thoroughly.
Slice 1/4-inch thick.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: lemon cookies
directions: Cream butter; add sugar and egg and beat until light and fluffy. Add lemon rind and juice.

title: betty's punch
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients together and cool.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Mix all together and freeze.

title: tio sancho fiesta dip
directions: In medium skillet, prepare taco mix with beef and water according to package.
Add beans and heat for 5 minutes.
In a 1 quart bowl, spread beef and bean mixture.
Layer remaining ingredients in order given above.
Serve with nacho chips.

title: mint meringue kisses
directions: Beat until soft peaks form in egg whites, salt and cream of tartar.
Gradually add white sugar.
Beat until stiff peaks form. Add green food coloring, peppermint flavoring and chocolate chips. Drop by teaspoon on wax paper covered cookie sheet.
Put in preheated 375° oven.
Turn off oven immediately.
Leave in oven overnight.
Do not open door.

title: chicken and vegetable turnovers
directions: Boil chicken (without the bones) and cut into small pieces. Put into big pot and cook over medium heat with mushroom soup, peas, mushrooms, onion, tomatoes, garlic powder, seasoned salt, salt and pepper.
Roll biscuits out flat.
Place 1 spoonful of mixture in center of biscuit.
Crimp edges all around.
Place on greased baking sheet.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 1 hour or until browned.
Serve hot.
Really good!

title: "no cook" picante
directions: Mix well.
Refrigerate until chilled.
Serve with chips.
This recipe will serve 5 people.

title: banana split cake
directions: Spread graham cracker crumbs on bottom of 9 x 13-inch dish; pour margarine on top.
Next mix powdered sugar, cream cheese and egg until smooth.
Spread this mixture on top of graham cracker bottom.
Next add 1 layer of banana slices, 1 layer of crushed pineapple and 1 layer of Cool Whip.
Repeat layers, then add cherries and nuts.
Chill.

title: orange-kissed brussels sprouts
directions: When you grate the orange rind, avoid the bitter tasting white layer, or pith, just beneath the surface.

title: babe ruth bars
directions: Bring sugars and corn syrup to a boil.
Stir in peanut butter. Add cornflakes and salted peanuts.
Press into a greased 9-inch pan.
Melt large chocolate bar and spread over top.
Cut into squares.

title: barbecued pork
directions: Marinate pork with sauce for 2 hours or more.
Roast 20 minutes at 350° in oven pan on rack.
Turn and roast 10 to 15 minutes until done.
Serve as puupuus.
Slice very thin and serve with boiled noodles, or dice for fried rice with peas and egg.

title: fresh vegetable dressing
directions: Put over chunky, cut-up broccoli, cauliflower and carrots; marinate a few hours.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Mix Wesson oil, sugar, eggs and apples.
Add dry ingredients. Pour into a greased and floured pan.
Bake 1 hour at 275°.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta according to directions.
When pasta is done, but still firm, rinse and drain well.
Place in large bowl which has a cover.
Pour dressing over pasta.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: dipper's nuggets chicken
directions: Mix eggs, water, salt, sesame seed and flour into a batter. Heat oil over medium heat to 375° in a heavy sturdy flat-bottomed 3-quart saucepan or deep fryer, filling utensil no more than 1/3 full.
Dip nuggets into batter; drain off excess batter.
Add nuggets in a single layer, about 8 or 9 at a time.
Fry about 3 to 5 minutes or until golden brown.
Drain on paper towels.
Serve with following sauces.
Makes 12 servings.

title: chocolate passion
directions: Cut brownies into cubes.
Layer in 3-quart serving bowl 1/2 of the brownies, 1 cup of the strawberries, 1 banana (sliced) and half of the whipped topping.
Repeat layers.
Keep in refrigerator until served.
Yields 16 servings.

title: oreo cheesecake
directions: Grind in food processor 8 ounces Oreos. Press evenly into bottom of spring-form pan. Bake at 350° for 5 to 8 minutes.
Mix in blender the cream cheese, sugar, eggs, vanilla and 6 ounces Oreos.
Pour over crust.
Bake for 45 to 50 minutes at 350°. Decorate top with crushed Oreos.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients in order given in greased casserole. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Last 5 minutes, top with French fried onion rings.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Open the bag and eat, eat, eat!

title: sweet potatoes
directions: Combine potatoes, sugar, milk, 1/2 of margarine, eggs and vanilla; mix well.
Put in a greased 8-inch square baking dish. Combine coconut, brown sugar, flour, remaining margarine and nuts. Spread on top of potatoes.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes, or until brown.

title: stuffed red cabbage rolls
directions: Remove 8 to 10 leaves.
Wash, then blanch for 3 minutes in salt water.
Remove and pat dry.
Melt the butter in a frying pan and render the fat from the bacon.
Add bread cubes and onion.
Fry until crisp and brown.
Add the apple pieces, cream and red wine. Remove from stove.
Let stand for 15 minutes.
Add seasonings to taste.
Place small amount of filling in leaves and roll them up. Roll a second leaf around each roll.
Place the stuffed leaves closely together in a greased dish.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.
Serve.

title: oven baked popcorn
directions: Cook brown sugar, butter and white Karo for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat, then add soda; stir well.
Then pour over popcorn. Bake in oven at 250° for 1 hour.
Stir every 15 minutes.
You may add nuts if you want.
Mixture should cover about 7 quarts of popcorn.

title: basic broiled fish
directions: Place steaks or thick fillets in a single layer on a preheated and greased broiler pan.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over fish.
Broil 4 to 6 minutes; turn and baste with sauce. Broil until fish flakes, 4 to 5 more minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: fried apple pies
directions: *You may use a mixture of equal parts of plain and self-rising flour.

title: chess cake
directions: Mix by hand cake mix, eggs and butter.
Press into 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Use mixer to combine cream cheese, eggs and sugar. Pour on top of cake.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: golden potatoes
directions: Slightly thaw and separate potatoes.
Mix potatoes with sour cream, cheese, salt, soup, pepper and onion.
Spread in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix margarine and corn flakes together.
Top potatoes with buttered corn flakes.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: "quick" swedish tea ring
directions: Take bread dough and roll into rectangle (15 x 9-inch) on lightly floured surface.
For filling, mix brown sugar, cinnamon and raisins.
Spread margarine evenly across dough.
Sprinkle filling evenly across dough.
Roll up tightly, beginning at 15-inch side.
Pinch edge of dough into roll to seal well. Stretch roll to make even.
With sealed edge down, shape into ring on lightly
greased cookie sheet.
Pinch ends together.
With scissors, make cuts 2/3 of the way through ring at 1-inch intervals.
Turn each section on its side.
Let dough rise until double (about 40 minutes).
Heat oven to 375° and bake until golden brown 25 to 30 minutes.
(If ring browns too quickly, cover loosely with aluminum foil.)
Spread ring with glaze while warm.

title: peanut blossoms
directions: Combine flour, brown sugar, baking soda, salt, shortening, peanut butter, milk, vanilla, and egg at low speed until stiff dough forms.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Roll in sugar.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes or until brown.
Immediately top each cookie with a candy kiss.
Press firmly so that cookie cracks around edge.
Makes 4 dozen cookies.

title: summer squash casserole
directions: Cook squash with onion in boiling salted water until tender-crisp.
Drain well.
Combine soup, sour cream and stir in carrot.
Fold in drained squash and onion.

title: fruit punch
directions: Mix all ingredients and mash strawberries before adding to liquid.

title: mustard dip
directions: Combine all ingredients except chives; chill. Serve with seafood cocktails or surrounded by crackers. Garnish with chives. Yields 1 cup.

title: german potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes.
Cool and slice.
In separate pan cube and fry. Add other ingredients in order given.
Bring to a boil.
Cook until clear, then add sliced potatoes.
Simmer at least one hour. Serve hot.
Serves 4 people.

title: stuffed chicken supreme
directions: Cut chicken breasts in half.
Place between sheets of waxed paper.
Pound a little flatter.

title: butter frosting
directions: Stir flour and milk together over heat until thick.
Cool. Cream together the sugar, vanilla and butter.
Beat butter mixture into cold flour mixture until of spreading consistency.
When finished, it looks like whipped cream.

title: stir-fried beef and peppers
directions: Trim fat from beef; cut beef with grain into 2-inch strips. Cut strips across grain into 1/8-inch slices.
Toss beef, 1 tablespoon vegetable oil, 1 teaspoon cornstarch, 1 teaspoon soy sauce, salt and pepper in a glass bowl.
Refrigerate 30 minutes. Mix chicken broth, 2 tablespoons soy sauce and the sugar.
Heat in wok or large skillet until hot.
Add 3 tablespoons vegetable oil; rotate to coat.
Add onion and garlic; stir-fry until garlic is brown.
Add beef; stir-fry until beef is brown, about 3 minutes. Remove beef from wok.
Add 2 tablespoons vegetable oil; rotate to coat.
Add tomatoes; stir-fry 30 seconds.
Stir in 1/2 cup beef broth; heat to boiling.
Stir in cornstarch mixture and cook, stirring until thickened.
Add peppers and beef.
Stir-fry 30 seconds.
Yields 6 servings.

title: tomato gravy
directions: Saute margarine and onion.
Add flour, tomato juice and cinnamon.
Cook to thicken, then add vinegar, sweetener, salt and pepper.
Enjoy!

title: panetela rellena(cuban cake)
directions: Prepare cake mix according to package directions.
Bake 3/4 of mix in a 9 x 13-inch pan (suitable for serving in).
Retain 1/4 of mix for pudding sauce.
While cake is cooling, drain pineapple juice and save.

title: chocolate miracle whip cake
directions: Mix all together and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: meat loaf parajun
directions: Mix together ingredients with bread crumbs.
Make the ground beef into football shape and put parajun cheese in middle.
Bake. Add tomato sauce and some more cheese.

title: chili
directions: Mix all together and let set and simmer about 1 hour.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: cookie crust
directions: Cream butter, Add dry ingredients.
Combine egg yolk and milk and add to the mixture.
Pat into 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake at 425° until light brown.

title: california pepper relish
directions: Halve, seed and chop peppers.
Layer with salt in large, glass bowl.
Allow to stand at room temperature 3 hours, stirring several times.
Drain peppers well.
Combine drained peppers, tomatoes and onions.
Stir in sugar, vinegar and spices.
Bring to boil (stir often).
Lower heat to simmer to prevent scorching. Cook for 30 minutes or until thick.
Remove spice bag.

title: orange cream fruit salad
directions: Mix pudding, milk and orange juice.
Beat well.
Add sour cream.
Put in fruit mixture.
Cover and refrigerate several hours.

title: italian bean salad
directions: In a medium bowl, stir together dressing mix and vinegar.
Add beans, chickpeas, olives, celery and thinly sliced onion.
Toss to coat well.
Cover and chill at least 4 hours or overnight.
Just before serving, toss with mayonnaise.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: skillet venison
directions: Marinate venison in the Kraft Italian salad dressing overnight.
Remove and brown the meat in a skillet.
While meat is browning, in a second skillet, prepare Rice-A-Roni according to package directions, but add tomatoes or 2 cups canned, chopped tomatoes, and Ro-Tel.
When Rice-A-Roni is ready to simmer, add browned venison, cover and cook for 20 to 30 minutes.
Yield: 4 to 6 servings.
Serve with crackers and salad.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: Mix cocoa, sugar, salt, and flour thoroughly.
Gradually add milk.
Cook until thickened.
Serve with homemade biscuits and butter.

title: taco salad
directions: Mix seasoning into the dressing.
Toss all ingredients.

title: whipped chocolate cream frosting
directions: Heat cream in pan over medium heat until boiling.
Add chocolate chips.
Remove from heat and stir with rubber spatula until melted and smooth.
Put in a large mixing bowl and refrigerate for 2 hours, stirring twice, until just chilled. Beat with mixer until soft peaks form.
Don't overbeat as cream will continue to thicken after a few minutes at room temperature.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix together. Pour in greased casserole dish. Heat oven to 350°. Bake 35 to 45 minutes.

title: pineapple pie
directions: Combine ingredients.
Pour into pie shell and bake at 350° until firm.

title: 2 chocolate pies
directions: Cook all but last two ingredients on top of stove until thickened.
Remove and add vanilla.
Pour into pie shells and cook at 350° in oven until crust is brown.

title: sour cream coconut cake
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time; add sour cream and flour and all other ingredients.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: jo's zucchini pie
directions: In large mixing bowl, combine thinly sliced zucchini, onion, vegetable oil, Bisquick, eggs, Parmesan cheese, parsley flakes, salt and pepper; stir until all ingredients are mixed and zucchini is evenly coated.
Pour mixture into a buttered baking dish (pie plate).
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes, or until golden brown.

title: barbecue spareribs
directions: Cook ribs in water; boil for 1/2 hour to 45 minutes. Mix all other ingredients together. Put ribs in a pan and pour sauce mix over. Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: cheddar cheese spread
directions: Beat butter until fluffy.
Add cheese and milk, a tablespoon at a time until spreadable and well blended.
Add remaining ingredients.
Blend until well mixed.

title: flaky parmesan pesto pinwheels
directions: In a food processor with a metal blade or a blender, process cream cheese and Parmesan until blended.
Add green onions and pulse until finely chopped.
Add pesto and process until thoroughly incorporated.
On a lightly floured board, roll one sheet of the puff pastry flat.
Spread half the cheese mixture over pastry, covering it completely.
Roll lengthwise, to make a log about
1 1/2-inches in diameter.
Wrap tightly in plastic wrap.
Repeat with the other pastry sheet.
Freeze logs until solid, several hours or months.
Remove logs from freezer 20 minutes prior to baking.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Slice logs into 1/4-inch rounds.
Place on ungreased baking sheets about 1 1/2 inches apart.
Bake for 10 minutes or until the pastry is lightly browned.

title: beans azteca
directions: In saucepan cook onion and green pepper (use boiling water) for 5 minutes or until tender; drain.
Combine cooked vegetable mixture, beans, corn, tortilla chips, barbecue sauce and chili powder.
Turn 1/3 of meat mixture into ungreased 2 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Spread 1/2 cup cheese spread over meat.
Repeat layers, top with remaining meat mixture.
Cover and refrigerate up to 24 hours.
Bake covered at 375° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: orange julius
directions: Blend in a blender and serve.

title: lemon icebox cake
directions: Thicken egg yolks, lemon juice and sugar in top of double boiler.
Dissolve 1 package of Knox gelatine in 1/2 cup water. Add to hot lemon mixture.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add 3/4 cup sugar to egg whites.
Fold egg whites into warm lemon mixture. Tear angel food cake into bite-size.
Alternate layers of lemon mixture and angel food cake in a spring mold.
Set in refrigerator overnight.
Ice with Cool Whip or serve with Cool Whip.

title: taco fantastaco
directions: Brown ground beef with chili powder.
Drain.
Combine ground beef with cheese, lettuce, tomatoes, corn chips, olives and prepared dressing.
Garnish salad with avocado slices and unbroken taco chips.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Mix and bake in 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes. DON'T LET GET DONE.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Saute minced onion in margarine; add remaining ingredients, then simmer for 10 minutes or until ready to baste chicken, ribs, etc.

title: castle spice
directions: Combine all ingredients in large pot. Bring to a boil and simmer. As it boils down, more water may be added. Use at Christmas.

title: swiss steak with noodles
directions: Pound flour, salt and pepper into both sides of round steak. Brown meat in greased skillet; add tomato soup and simmer slowly over moderate heat until savory and tender.
Remove meat and cut into desired portions.
Cook egg noodles as directed and drain. Saute egg noodles in steak gravy.
Pour into large platter and top with Swiss steak and parsley.

title: broccoli-onion delight
directions: Boil cut up broccoli and onions until tender (don't overcook). Melt 1/8 cup butter and blend in flour, salt and dash of pepper. Add milk and cook, stirring constantly until thick and bubbly. Reduce heat and blend in cream cheese.
Place broccoli and onions into casserole dish and pour sauce over it.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Mix remaining butter with bread crumbs and spread on top. Cook at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: rice and broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and beef bouillon cubes until tender.
Butter a casserole and add drained broccoli.
Sprinkle with onion and pour soup and sour cream over top.
Sprinkle mixed cheese over top. Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: clam cakes
directions: Put crackers, clams and onion through food chopper.
If too thick, add a little clam juice.
Fry in deep fat.

title: sausage balls
directions: Combine ingredients and mix thoroughly until flour is absorbed.
Shape into small balls.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
These freeze well and can be heated quickly in the microwave.

title: sweet potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Cook sweet potatoes in boiling, salted water until done; peel and mash. Stir in all of remaining ingredients except 2 tablespoons of sugar.
Turn mixture into prepared casserole and sprinkle with remaining sugar.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: marinated chuck roast
directions: Sprinkle tenderizer on each side of roast and pierce with fork.
Place roast in 13 x 9 x 2 baking pan.
Combine remaining ingredients in a small bowl.
Mix well.
Pour over roast.
Cover and chill overnight.
Bake in marinade for about 2 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Grease a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Heat oven to 350°.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Put butter and peaches in deep baking dish.
Place in a 350° oven.
Make batter of sugar, flour, salt and milk.
Add batter to butter and peaches.
Don't stir.
Bake for 1 hour.

title: chipped beef dip
directions: Mix together and spread in 8-inch pie plate.
Spread 1/4 cup chopped pecans on top.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: burrito pie
directions: Fry ground beef and pour off fat.
Add onions, taco seasoning mix and water.
Cook slowly until onions are soft.
Add refried beans, tomato sauce and chili powder.
Cook about 10 minutes.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Combine the cake mix (dry) and the pudding mix (dry); add oil and mix well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each egg.
Add flavoring and stir well; add hot water and mix thoroughly.
Stir in the poppy seed.
Bake in a well-greased tube or Bundt pan at 350° for 40 minutes.
Cool in the pan for 10 minutes before transferring to cake plate.

title: poor man's casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Scramble hamburger meat; drain.
Layer hamburger, Veg-All, mushroom soup, then fried onions.
Repeat. Top with fried onions.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Blend peanut butter and cream cheese until smooth.
Add sugar and vanilla.
Mix thoroughly until smooth.
Fold in whipped topping.
Pour in graham cracker crust.
Chill for several hours.

title: two hour rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Combine egg, salt, milk, oil and sugar.
Mix all together and add flour.
Let rise once, then make into rolls.
Let rise again.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Brush with melted butter or margarine while hot from oven.

title: caramel dip
directions: Mix together all ingredients; ready to eat!
Good with sliced apples.

title: chocolate walnut biscotti
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Beat margarine and sugar until light and fluffy.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Mix in flour, baking powder and salt.
Stir in chocolate and walnuts.

title: uncooked fruit cake
directions: Melt marshmallows and milk.
Slowly add other ingredients and mix 1/2 teaspoon nutmeg, cinnamon and allspice.
Mix well and store in a tight container.

title: grasshopper pie
directions: Finely crush Oreo cookies; mix with melted butter.
Press into a 9-inch spring-form pan, reserving 1/2 cup crumbs for topping. Stir creme de menthe into Marshmallow Creme, mixing until well blended.
Fold in whipped cream.
Pour into pan.
Sprinkle with remaining crumbs.
Freeze.

title: caramel refrigerator cookies
directions: Mix shortening, sugar, egg and vanilla thoroughly.
Sift flour, salt and soda together.
Stir into mixture.
Add nuts. Form roll, 2 1/2-inches across.
Wrap in waxed paper or foil. Chill until firm.
Bake in 400° oven on greased cookie sheet for 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly browned.
I slice mine about 1/8-inch thick.
Yields 5 dozen.

title: mocha sensation
directions: Gradually add milk and coffee granules to Marshmallow Creme. Mixing with electric mixer or wire whisk, whisk until well blended.
Heat over medium-low until mixture is warmed, stirring constantly, and Marshmallow Creme is melted.
Serve warm or chilled.
Makes four 1-cup servings.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast and sugar in warm water.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour onto floured surface.
Knead, roll and cut; put a pat of butter into center.
Fold over and let rise 10 minutes. Cook at 450° for 10 minutes.

title: burnt sugar icing
directions: Combine eggs whites, sugar, water and corn syrup in top of double boiler.
Heat water to boiling point.
Beat with beater for about 7 minutes or until mixture thickens and holds shape.
Remove from boiling water.
Add burnt sugar syrup and continue to beat until stiff enough to spread.

title: rice pudding
directions: Bring water and salt to a boil.

Add rice and let simmer over low heat for about 20 minutes (until most of water is absorbed). Add milk, 1 cup at a time (5 cups), allowing rice to absorb milk before adding the next cup of milk (about 20 minutes each time).

title: 4 hour beef stew
directions: Place ingredients in casserole in order listed.
Cover tightly with foil; bake for 4 hours in a 250° oven.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Stew chicken breasts.
Reserve broth. Remove chicken from bones.
Melt margarine and stir into dressing.
Empty soups into large bowl. Add 2 cans soup broth.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Place layer of dressing and layer of chicken.
Add 1/2 soup mixture. Repeat and top with dressing crumbs. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: tortilla soup
directions: Brown meat with the onion.
Add garlic, salt and pepper.
Add all other ingredients.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Serve over tortilla chips. Top with cheese.

title: sunday breakfast cake
directions: Pour water over the oats, let stand 20 to 30 minutes.
Beat margarine then add sugars and beat.
Blend in vanilla and eggs. Stir in oats.
Sift together flour, soda, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Add to creamed mixture.
Blend well.
Pour into greased and floured 9-inch square pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: cindy's chili
directions: In large pan mix ground beef and onion; cook until meat is brown and onion tender.
Drain fat.
Add beans, soup and juice. Bring to oil.
Cook 1 1/2 hours on medium heat.
Serve with favorite crackers and top with shredded Cheddar cheese.
Yield: about 10 servings.

title: sloppy pudding(great for last minute dessert)
directions: In a large bowl, pour in vanilla wafers.
Add fruit cocktail; stir well.
Chill.

title: chocolate cream pie
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients; gradually stir in milk.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens. Remove from heat.
Mix small amount of mixture into egg yolks, then blend into hot mixture.
Boil 1 minute longer.
Remove from heat; blend in margarine and vanilla.
Pour into baked crust.
May be topped with whipped cream when cooled.

title: egg rolls
directions: Fry sausage and drain. Stir-fry vegetables one at a time in oil and drain. Mix with sausage.
Add soy sauce and salt.
Cool. Add 4 tablespoons of mixture to bottom edge of egg roll, spreading evenly across, stopping about 1-inch from edge.
Roll up the egg roll loosely until halfway.
Seal the edges with beaten egg or cornstarch water.
Deep fry in oil until golden brown.
Drain on paper towel.

title: short-cut chicken and rice
directions: Coat a large skillet with vegetable cooking spray; place over medium heat until hot.
Brown chicken on both sides.
Remove chicken and set aside.
Combine soup, wine and water; stir in rice mix.
Pour mixture into skillet and bring to boil.
Arrange chicken over rice; cover, reduce heat and simmer 25 minutes or until rice is tender.
Let stand 10 minutes.

title: pineapple dressing
directions: Cream butter with sugar.
Beat in eggs one at a time.
Stir in bread and pineapple.
Put in greased 8 x 8-inch pan.
Double recipe for 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Good with ham or turkey.

title: blueberry custard pie
directions: In a saucepan, stir together 1/2 cup sugar, 3 tablespoons cornstarch and cinnamon.
Stir in the blueberries and orange juice.
Cook and stir until mixture is bubbly.
Cover and set aside.

title: alma's pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat together eggs, sugar, margarine, Crisco and vanilla.
Add flour, baking powder and salt, alternating with milk and water.
Mix together and pour into angel food cake pan or Bundt pan (floured and greased).
Bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: meatballs
directions: Cook 3 1/2 to 4 hours in crock-pot on high or bake 1 1/2 hours in 350° oven.

title: great easy chicken
directions: Combine chicken with broth and soup.
Bake with cover on pot at 350° or more for about 1/2 hour.
Remove cover and bake another 1/2 hour to brown chicken.
Check to baste or turn chicken parts over so top ones don't overbrown and move bottom pieces to top so they brown.

title: fruit salad
directions: Add enough water to reserved juices to make 3 cups liquid. Add remaining ingredients, except fruit.
Bring to boiling and cook 1 minute. Cool.
Mix in fruit and maraschino cherries (as many as you like).
Chill.
Add several sliced bananas before serving.

title: peanut brittle(microwave)
directions: In 1 1/2-quart casserole, stir first 3 ingredients together. Microwave at High for 4 minutes.
Stir in peanuts.
Microwave at High 3 to 5 minutes until light brown.
Add butter and vanilla to syrup, blending well.
Microwave on High 1 to 2 minutes more. Peanuts will be lightly browned and syrup very hot.
Add baking soda and gently stir until light and foamy.

title: banana smunchies
directions: Mash very ripe bananas into a smooth paste.
Mix in peanut butter.
Chill well.
Drop 2 tablespoons onto one square graham cracker.
Cover with second graham cracker square.
Freeze until ready to use.
Yield:
26 servings.
Serving Size:
1 Smunchie.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix in big bowl potatoes, sour cream, soup, dip, salt and pepper.
Now stir in cheese.
Put in greased baking dish.
Pour melted butter on top.
Sprinkle crushed corn flakes on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: spicy chicken pasta
directions: Cut chicken into small pieces, season with salt, pepper, garlic salt and Italian seasoning. Brown in olive oil. Cook vegetables. When chicken is done, add vegetables and can of tomatoes & salsa. Cook spaghetti noodles. When noodles are done, mix all ingredients together in a large serving bowl.

title: party and picnic meatballs
directions: In crock-pot or slow cooker, dissolve jelly in spaghetti sauce.
While that is heating, mix all other ingredients with enough bread crumbs so it holds together.
Roll into small balls and brown on all sides.
Drop into sauce and cook on medium about 3 hours.
Can be made ahead and reheated.

title: three corn souffle
directions: Cook onion and pepper.
Add tomatoes and cool.
Mix with corns.
Add yolks, cheese and corn mix.
Combine well.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold into mixture.
Bake in greased casserole (1 or 1 1/2-quart size) at 300° for 1 hour.
Do not have to serve immediately.

title: barbecue brisket
directions: Fold brisket in foil with all above and marinate 24 hours. Bake at 200° for 8 hours.
Pour small bottle barbecue sauce over meat.
Bake 15 more minutes.
Let stand 5 to 10 minutes.

title: texas school cake
directions: Mix cocoa, oleo, water and oil in pan.
Bring to boil; pour over sugar and flour which have been stirred together.
Add buttermilk, soda, eggs and vanilla.
Stir well and pour into greased and floured 12 x 8-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for about 15 minutes.

title: pennsylvania dutch pot pie(chicken)
directions: Boil chicken in enough water to cover chicken for approximately 45 minutes; cool and debone chicken.
Keep chicken broth.

title: pork chops
directions: Put pork chops in baking dish. Mix Coke and ketchup. Pour over pork chops. Sprinkle brown sugar on top. Bake at 350° about an hour or until tender.

title: lemon butter icing
directions: Blend all ingredients together; beat until smooth and fluffy. If necessary, thin with a few drops of milk.

title: squash dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 400°.

title: great lemon cucumber salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together, place in glass square dish, if possible.
Chill until jellied.
Serve on lettuce leaf with mayonnaise on top.

title: fat-free chocolate sauce
directions: In a small saucepan, stir together sugar, cocoa powder and cornstarch.
Add milk.
Cook and stir constantly over medium heat until sauce is thickened and bubbly.
Cook and stir for two minutes more.
Remove from heat.
Stir in the vanilla.
Cool sauce slightly.

title: caramel corn
directions: Bring to a soft-ball stage. Remove from heat. Stir in 1 teaspoon baking soda. Pour over air popped popcorn (6 quarts). Stir very good. Bake in 200° oven for 1 hour, stirring every 20 minutes. Stir just before dumping onto countertop. Gently break into small pieces. Enjoy!

title: pasta and bean soup("low-fat")
directions: In stockpot, combine first 9 ingredients.
Heat just to boiling, reduce heat and simmer 25 minutes. Stir in beans and green pepper. Simmer 10 minutes. Add macaroni and heat through. Makes 12 cups.

title: oriental pot roast
directions: Brown meat in oil until browned on all sides.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over browned meat.
Simmer on stove top for approximately 2 hours or until meat is tender.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: orange delight cake
directions: Mix well and bake cake in 3 greased and floured 9 to 10 inch pans for 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.	Cool before frosting.

title: peach custard cake
directions: Arrange peaches on crust.
Sprinkle sugar and cinnamon.
Bake 20 minutes.
Mix reserved syrup, milk and egg.
Pour over peaches. Bake 30 minutes more.
Total baking time is 50 minutes or until custard is firm.

title: dill pot roast
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
Coat pot roast with lemon pepper, salt and pepper.
Brown roast in bacon drippings on both sides. Combine soup mix, pickles and Worcestershire sauce; pour over browned roast.

title: nutty noodle crunch
directions: Combine noodles, raisins, peanuts, almonds and coconut.
Heat butter and honey to boiling and remove from heat.
Stir in the vanilla.
Pour over noodle mixture. Toss to coat evenly. Spread in a 10 x 15-inch baking pan. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Loosen from pan and cool. Store in airtight container.
Makes 7 cups.

title: baked caramel corn
directions: Melt butter; stir in brown sugar, corn syrup and salt.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Boil without stirring for 5 minutes.
Remove from the heat; stir in soda and vanilla. Gradually pour over popcorn, mixing well.
Turn into two large shallow baking pans.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Cool completely.
Break apart and store in a tightly covered container.

title: four bean salad
directions: Drain beans.
Mix in onion and celery to beans.
Whiz oil, lemon juice and sugar in blender.
Pour over bean mixture.
For best results, marinate 12 hours or overnight.

title: chicken risotto
directions: Place chicken pieces skin side down in a large skillet over very low heat.
(Do not add fat).
Cook chicken slowly in its own fat until skin side is rich brown, about 10 minutes.
Turn and brown other side.
Remove chicken from skillet with tongs.
Add rice and seasoning packet from risotto mix to pan fat; stir to coat rice with fat.
Pour chicken broth into a 4 cup measure.
Add water to make 2 1/2 cups.
Stir into the rice mix; bring to boiling.
Arrange chicken pieces over mixture.
Lower heat and cover.
Simmer 20 minutes or until chicken is tender and liquid is absorbed.
Stir in olives.
Fluff up rice.
Great for lunch or dinner party.
Serves 4.

title: hobo beans
directions: Brown hamburger; drain off any excess grease.
Mix with onion soup.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Bake in covered baking dish at 400° for 45 minutes.

title: snack pizzas
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Put a little grease or oil on the baking sheet.
Pat each biscuit into a 4-inch circle.
Put each circle on baking sheet.
Mix tomato sauce and oregano in a measuring cup.
Spoon some on each biscuit.
Put pepperoni on top of the sauce.
Sprinkle with the cheese.
Bake about 8 minutes or until crust is lightly brown.

title: butterscotch crunchies
directions: In large saucepan, melt butterscotch chips and peanut butter. Remove from heat; stir in corn flakes.
Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Let set.
Makes 36.

title: oatmeal apple cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease cookie sheet with shortening. Combine shortening, sugar, egg, milk and vanilla in large bowl. Beat at medium speed of electric mixer until well blended.
Combine flour, cinnamon, salt, baking soda and nutmeg in small bowl.
Mix into creamed mixture at low speed until just blended.
Stir in, one at a time, oats, apples, raisins and nuts with spoon.
Drop rounded tablespoonfuls of dough 2 inches apart onto cookie sheet.
Bake for 13 minutes or until set.
Cool 2 minutes on cookie sheet.
Remove to wire rack.

title: salmon mousse
directions: Soften gelatin in cold water.
Add boiling water and stir until dissolved; cool.
Add mayonnaise, lemon juice and rind, onion, Tabasco, paprika and salt.
Mix well.
Chill to consistency of unbeaten egg white.
Add salmon and capers; beat well.
Whip cream and into salmon mixture.
Turn into 5 1/2 cup oiled fish mold.
Add cheese and fill mold.
Chill until set.
Unmold on serving platter.
Garnish with watercress and lemon slices.

title: spoon bread
directions: Scald milk in a double boiler.
Gradually stir in the corn meal and cook until the consistency of mush.
Add butter, salt and sugar and pour over the well-beaten eggs gradually, while stirring.
Pour into a greased 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Bake in a hot oven at 425° for 45 minutes.
Serve at once with plenty of butter.
Serves 6.

title: spice fruit dip
directions: Mix sugar and spices in a small bowl gently.
Stir into whipped topping.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Sprinkle additional cinnamon on top, if desired.
Serve as a dip with apple, pear, peach and melon slices, cookies or pound cake cubes.

title: easy black bean soup with sausage
directions: In a 3-quart saucepan, combine carrots, celery and water. Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes or until vegetables are crisp and tender.

title: guacamole salad spread
directions: In small saucepan, sprinkle unflavored gelatine over cold water; let stand 1 minute.
Stir over low heat until gelatine is completely dissolved, about 5 minutes.
Stir in dressing, hot pepper sauce, chili powder and salt.

title: chicken corn soup
directions: Cut up and cook chicken in enough water to cover it.
After it is well cooked, remove meat from bones, cut it up fine and return to broth.
Dice onion and celery and add to broth.
Add corn and cook until vegetables are done.
Add small rivvels by mixing flour, egg, salt and pepper until mixture is crumbly.
Drop into broth and simmer 15 minutes more.
This soup can be simmered as long as you wish.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except bacon.
Put in a greased casserole dish.
Top with bacon slices.
Bake at 350° until bacon is done.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Fry ground beef with chopped onion.
Pour grease and all in casserole dish.
Pour corn over meat.
Pour tomatoes or tomato juice over the corn.
Mix meal, sweet milk and egg.
Spoon on top and bake at 400° until bread is done.

title: peanut soup
directions: Wash tomato.
Peel onion.
Cut both into small pieces.
Peel and cut potato into small pieces.
Place in a pot with water, bones and salt to taste.
Boil until soft.
Mix ground nuts (peanuts) with milk.
Add to pot with rice and cook 1/2 hour more. Remove bones and serve.

title: seoul chicken
directions: In a small bowl, mix vinegar, soy sauce, honey and ginger. Place oil in a large frying pan and heat to medium temperature. Add chicken and cook, turning, until brown on all sides, about 10 minutes. Add garlic and red pepper.
Cook, while stirring, for 2 to 3 minutes. Add vinegar mixture. Cover and cook about 15 minutes or until chicken is fork-tender.
Uncover and cook 1 to 2 minutes or until sauce is slightly thick. Serve with rice.
Makes 4 servings.

title: cranberry congealed salad
directions: Mix Jell-O as directed. Add cream cheese; mix well. Add other ingredients. Refrigerate. This is great with chicken and dressing.

title: potatoes bob
directions: Grease pan.
Combine all ingredients and bake at 375° until potatoes are soft.

title: potato cakes
directions: Peel potatoes; boil and mash well.
Add butter and work in the flour.
Turn onto a floured board; roll out to 1/2-inch thickness. Cut into rounds or triangles.
Cook in slightly greased pan for 3 minutes on each side, pricking with a fork.
Makes about 20 cakes. Delicious with sausage or bacon.

title: knobby apple cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening; add egg and beat well.
Sift together flour, cinnamon and baking soda; add to mixture, then add vanilla.
Fold in apples and nuts.
Batter will be quite stiff, but apples will moisten.
Pour batter into 8 x 8-inch greased and floured dish.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Cut into squares.
Delicious topped with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: linguine salad
directions: Prepare linguine according to package directions.
Dice vegetables while linguine is cooking.
Drain linguine well.
Mix in seasoning.
Add vegetables and Italian dressing.
Mix well and chill overnight.

title: cheese dip
directions: Brown hamburger meat.
Melt cheese and cheese soup add rest of the ingredients.
Serve with Frito scooper or tortilla chips or veggies.

title: frozen strawberry salad
directions: Cream the cream cheese and sugar.
Fold in all ingredients gently.
Freeze overnight in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Remove from freezer 30 minutes before serving.
Cut into squares.
Serves 12.

title: crabmeat pate
directions: Heat soup in a medium saucepan over low heat.
Remove from heat.
Dissolve gelatin in cold water.
Add to soup, stirring well.
Add next five ingredients and mix well.
Spoon into an oiled 4 cup mold.
Chill until firm.
Unmold and garnish with parsley.
Serve with assorted crackers.

title: lasagna
directions: For
sauce,
cook
ground
beef in skillet until brown. Add salt,
pepper and minced garlic; add spaghetti sauce.
Use 1 jar of
spaghetti sauce and 1 jar of Italian cooking sauce. Simmer about
10 minutes.
Start layers in pan (1 layer sauce, 1
layer noodles).
Spread
Ricotta
cheese
over
noodles. Sprinkle
with Mozzarella and Parmesan cheese.
Repeat layers ending with sauce. Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: tuna salad
directions: Combine tuna, relish and eggs in a medium sized bowl.
Add salad dressing; may be eaten as a salad with crackers or spread on bread for a sandwich.

title: lemon cake
directions: Beat cake mix, lemon pudding, oil, water and eggs until well blended.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Let cake cool.
Mix powdered sugar and lemon juice, then pour over cake for a glaze.

title: sausage rolls
directions: Mix sausages together well and chill for 30 minutes.
Mix Bisquick, margarine and milk.
Divide sausage into 3 parts. Divide Bisquick mixture into 3 parts and roll out in rectangles. Spread sausage on each rectangle and roll up like jelly roll.

title: gourmet spaghetti
directions: Saute celery in margarine. Blend in herbs and spice mix from dinner and flour.
Gradually add milk.
Cook, stirring constantly until thickened.
Add shrimp.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes.

title: sweet potato delight
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into 1-quart baking dish.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Top with marshmallows and lightly brown. Makes 6 servings.

title: zucchini nut bars
directions: Mix ingredients together, adding 2 cups grated zucchini.
Pour into an ungreased cookie sheet.

title: hoagie salad
directions: Place layer of shredded lettuce in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with layer of chipped ham.
Add layer of cheese.
Place another layer of lettuce.
Sprinkle diced onions over this layer.
Add carrots on top of this layer and spread mayonnaise over carrots.
Sprinkle grated cheese, then bacon bits over the top.
Let sit in the refrigerator for 12 hours, then top with tomato slices.

title: healthy breakfast bread
directions: Set aside 1 cup white flour.
Mix remaining flours, nuts, yeast, peel and salt.
Heat milk, honey and oil to 125° to 130°; do not boil.
Stir into dry ingredients.
Add enough dry flour reserved to make dough workable. Knead about 8 minutes.
Cover and let rise 10 minutes.
Divide and form into 6 balls and place 3 into each pan that is greased.
Cover and let rise, 30 to 45 minutes.
Bake at 375°
for 45 minutes.
Cover loaves with foil last 15 minutes.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix together flour, baking powder and salt.
Work shortening and peanut butter together in a bowl until creamy.
Add sugar and beat until light and fluffy.
Add egg and vanilla; beat thoroughly.
Add dry ingredients; mix until smooth.
Form a 1/2-inch ball.
Place 2 inches apart on a cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 375°.
Makes 3 dozen cookies.

title: fireside coffee mix
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Store in airtight container.
To serve: Mix 2 tablespoons with 1 cup of hot water and serve.

title: oven-fried parmesan chicken
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients; mix well.
Dip chicken in butter and dredge in cracker crumb mixture.
Place chicken in a lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.
Yield: 4 servings.

title: peachy wizard
directions: Drain peaches, reserving syrup.
Add cold milk to syrup to make 2 cups.
Set aside 5 peaches for garnish.
Dice remaining peaches.
Pour measured liquid into a deep narrow-bottom bowl. Add pudding mix.
Beat slowly with hand mixer or at lowest speed of electric mixer until well blended, about 2 minutes.
Quickly stir in peaches and pour at once into individual dessert dishes. Let stand to set, about 5 minutes.
Garnish with reserved peach slices.
Makes about 2 1/2 cups or 5 servings.

title: grilled ranch bread
directions: Combine butter with dressing mix.
Slice bread lengthwise and spread tops with butter mixture.
Place bread under broiler until crispy and golden brown.

title: lazy pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt 1/3 cup shortening or margarine in a 2 x 9 x 9-inch cake pan.
Combine flour, salt, milk and sugar and pour over margarine.
Drop over batter, fruit and juice.
Sprinkle with cinnamon-sugar.
Bake for 25 minutes.

title: natchez cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Add flour, sifted twice with salt; add 1 egg and 1 egg yolk. Add whiskey. Spread dough evenly and spread egg white on top of this letting excess run out corners of pan. Sprinkle on sugar, cinnamon and nuts; press slightly. Bake in shallow pan (10 x 15-inch) in 325° oven for 40 minutes. Let cool and cut into squares.

title: cowboy quiche
directions: Beat eggs, flour and evaporated milk together and season to taste with salt and pepper.
Pour mixture over cheese and chilies. Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.
Allow quiche to set 15 minutes before serving.

title: garlic chicken pasta with prosciutto
directions: Heat oil in a large skillet and saute garlic until soft and light brown. Add tomatoes, proscuitto, chicken and butter; saute for about 5 to 10 minutes. Add basil, and saute for another 5 minutes. In a stockpot, bring water to boil and cook linguine until firm, al dente. Drain pasta and transfer to a bowl, add the chicken/tomato mixture and cheese; toss gently to combine. Sprinkle with basil and serve. Prep Time: 30 minutes. Cook Time:30 minutes Yields 8 servings.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut biscuits into 4 pieces.
Roll in sugar and cinnamon.
Put in well-greased Bundt pan.
Melt butter and stir in brown sugar and water.
Pour over biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sausage roll-ups
directions: Pop frozen pie crust out of foil pan and place upside-down on sheet of waxed paper to thaw, about 10 minutes.
Flatten thawed pie crust by gently pressing down.
Spread sausage evenly on top of crust to 1/2-inch from edge.
Begin at one end and roll up pie crust jelly roll style.
Cut off excess crust 1/2-inch from each end.
Slice roll into 1/2-inch slices.
Arrange slices with cut edge flat on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes until crust is browned.
Serve warm.
Makes 12 pinwheel appetizers.

title: ranch-style baked beans
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In large skillet, melt butter or margarine and brown meat.
Stir in soup.
Mix beans, catsup, water, mustard and vinegar.
Pour into a 2 1/2-quart casserole or bean pot.
Bake 30 to 45 minutes.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Mix Jell-O and water until Jell-O is dissolved.
Let set until jelly-like. Stir well and mix in cucumber, onion, carrots, green pepper, cottage cheese and Miracle Whip.
Chill until set.

title: praline pie
directions: To make praline layer:
Cream butter with one-third cup brown sugar in small bowl.
Stir in pecans.
Press over bottom of pie shell in even layer.
Bake in hot 450° oven for 10 minutes; remove.
Cool 10 minutes.
Lower heat to 350°.

title: orange buttermilk molded salad
directions: In saucepan, bring pineapple and sugar to boil.
Remove from heat and stir in gelatin.
Cool to room temperature and add buttermilk.
Fold in topping and pecans.
Pour into 8-cup mold and chill 4 hours or overnight.

title: corn bread
directions: Cream together the margarine and sugar. Add eggs. Sift corn meal, flour, soda and salt. Add to margarine and sugar alternately with buttermilk. Bake around 30 minutes at 350° in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: layered ranchero dip
directions: On a 15 x 10 inch shallow serving platter, thinly spread bean dip.
In a small bowl, combine sour cream, mayonnaise, and taco seasoning mix; spread over bean dip.
Sprinkle with cheese, onions, tomatoes, and olives.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: delicious punch
directions: Mix well and refrigerate.

title: pizza meat loaf
directions: Mix all, except sauce and cheese, together.
Press into 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Pour off drippings. Spread pizza sauce over and bake for 10 minutes.
Sprinkle grated cheese over all; bake until melted.
Remove from oven and serve.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Layer cabbage, meat mixture, rice and canned tomato soup. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cheese log (ball)
directions: Mix all together and form into a log or ball.

title: old fashion chocolate cake
directions: Cream the sugar, butter and Wesson oil. Add eggs, one at a time. Sift flour and baking soda together.
Add flour mixture alternately with buttermilk and vanilla. Beat for 2 minutes. Bake small layers (about 3/4 cup batter to each pan).
Makes 7 layers. Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Mix in large bowl chicken, chicken soup, mushroom soup and Ro-Tel; stir well.
Crush nacho chips and add to mixture.
Put in a casserole dish and cook about 20 to 30 minutes or until it's hot all the way through.
Remove from oven and top with cheese.
Put back into oven until cheese is melted.

title: green rice
directions: Cook rice. Saute onion and celery in oleo. Cook broccoli.
Mix all ingredients and pour into casserole dish.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken pie
directions: Boil chicken. Take
meat
off bone.
Place chicken in a large casserole dish.
Put
chopped
onion,
salt
and pepper. Set aside.
Put cream
of
chicken soup and chicken broth in a saucepan. Bring to	a
boil.
Pour	over
chicken.	Make
sure broth gets under the chicken.
Next melt margarine.
Mix flour and milk until
smooth.
Add
melted
margarine.
Stir
until smooth. Pour over chicken. Do not stir.
It will make its own crust. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: winnie the pooh's microwave custard
directions: Break the eggs into a 5 or 6-cup glass bowl and beat lightly with a fork.
Add the milk and sugar and beat again until it is well mixed.
Microwave on High for 4 to 6 minutes, stirring every 2 minutes, just until the custard starts to thicken.
It will continue to cook after you take it out of the microwave.
Stir in vanilla or lemon extract.
Pour the custard into 6 custard cups. Cover the cups with waxed paper and let the custard cool and set completely.
Serves 6.

title: easy chocolate pudding
directions: In heavy saucepan, large enough for the amount of pudding you are going to make, heat 3/4 of the milk until bubbles form around the edges.
Add chocolate, stirring until melted.
Add sugar to milk mixture.
Stir cornstarch into reserved 1/4 of the milk. Stir into pudding along with salt.
Cook, stirring, until bubbling and thickened.
Fold in vanilla.

title: lemon brownies
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients together.
Spread in a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle the pecan pieces over mixture in pan.
Beat the cream cheese, eggs and confectioners sugar with mixer until creamy.
Pour over dough in pan.
Bake in a 325° preheated oven until brown, approximately 30 minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake uncovered at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: apple pie
directions: Place apples in unbaked crust.
Pat butter over top of apples. Sprinkle sugar, cinnamon, nutmeg and allspice over top.
Cover with unbaked crust.
Cut slits in top and brush with butter and sugar. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken hmmmm
directions: Sprinkle breasts with parsley and garlic powder.
Roll in butter, then dressing mix.
Place in a greased baking dish. Sprinkle remaining crumbs over chicken and moisten lightly with water.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: dad's best baked beans
directions: Combine all ingredients in a 9 x 9-inch square baking pan; mix well.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 6.

title: quick beef hash
directions: Brown steak in oil.
Remove and add roux and one cup of water. Add seasonings; cook 10 minutes.
Put steak back in and add beef broth.
Cook about one hour.
Add potatoes and peas and carrots. Cook 1/2 hour.
Add tops and parsley.
Serve over grits or rice.

title: french bread puff
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cut
bread	at 1-inch intervals but not in slices.
Mix margarine, garlic powder and onion.
Spoon mixture between slices and	spread	evenly.
Wrap loaf in foil and place on ungreased
baking
sheet.
Heat	for
15 minutes. While bread is heating,
beat
egg
whites until stiff.
Separately beat egg yolks until
thick.
Fold egg yolks and cheese into egg whites. When loaf is ready, fold back foil to make a skirt.
Spoon egg mixture
over
loaf.
Bake	until topping is golden brown (about 4 minutes).

title: sponge cake
directions: *Or 1/2 teaspoon cream of tartar and 1/2 teaspoon soda.

title: "stuffing lasagna"
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Brown meat in large skillet on medium-high heat.
Add 1 cup of the sauce and water; bring to boil.
Add stuffing mix, stir just to moisten.
Remove from heat.
Beat egg in medium bowl; stir in Ricotta and Parmesan cheese, spoon 1/2 of stuffing mixture evenly into 8-inch square baking dish.
Spoon half of the cheese mixture over stuffing mixture.
Top with 1/2 cup each Mozzarella cheese and sauce.
Repeat layers with remaining stuffing and cheese mixture (1/2 cup sauce and 1 cup Mozzarella cheese). Bake 40 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Let stand 5 minutes.
tags: Stove Top chicken flavor stuffing mix in canister

title: mary ann's salad dressing
directions: Mix 1 bunch leaf lettuce and 1 bunch green onions. Pour dressing over greens just before serving and toss to mix. Tastes like wilted lettuce salad.

title: london broil
directions: Mix ingredients and marinate steak overnight. Broil or grill steak rare. Slice diagonally and thin.

title: quick hot fudge sauce
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a saucepan; blend well. Gradually add water; cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until smooth and thickened.
Bring mixture to a boil; boil 2 minutes, stir in vanilla.
Serve hot over cake or ice cream. Store in refrigerator; reheat as needed.

title: chicken with tarragon sauce
directions: Saut onions, garlic and 1 Tbsp. tarragon in butter till onions are lightly browned.
Add chicken breasts and brown on both sides.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Place browned chicken in covered baking dish and set aside.
In the same pan add wine and 1 Tbsp. chopped tarragon and bring to a high simmer.
Pour wine mixture over chicken breasts and bake in 300 degree oven in covered dish for 1 hour.
After chicken has baked, drain off the wine and chicken broth into skillet.
Add whipping cream and bring to a high simmer.
Add flour to desired thickness. Cook pasta according to directions on package.
Serve chicken breasts on pasta covered with plenty of sauce. Serves 6.

title: beef jerky
directions: Place meat in freezer for 2 to 3 hours.
Slice into 1/4 inch slices.
Place all ingredients in a glass or plastic bowl.
Add meat.
Refrigerate overnight.
Drain meat and pat dry.
Line cookie sheet with foil.
Place meat on cooling racks on cookie sheets.
Cook for 8 1/2 to 10 hours with door cracked open at 150° or warm.
Let cool.
Store in airtight container.

title: cacoila(portuguese beef with pork)
directions: Combine
all
ingredients
in
good
sized pot and cook slowly for
1/2 hours or until meat is tender.
Add only a little salt at the beginning.
Later add more salt and pepper to taste. Add warm water, if needed.
Stir often.

title: coconut cake
directions: Mix cake according to box directions, making 4 thin layers. Mix sugar, coconut and sour cream,
stirring well until sugar has dissolved. Spread between layers and cover cake with Cool Whip.

title: family size potato omelet
directions: Chop fresh or frozen chives, unthawed.
Heat 1 tablespoon oil in a nonstick 12-inch skillet over medium heat.
Add onion and next 4 ingredients.
Cook until onion and green pepper are crisp and tender.
Whisk together eggs and water in a bowl.
Stir in vegetable mixture.
Wipe skillet with a paper towel.
Heat skillet over medium heat.
Add remaining 2 tablespoons oil, rotating pan to coat bottom.
Add egg mixture.
As mixture starts to cook, gently lift edges off omelet with a spatula and tilt pan so uncooked portion flows underneath.
Cover and cook 5 minutes to allow portion on top to set.
Cut in fourths.
Serve immediately with sour cream and chives.
Yields 4 servings.

title: hamburger yummy
directions: Brown meat and onions; drain off grease.
Add rice and beans; cook until warm.
Pour in long cake pan.
Top with sliced cheese. Put in oven and heat till cheese is melted and bubbly.
Serve with Fritos.

title: blueberry banana pie
directions: Mix cream cheese, Cool Whip and 1 cup sugar until creamy. Slice bananas and lay on cooled pie crust.
Pour cream cheese mixture over bananas.

title: old dutch apple strudel
directions: Arrange apples in a buttered baking dish.
Drizzle honey over apples and sprinkle with cinnamon and lemon juice.
In a large bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda and salt. Stir in beaten egg until mixture is crumbly.
Spoon the mixture evenly over the apples.

title: baked french toast
directions: Beat eggs. Add flour, sugar, cinnamon, allspice, salt, baking powder and vanilla.
Mix until smooth. Beat in milk.
Pour into baking dish that has been sprayed with Pam. Dip bread into mixture, turn over, cover and refrigerate overnight. Before baking, turn slices over.
Melt butter and drizzle over top. Bake at 400° for 10 minutes. Turn bread and bake an additional 5 minutes until golden brown.
Serve with syrup, cinnamon sugar, confectioners sugar or any other topping of your choice.

title: cold taco dip
directions: Mix all together and spread on a cookie sheet.
Layer on 1/2 head shredded lettuce chopped green onions, 3 to 4 chopped tomatoes, 1/2 to 1 pound grated Longhorn cheese and sliced jalapeno peppers.

title: coconut-crusted chicken fingers
directions: Combine tempura batter mix and beer in a shallow dish and set aside. Combine coconut and almonds. Dip each chicken strip into batter mixture, then roll in coconut mixture, pressing firmly to coat well. Pour oil to depth of 1 1/2-inches into a Dutch oven. Heat to 350°. Fry chicken strips, in batches, 2 minutes or until golden. Drain well on paper towels. Repeat procedure with remaining chicken strips. Serve chicken fingers with Honey-Mustard Sauce.

title: chili
directions: Brown hamburger and onion; drain off any grease.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer.

title: quiche 2
directions: Beat eggs and cream together.
Stir in pepper and Swiss cheese.
Saute shrimp and mushrooms for 10 minutes; add onion and salt, if desired.
Stir into egg/cheese mixture.
Pour into pie crusts.
Sprinkle with parsley and Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 375° 30 to 35 minutes or until top is golden.

title: fried chicken coating mix
directions: Combine the first nine ingredients.
Store in an airtight container.
When ready to fry chicken, dip into the egg and milk mixture then into the coating and fry in oil.

title: homemade barbecue
directions: Cook garlic, onions, peppers, tomatoes and red crushed peppers together until tender.
Add water as needed.
Make sure that the fat is cut off the meat.
Then cook the steak and chicken together in a pressure cooker for about 30 minutes.
(Do not save broth.) After cooking the meats, tear apart.
Then add all the ingredients, including the sugar and barbecue sauce together. Cook until cooked down.
Serves 6 to 10 people or can be frozen.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Add first 6 ingredients to meat and simmer 45 to 60 minutes.
Combine cottage cheese with eggs, parsley, Parmesan cheese, salt and pepper.
Layer in lasagna pan, noodles, meat mixture, cottage cheese mixture and Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: creamed spinach
directions: Cook spinach and drain thoroughly.
Combine with sour cream and soup mix in casserole dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Serves 4.

title: irish bread("a gaelic blessing")
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and soda.
Set aside. Cream butter and sugar.
Add beaten egg and buttermilk; blend well.
Add liquid mixture to dry ingredients.
Mix by hand only until dry ingredients are well moistened.
Fold in raisins and caraway seed.
Pour into Crisco floured 1 1/2-quart pan or 1 1/2-quart glass casserole.
Brush top with melted butter and sprinkle with a little sugar.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes. Reduce to 325°.
Bake for 30 minutes in 13 x 4 x 3-inch pan.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: *I start with 2 cups of water to be sure I have 1 1/2 cups when needed.

title: zurich apple cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar in a bowl until fluffy.
Add grated lemon peel; add eggs, one at a time, beating after each.
Sift flour and baking powder while mixing.
Add milk, 1 tablespoon at a time.
Mix until smooth.
Pour ingredients into a greased round pan.

title: a-b-c potatoes(at home - barbecue - camping)
directions: For barbecue or camping:
Make pan out of heavy-duty foil by folding in half a 36 x 18-inch piece and folding up sides to form a pouch.
Place potatoes into pouch; cover with carrots and onions.
Sprinkle salt, pepper, paprika, parsley and dot with butter and seed.
Fold foil to seal, leaving room for steam. Grill on grill for 55 to 60 minutes until done, turning several times.
Open package and cover veggies with cheese and crumbled bacon.
Re-close (tightly) foil and return to grill for about 1 minute to allow cheese to melt.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Saute onion and pepper.
Add flour and stir until smooth; gradually stir in milk.
Add other ingredients except reserved and cook 10 minutes.
Place cooked noodles in two 13 x 9-inch pans and cover with cooked mixture.
Repeat layers once.
Top with cheese, almonds and mushrooms.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Serves 16 to 20.

title: golden sherbet punch
directions: Combine sugar and mint with two cups of boiling water in a bowl.
Cool and strain.
Add lemon juice, apricot nectar, lime juice, orange juice and pineapple juice.
Mix and chill.
Add ginger ale and sherbet just before serving.
Serves 20 to 25.

title: celeste's sunflower oatmeal bread
directions: In small bowl combine yeast, sugar and warm water and stir to dissolve.
Let stand until foamy, about 10 minutes.
Combine buttermilk, honey, molasses and butter in small bowl.
In large bowl combine whole wheat flour, oats and sunflower seeds.
Add buttermilk mixture, yeast mixture and egg.
Mix well.
Add flour, about 1/2 cup at a time until soft dough.
Turn dough onto lightly floured surface, knead for about 5 minutes.
Add flour until smooth and springy dough.
Place in greased bowl and turn to cover top. Cover with plastic wrap and rise until doubled, about 1 1/2 hours. Gently deflate dough onto floured surface.
Divide into 3 round loaves.
Place on greased baking sheet loosely sprinkled with oats. Wrap lightly with plastic.
Rise 30 minutes until doubled.
Place in oven, preheated to 375° for about 30 minutes.
Makes 3 small round loaves.

title: 3-layer strawberry salad
directions: First Layer:
Mix pretzels, 1/4 cup sugar and margarine and pat into 9 X 13 pan.
Bake 8 minutes at 400 degrees.

title: swedish apple pie
directions: Cream egg and sugar, then add flour, baking powder and salt. Mix well.
Add vanilla, apples and nuts.
Grease pie plate.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: quick 'n easy salmon
directions: Rinse fillet and place it in a Pyrex casserole dish.
Pierce repeatedly with fork, then pour on soy sauce and lemon juice. Sprinkle on salt, m.s.g. and spices.
Cover dish with plastic wrap.
Set aside overnight or for 30 minutes.
To cook, place in microwave for 12 minutes on High or wrap in foil and place on grill for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: calopie(pinto beans and pork roast)
directions: Mix all together and cover with water. Cook on very low heat for about 4 hours.
I cut the roast in big slices and all was done in 3 hours. Serves 4 generously.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour water over oatmeal and let stand 20 minutes.
Cream margarine; add sugars and eggs.
Beat on medium speed for 2 minutes.
Add oatmeal to mixture and beat for 2 more minutes.
Add remaining ingredients and blend well.
Bake 35 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: marinated mushrooms
directions: Clean and trim ends from mushrooms; set aside.
Combine the next 6 ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Stir in mushrooms.
Reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes.
Let cool.
Cover; chill 8 hours.
Stir occasionally.
Drain and serve.
Great appetizer.

title: shrimp creole
directions: In a large saucepan (1 gal), over medium heat, melt the butter. Add the onions, peppers, and celery to the pan. Season the vegetables with salt and cayenne. Saute the vegetables until they are wilted, About 6 to 8 minutes. Stir in the bay leaves, tomatoes, and garlic. Simmer the mixture with the Worcestershire sauce and hot sauce. Whisk the flour and water together. Add the flour mixture to the tomato mixture and continue to cook for 4 to 6 minutes. Season the shrimp with Essence.
