Add the shrimp to the mixture and continue to cook for 4 to 6 minutes or until the shrimp turns pink and curl up. Stir in the green onions and parsley. Taste to see if more seasoning is needed.

title: holiday nut cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and beat.
Add flour and beat well.
Add nuts and fruit to mixture.
Stir with a spoon. Grease a cake pan.
Pour batter in and bake at 250 for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: pizza burgers
directions: Grind Spam and cheese.
Brown ground beef (drain).
Add to Spam and cheese.
Add salt, Italian seasoning, parsley and spaghetti sauce.
Put on buns (open-faced).

title: spiced pear jam
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large heavy pot.
Simmer uncovered for 1 1/2 to 2 hours or until thickened.
Stir frequently.
Remove from heat and skim off foam.
Pour hot jam into hot jars leaving 1/4-inch space.
Adjust caps.
Process for 10 minutes in boiling water.
Yield:
6 half pints.

title: pecan pralines
directions: Cook sugar, salt and milk until it boils.
Add butter and let remain on fire until completely melted.
Remove from fire and beat until thick.
Add nuts and vanilla.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper.
If candy is too thick to handle, reheat to consistency desired.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: pumpkin muffins
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, oil and pumpkin.
Stir in other ingredients. Spray muffin tin with Pam cooking spray, and fill approximately 1/3 full with batter.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Serve hot or cold with butter.
Makes 18 lg. or 24 small muffins.

title: mrs. denver's baked chicken croquettes
directions: Make a thick white sauce of the first 4 ingredients in a medium saucepan.
Cool slightly.
Add the eggs, chicken, cheese and seasonings.
Chill until easy to handle.
Preheat oven to 400°.
Shape chicken mixture into 12 cone or patty shapes; roll in crumbs and place on a baking pan that has been greased with 3 tablespoons butter or margarine.
Bake until well browned, 20 to 30 minutes.
Serve with sauce.
Serves 6.

title: cream of anything soup
directions: Steam vegetables until tender.
In blender puree a third of vegetables using water cooked in.
Melt margarine in large pot. Add flour, stirring until it begins to brown.
Slowly add milk. Add both pureed vegetables and steamed vegetables, soy sauce, basil and rice.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Do not boil.

title: brown bread
directions: Mix
the
raisins
with
hot
water and let stand until cool. Add rest of the ingredients and mix.
Place in either a loaf
pan or fill 3 (No. 2) cans half full.
Bake for about 1 hour at 350°.

title: strawberry pretzel dessert
directions: Mix pretzels, sugar and oleo and pat in bottom of 13 X 9 pan. Bake at 375 for 10 minutes. Beat together cream cheese and sugar. Fold in cool whip
and spread over baked crust. Put in refrigerator to chill. Dissolve jello in 2 1/4 c. hot water and add frozen strawberries. cool this mixture and pour
on top of chilled layer. Refrigerate.

title: chicken or turkey rouladens
directions: Pound chicken or turkey breast very thin.
Cut cheese a little smaller than breasts.
Place on breasts; cover with ham.
Roll up; fasten with toothpicks or thread.
Roll in flour seasoned with salt and pepper.
Dip in the eggs, then in bread crumbs.
Melt oleo in skillet; saute the rolls over low heat until browned on all sides.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Mix all soups together with the rice and put into large casserole or a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put the chicken on top of soups and water.
Sprinkle chicken with onion soup mix (use all).
Bake at 350° for 1 hour (45 minutes with lid on, 15 minutes with lid off).

title: chicken magnific
directions: Melt margarine in frypan; add chicken and cook until white (covered on low heat).
Add chicken soup and seasonings.
Add mushroom soup and water.
Cook 30 to 40 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: mayonnaise baked chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Dip
chicken pieces in mixture and then roll in bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: beer batter bread
directions: Coat inside of loaf pan with nonstick cooking spray.
Combine flour, whole wheat flour, sugar, salt and yeast in large bowl. Combine beer, butter and molasses in small saucepan.
Heat to very warm (125° to 135°).
Pour into flour mixture; add egg.
Mix at low speed to blend.
Then beat at medium speed for 2 minutes, scraping down side of bowl as necessary.
Scrape dough down from sides, forming one mass; lightly oil top of batter.
Cover and let rise in warm place for 30 minutes.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients, except cheese.
Stir until well mixed.
Pour in pan and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake in 325° oven for about 20 to 30 minutes, until cheese melts and salad is hot.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Layer bread cubes in 13 x 9-inch greased (Pam) pan, then sausage.
Mix egg, milk and dry mustard and pour over sausage. Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Refrigerate overnight.
Cook, covered with foil.
Start in cold oven.
Cook in 350° oven until set and light brown around edges (approximately 30 minutes). Great served with salsa.

title: grandma's chicken soup
directions: You will need a large pot.

title: zucchini and pork
directions: Heat skillet. Cook pork until well done in 1 tablespoon soy sauce and 1 teaspoon salt. Add onion and cook until done. Remove meat and onion. Cook squash in same skillet with 1/2 cup water and sugar
until soft (5 to 7 minutes).
Add pork and onion. Add 1 tablespoon soy sauce, cornstarch, 1 teaspoon salt and 1 cup water. Bring to a boil.
Serve hot.

title: sausage balls
directions: Grate cheese with large side of grater.
Mix cheese and sausage.
Add Bisquick and mix well.
Mixing with hand is best. Roll into small balls and bake on cookie sheet at 350° until slightly brown.

title: new england cheese puffs
directions: Sift all dry ingredients together in a bowl. Beat the yolks of eggs and add to the milk. Stir into the dry ingredients and mix well. Add cheese. Beat the egg whites until stiff and fold into the batter. Drop by spoonfuls into hot deep fat and cook until golden brown. Drain on brown paper before serving.

title: squash-onion casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, except cheese and bacon.
Place in a casserole dish.
Sprinkle cheese and crumble bacon on top.
Bake about 1 hour at 350°.

title: sauerkraut ball
directions: Combine all ingredients and form into a ball.
Making frosting using 8 ounces cream cheese and 2 tablespoons milk.
Spread this mixture on ball.
Garnish with olives and parsley.
Let stand in refrigerator overnight for flavors to blend.

title: lamb stew
directions: Quarter onions. Place in Dutch oven with lamb chops and saute in oil until browned. Add the can of tomatoes and water. Bring to boil. Then add string beans and simmer until lamb and beans are tender. Serve with French bread.
This is better refrigerated and served the next day.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream sugar, oleo, cream cheese, and vanilla together in large mixing bowl.
Sift flour 4 times before measuring.
Add to cream mixture alternately with eggs, beating after each egg.
Pour into greased and floured bundt pan.
Bake 300° for 1 hr 45 min.
Remove from oven and cool 20 minutes in pan before turning out.

title: coconut-pecan frosting
directions: Combine sugar, flour and salt in a heavy saucepan.
Mix well. Gradually stir in milk.
Add butter and cook over medium heat until butter melts.
Gradually add egg yolks to hot mixture, stirring constantly.
Bring to a boil and cook over medium heat 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add vanilla, coconut and pecans. Stir until frosting is cool and spreading consistency.

title: tex-mex dip
directions: Layer ingredients as listed and serve with large Fritos or Tostitos.

title: lemonade cooler
directions: In a juice extractor, put 2 apples, then add the lemon (no seeds), then remaining apples.
Mix well.
Add to crushed ice. Makes 1 serving.

title: wacky chocolate cake
directions: Grease a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan with oil.
Sift together dry ingredients in bowl.
Make 3 holes in the dry ingredients.
In one, put vanilla, one vinegar and the other one oil.
Pour water over all.
Mix well with a fork or a hand beater.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until cake tests done.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix well and serve with fresh vegetables.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in the boiling water. Add frozen strawberries and break apart with a fork.
Add bananas.
Pour half of the mixture in a bowl and let gel. Spread sour cream on top and pour remaining mixture over cream.
May use nuts (optional).

title: vegetable chili(vegetarian)
directions: Combine onions and 1/4 cup bouillon in Dutch oven. Cook over medium-high heat until onion is wilted, 5 minutes.
Stir in garlic, chili powder, cumin and oregano. Cook 1 minute more.
Add remaining bouillon and the carrots and potatoes to Dutch oven. Cover and cook 10 minutes. Add chopped tomatoes and beans. Simmer until vegetables are tender, 15 minutes more.
Remove chili from heat and stir in cilantro.
Serve with a dollop of yogurt.
Makes 10 cups.
Can be frozen up to 3 months.

title: mock girl scout thin mints
directions: Add peppermint oil to chocolate and stir until well blended. Dip crackers into mixture.

title: mexican black bean soup
directions: Soak beans overnight.
The next day, bring beans to a boil in 6 cups water.
Simmer until almost tender.
Heat butter and saute carrot, onion and garlic.
Add to beans along with jalapeno peppers.
Continue cooking until beans are done.
Puree half of bean mixture and return to pot with remainder of cooked beans. Add salt, pepper, cumin, lime juice and tomatoes.
Allow to simmer a few minutes to blend flavors.
Adjust seasonings if necessary. Serve hot.
Freezes well.

title: tang salad
directions: Add Tang to condensed milk and stir.
Add Cool Whip and sour cream.
Mix thoroughly.
Add mandarin oranges.
Stir gently.

title: plum nutty cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients; beat in oil, eggs and plums.
Fold in nuts and bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
While cake is warm, glaze with 1/2 cup powdered sugar and enough lemon juice to make glaze runny.

title: stewart's spaghetti pie
directions: Brown and drain hamburger.
Add all ingredients.
Let simmer 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage and beef. Drain well. Saute pepper, onion and celery in meat drippings. Combine uncooked rice, meat, pepper, onion, celery and soups. Pour into a large casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 1 hour, stirring once. Serves 8.

title: never fail dill pickles
directions: In top of jar put alum, dill and garlic.
Pack cucumbers into jars.
Boil water, vinegar and salt.
Pour over pickles in jars and seal.
Don't double recipe.

title: fat-free cheese cake
directions: *Or use any crust make out of crumbs (graham cracker, chocolate wafer, vanilla wafer) or the ingredients.
Spray a 9-inch spring-form pan with Pam.
Sprinkle sides with 2 tablespoons crumbs.
Mix remaining crumbs with sugar and melted butter.
Pack crumb mixture in bottom of pan.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix
ingredients
except
corn
flakes or bread crumbs. Put into a
9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Mix 1/2 of the oleo with crumbs and put on top.
Bake 60 minutes at 350°.

title: ranch chicken
directions: In a large skillet, brown seasoned chicken in butter. Sprinkle dry salad dressing mix over chicken.
Add water and 1 tablespoon of butter.
Cover and simmer until chicken is tender, approximately 30 minutes.
Remove chicken and keep warm.
Reduce sauce to desired consistency.
Pour sauce over chicken and top with almonds.
Serve over rice or noodles.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: egg burrito
directions: Scramble eggs as desired.
Then roll them up in the tortillas in burrito fashion.
Top with all or just a few of the remaining ingredients.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.
(Do not mix the pistachio pudding as directed on box.)
Pour dry pistachio pudding on crushed pineapple.
Then mix the rest of the ingredients.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in an ungreased sheet cake pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Cool and frost.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Store in refrigerator.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar. Add slightly beaten eggs. Crush wafers and add all dry ingredients to liquid. Mix well.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 250° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: apple butter
directions: Boil apples in cider.
Stir constantly.
Cook for 3 hours until thick.
Put through sieve to filter out skin and seeds. Return to pot.
Stir while cooking another hour.
When thick enough to spread, pour into sterilized jars.

title: florida pie
directions: Mix all these together.
Pour into pie shells and chill for several hours.

title: southern tea cakes
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar; add the eggs gradually. Sift and add the flour, baking powder and salt alternately with the milk. Turn onto a floured board; roll out 1/4-inch thick. Cut into rounds. Place on a greased baking sheet and bake 12 to 15 minutes at 350°.

title: vegetable bake
directions: In a large roasting pan, cut potatoes into large French fries shape.
Cover bottom of pan.
Add the rest of the vegetables. Season with salt, garlic powder and seasoning salt on top.
Cut 3 sticks of Parkay up on top.
Cover with foil.
Bake on low for 1 hour or until potatoes are done.
Remove from oven.
Cut up 1 stick Parkay on top and let melt.

title: chalupa
directions: Mix all ingredients in slow cooker, Dutch oven, etc.
Cover with water (more water can be added during cooking, if needed). Cover and cook slowly for approximately 8 hours or longer.
After 5 hours, remove roast, debone and shred meat.
Return meat to pot and continue cooking.
Serve with taco or Fritos chips, grated cheese, shredded lettuce, tomatoes, onions and taco sauce.
Also makes a great filling for burritos.

title: shipwreck
directions: Best cooked in cast-iron pot on stove burner.
First brown hamburger in pot.
Add all other ingredients. Mix well.
Add any other seasonings to taste.
Cook until meat and vegetables are done.
Marvelous one pot stew dinner.
Serve with cornbread. Wonderful on stormy cold days.

title: chicken-broccoli bake
directions: Layer broccoli in greased 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Spread chicken on top.
Mix the next 6 ingredients and pour over chicken. Sprinkle with cheese and top with stuffing mix.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: sausage ballsgroves, texas
directions: Mix sausage, grated cheese and Bisquick.

title: aunt lill's hamburger
directions: Brown hamburger in butter.
Then add onion, catsup, water, chicken soup, chili powder, soy sauce, brown sugar and mustard. Heat and stir for 15 minutes.
Spoon out on large bun.

title: lite parmesan lemon pepper chicken
directions: Season the tenderloins with lemon pepper seasoning.

Place on baking sheet and bake in 350 degree oven for 20 minutes, turning once during baking. While chicken is baking, heat the chicken gravy, Parmesan, and bouillon granules. This mixture can be thinned with a little fat free chicken broth, if desired.
When the chicken is done, place the baked tenderloins on a bed of yellow rice.
Spoon the gravy over the top.
Makes 4 servings. About 1/2 gram of fat per serving.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs to foamy. Beat in oil. Add about half of the dry ingredients and half of the zucchini. Beat until blended.
Add rest of the dry ingredients and zucchini. Add vanilla and nuts. Mix well.
Pour into 2 loaf pans. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: jelly nut cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add egg yolks.
Mix and form in 1-inch balls.
Beat egg whites until foamy.
Dip in ball and roll in nuts.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Punch hole in center (not all the way through).
Bake for 5 minutes at 350°, then re-punch hole.
Return to oven for 15 more minutes (maybe less, depending on oven).
Take out and fill hole with jelly while hot.

title: ribbon party salad
directions: First Layer:
Mix the two boxes of cherry gelatin as directed on package.
Pour in pan and allow to set until firm.

title: crock-pot pizza
directions: You will also need a 5-quart crock-pot.

title: spanish style corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl.
Pour into a large greased 10-inch
iron
skillet.
Bake
in
a
475° oven for 20 minutes.
Reduce
heat to 375°.
Bake 20 minutes more or until bread tests done.
Serve warm.

title: bumble berry pie
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients in a large bowl, stirring gently. Fit 1 pie crust in a 9 inch pie plate according to directions; spoon fruit mixture into crust.
Roll remaining crust to press out fold lines.
Cut into 1/2 inch strips and arrange in a lattice design over filling; fold edges under and crimp; place pie on baking sheet.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes; reduce heat to 350°. Bake 25 minutes more shielding edges with foil to prevent excessive browning, if necessary.

title: close to k f c original recipe
directions: Spray pan with Pam or grease pan.
Coat chicken in flour mixture.
Brush with melted butter; let dry.
Bake at 350° until done, about 45 minutes to an hour.

title: raw apple dip
directions: Mix all ingredients with a blender or mixer.
Refrigerate. Stir mixture before using.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Prepare popcorn and set aside.
Simmer first 3 ingredients for 6 minutes.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour over popcorn and separate on wax paper until cool.

title: classic chili
directions: Heat oil in large saucepan.
Add beef; brown on all sides. Add water, seasonings, Tabasco sauce, shallots, parsley, onion, Worcestershire sauce and soy sauce.
Stir to mix well.
Bring to a boil.
Cover and reduce heat.
Simmer for 1 hour and 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add beans and tomatoes; stir to mix well. Add cornmeal.
Mix well.
Simmer, uncovered, for an additional 30 minutes until meat is tender.

title: garbanzo dip(sam and colleen nunn)
directions: Drain chickpeas.
Combine all ingredients in blender until creamy.
Serve chilled, sprinkled with fresh chopped parsley. Healthful as dip for raw vegetables or as a spread with pita bread.
Contains 35 calories per serving (1 tablespoon).

title: divinity candy
directions: Cook the sugar, Karo and water slowly until starts to spin a thread.
Beat the egg whites stiff and add about 1/3 syrup to this. Beat.
Put the remaining syrup back on the stove and cook a few minutes longer.
Pour another 1/2 of this in the egg white mixture and beat.
Put the remaining syrup back on fire and cook until crack stage when dropped in cold water.
Take off stove and add remaining syrup to egg white mixture.
Beat.
Add the pecans and vanilla and beat until stiff.
Pour in buttered platter.

title: orange julius
directions: Combine orange juice, sugar, milk, water, and vanilla in blender container.
Cover and run on high until well blended.
Add ice cubes two at a time, and blend well each time.
Pour into glasses, drink, and enjoy.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix cheeses, onion and Worcestershire sauce together; chill. Form into ball and roll in chopped pecans.

title: tuna burgers
directions: Put butter in skillet.
Fry about 4 to 5 minutes on each side. Makes 4 burgers.

title: artichoke relish
directions: Wash and cut up the artichokes, onions and peppers.
Mix all the vegetables and let soak overnight in 1 gallon of water and 1 cup salt.
Next morning, pour into colander and squeeze out the water.
Mix vinegar, sugar, turmeric, pepper and mustard seed. Add this to the vegetables.
Boil for 10 minutes.
Save out 1 cup of vinegar to mix with the flour and prepared mustard and add this after the pickles have boiled the 10 minutes, then cook 5 minutes more.
Put in jars (real hot) and seal.

title: nectarine blueberry bread
directions: Stir together almonds and 1 Tbsp. sugar.
Set aside.
Beat together all remaining ingredients.
Pour into greased pans (2 medium foil pans).
Sprinkle almonds and sugar over batter.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes and remove from pan.

title: apple crisp
directions: Pare and slice apples.
Put in greased 8 x 11-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and add water.
Blend flour, butter and sugar.
Sprinkle over apples.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: chewy peanut butter strips
directions: Blend Crisco, peanut butter, sugar, salt, eggs and vanilla. Add dry ingredients (which have been sifted together) to Crisco mixture.
Stir in coconut.
Spread in 8 x 12-inch pan which has been rubbed with Crisco.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cut in strips while still warm and roll in confectioners sugar.
Yield: 30 (1 1/4 x 2 1/2-inch) strips.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to directions on package, being careful not to overcook.
Line casserole with broccoli; cover with sliced water chestnuts.
Mix soup, sour cream, onion and cheese. Place on top of this.
Make crumbs of Ritz crackers; mix with melted oleo.
Place this on top of broccoli and soup mixture topping.
Bake in a 350° oven until bubbly and hot, about 30 minutes.

title: pecan pie bars
directions: Mix flour and brown sugar; cut in butter.
Pat into ungreased 11 x 7 1/2 x 1 1/2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Beat eggs slightly; stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour over baked layer.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool until pecan layer is slightly firm before cutting into bars.
Makes 32.

title: fat free double layer pumpkin pie
directions: Mix cream cheese, milk, sugar and sugar substitute in large bowl with wire whisk until smooth.
Gently stir in whipped topping.
Spread on bottom of pie crust.
Pour 1 cup milk into bowl with Jell-O pudding and beat until well blended, 1 or 2 minutes (mixture will be thick).
Stir in pumpkin and spices; mix well.
Spread over cream cheese layer and refrigerate for at least 3 hours.

title: jamaica chicken
directions: In a saucepan, heat butter; add sugar and stir until bubbly. Add chicken and brown on both sides, adjusting heat so butter mixture does not scorch.
Add onions and cook until transparent. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer, turning chicken as necessary, until it is tender, 30 to 45 minutes.
Skim fat from sauce if you like; serve chicken with sauce as is.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: bacon-apple salad
directions: Tear lettuce into bite-sized pieces.
Crumble fried crisp bacon.
Core and chop apples.
Cut green onions into small pieces. Mix first 5 ingredients in a large bowl; mix.
Mix oil, lemon juice, salt, pepper and garlic powder (to taste).
Toss salad with oil mixture.

title: apple slice cake
directions: Beat sugar
and eggs.
Add slowly.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan ungreased at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: under-the-sea salad
directions: Mix both packages Jell-O with 2 cups very hot water. Add cream cheese and 1 cup cold water. Mix well by hand. Stir in can of pineapple. Whip the cream and fold into mixture. Refrigerate overnight.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Combine crumbs and butter in baking dish to form crust. Combine other ingredients and pour on top of crust.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: cook while you sleep cookies
directions: Beat egg whites and salt until it forms soft peaks.
Add sugar and whip until stiff.
Fold in chips and nuts.
Drop by teaspoon onto a cookie sheet that has been covered with aluminum foil.

title: no flour peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together and drop onto greased cookie sheet. Flatten with fork. Bake at 300° for 12-15 min.

title: sonny's cakes
directions: Add 1 egg to oleo and cake mix; pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Mix the cream cheese and 3 eggs; beat after each egg.
Add confectioners sugar; mix and pour over cake mix.
Bake at 350°. Cut into squares.

title: fresh raspberry pie
directions: Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and milk
to spreading consistency and spread on bottom of pie crust.

title: mixed nut bars
directions: Cover crust with layer of mixed nuts. Pour the melted chips, butter and syrup over the nuts. Bake at 350° for an additional 10 minutes. Cool and cut into bars. Do not refrigerate before cutting.

title: calico bean casserole
directions: Fry bacon; remove from skillet.
Add hamburger and onions to drippings and brown.
Break bacon into pieces; add to mixture of beans.
Add catsup, mustard, sugar and hamburger; mix well.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix eggs, flour, sugar, soda and salt together.
Add fruit cocktail (juice and all).
Stir (don't beat); mix well.
Put in ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan and bake at 325° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain peaches and pineapple real good.
Use juice from fruit. Mix vanilla pudding and Tang.
Put peaches, pineapple, grapes and bananas in bowl.
Pour over the vanilla pudding sauce and mix well.
Chill.

title: sausage and cheese nibbles
directions: Mix all together; roll into 1/2 to 3/4-inch balls.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: hamburgers ala steve
directions: Combine ingredients; form into 8 patties and grill.

title: spanish rice
directions: Brown turkey in olive oil.
Add green pepper and onion.
Cook 5 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients and cook until rice is tender.

title: spiced apple cider
directions: This is
to
be brewed in party size percolator.
Place spices in	coffee	basket.
Pour cider over this.	Perk as you would coffee.

title: butter dipping chocolate
directions: Let butter soften up and cream confectioners sugar and bourbon liquid in it.
Let stand for 24 hours in sealed container.

title: teriyaki marinade
directions: Combine ingredients.
Pour over chicken, turkey, pork or beef. Let stand for at least one hour.
If using beef, use a cheaper cut, e.g. chuck rather than sirloin.
Grill or broil the meat.

title: hot and tasty dip(microwave)
directions: Microwave (Medium) cream cheese in 1-quart casserole or serving dish 30 to 45 seconds or until soft.
Blend in remaining ingredients.
Microwave (Medium) 5 to 6 minutes or until hot, stirring after 3 minutes.
Garnish with finely chopped nuts or parsley.
Serve with vegetables (cut for dipping), crackers or chips.
Makes 2 cups.

title: applesauce bars
directions: Grease and flour jelly roll pan (10 x 15-inch).
Start oven preheating (350°).
Sift flour once; measure and sift with next 7 ingredients into mixing bowl.
Add shortening, water, nuts and raisins all at once.
Beat with spoon 2 minutes.
Add applesauce and unbeaten egg.
Beat another 2 minutes.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake about 30 minutes or until wooden pick stuck in center comes out clean.
Frost with Caramel Frosting.
Cut into bars. Makes 48 bars.

title: pickled breaded bluefish
directions: Remove dark meat; cut into 1-inch squares.
Bread with bread crumbs.
Fry in oil until golden brown.
Let cool.
Mix together all pickling ingredients.
Put bluefish nuggets into bowl.
Pour in pickling mixture.
Be sure bluefish nuggets are completely covered.
Let stand in refrigerator for about 24 hours.

title: pudding frosting
directions: Cream shortening and sugar until fluffy.
Cook pudding until thick; cool.
Add to mixture and beat, adding one spoon at a time.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Mix first three ingredients with one cup warm water.
Set aside.
Beat egg.
Add to sugar mixture.
Add yeast.
Mix.
Add flour, one cup at a time, until well mixed.
Place in refrigerator 3 to 4 hours or overnight.
Roll.
Cut.
Dip in melted margarine. Let rise 1 hour.
Bake at 450° until done.

title: honey baked apples
directions: After coring apples, enlarge hole slightly to allow for filling.
Pare a strip from top of each.
Place each in 6 ounce custard cup.
Combine banana, cranberries, honey and cinnamon. Fill centers of apples.
Pour 1 tablespoon of water over each apple.
Cook, uncovered, in countertop microwave oven for 5 to 7 minutes, or until tender, rearranging once while cooking.
Let stand until cooled slightly.
Cooking instructions are approximate, as microwave oven temperatures vary.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Spray bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan with Pam.
Sprinkle on bottom of pan, pecans and coconut.
Mix cake mix as directed on package and pour over pecans and coconut.
Mix cream cheese, oleo, vanilla and powdered sugar.
Pour or glob (mixture will be thick) on top of cake mix.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: breakfast on a bagel
directions: In broiler or toaster oven, lightly toast bagels cut side up. In medium bowl, beat together eggs, water, green onions, basil, salt and pepper; set aside.
In large nonstick skillet, melt 1 teaspoon butter over medium heat.
Add ham and cook, turning often until lightly browned, about 1 minute.
Lay on 4 bagel halves. Melt remaining 2 teaspoons butter in skillet over medium heat. Stir eggs and add to skillet.
Cook 2 to 3 minutes.
Stir occasionally until fully cooked.
Divide up to put on bagel.
Add cheese and cover with remaining bagel halves.

title: icebox fruit cake
directions: Melt sugar, juice, oleo and marshmallows.
Remove; add crumbs and nuts.
Spray aluminum foil squares with Pam or grease with oleo.
Make roll or rolls and refrigerate until firm.
Slice as needed.

title: chicken salad
directions: Bake chicken breast halves at 325° for about 45 to 55 minutes. Let cool and pull from bone.
Chop into small pieces.
Add remaining ingredients.
Makes enough for large loaf of bread.

title: shrimp genovese
directions: Mix all but noodles.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serve over noodles with a tossed salad on the side.

title: heavenly fruit salad
directions: Prepare pudding mix as directed on package.
(Do not use instant.)
Cook and cool pudding completely.
Add whipped topping and well-drained fruit to pudding and mix well.
Pour into serving bowl and refrigerate.
Marshmallows can be added, if you desire. Serves 8.

title: dieter's salad dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill overnight.
Serve with fresh vegetables.

title: veggie pizza
directions: *Blot tomatoes on paper towel before putting on pizza.
Put on directly before serving.
Recipe can be made 24 hours in advance and refrigerated except tomatoes.

title: pear honey
directions: Wash, core, pare, finely chop or grind and measure pears.
Add lemon, sugar, ginger, pineapple and 1/3 cup water to pears.
Boil until thick.
Pour boiling hot into hot jars.
Seal.

title: chocolate almond cheesecake
directions: Combine chocolate wafer crumbs, almonds, sugar and butter/margarine.
Firmly press onto bottom and sides of a 9-inch spring-form pan.
Set aside.

title: great apple dessert
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Peel and slice Granny Smith apples. Place in Pyrex dish, covering bottom.
Add water to cover apples. Sprinkle with cinnamon and 2 tablespoons of sugar.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over apples. Melt margarine and pour over cake.
Sprinkle more cinnamon on top.
Bake until golden brown, about 30 minutes.

title: creamy banana pie with coconut crust
directions: Combine coconut, sugar and flour.
Blend in margarine.
Press into 9-inch pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes until lightly brown.

title: crustless pumpkin pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray 9-inch pie pan with cooking spray.
In a large bowl, combine baking mix and dry pudding mix. Add pumpkin, milk, eggs, brown Sugar Twin and pumpkin pie spice. Using an electric mixer, blend for two minutes.
Pour into sprayed pie pan.
Bake for 50 minutes or until center is puffed up.

title: spinach and dill rice
directions: Mince spinach.
Heat olive oil.
Add spinach and garlic.
Add salt, dill, vinegar and pepper.
Cook over medium heat 10 minutes, stirring, all excess liquid should evaporate.
Bring water to boil; add rice and salt.
Cook 25 minutes.
Add spinach and rice.
Cook once more over low heat, 3 to 5 minutes.
Toss cheese together and sprinkle over rice.
Serve.

title: wendy's pizza dip
directions: Mix cream cheese, sour cream, oregano, red pepper spice and onion.
Spread in 8-inch square baking dish.
Add on top in following order:
pepperoni, green pepper, red pepper and Mozzarella.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes until cheese melts and is bubbling hot.
Spread on crackers.

title: homemade cherry cheesecake
directions: Let cream cheese soften to room temperature.
Whip until fluffy.
Add condensed milk while continuing to beat until blended.
Add lemon juice and vanilla, blend well and pour into prepared crust.
Chill overnight.
Top with cherry pie filling.

title: chicken breasts diane
directions: Place chicken breasts between sheets of waxed paper or plastic wrap.
Pound slightly with a mallet (or 2 x 4).
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients. Place in loaf pan. Top with 1/2 slice bacon and small amount of catsup. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: party casserole potatoes
directions: Beat cream cheese and sour cream until smooth.
Add to mashed potatoes gradually, beating until light and fluffy.
Add chives, parsley and garlic salt, mixing well.
Spoon into buttered baking dish.
Brush top with melted butter; sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
May top with shredded cheese, if desired. May store in refrigerator or freezer up to 10 days before baking. Yields 12 servings.

title: biscuits
directions: Heat oven to 450 degrees.
Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup; level off.
In large bowl, cut shortening into flour with fork or pastry blender until consistency of course meal.
Add milk; stir with fork until mixture leaves side of bowl and forms a soft, moist dough (1 to 3 additional tablespoons may be needed to achieve desired consistency).
Turn onto floured surface; gently knead 10 times or until no longer sticky.
Roll out 1/2 inch thick; cut with two inch floured cutter.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 450 degrees 8 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.
Yields 10 to 12 biscuits.

title: oven-baked chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.

Mix together egg whites and water in a shallow dish. Set aside. Combine cereal, garlic powder, pepper and seasoned salt. Dip chicken in egg mixture and then in cereal mixture, coating well. Arrange in baking pan coated with nonstick cooking spray.
Bake 45 minutes or
until tender.

title: dehaan's summer squash bake
directions: Cook squash and onion in water for 5 minutes; drain.
Blend sour cream and soup.
Mix with cooked squash and mushrooms. Combine Stove Top with a little water and margarine to moisten slightly.
Place half of the dressing in bottom of casserole or baking pan.
Spoon vegetable mixture evenly over the dressing. Top with remaining dressing.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes or until browned.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Combine onion soup mix with remaining ingredients.
Simmer 10 minutes or longer.
Add 2 cups catsup.
Stir.
Heat.
Makes 2 quarts.
Very good.

title: apple chip cake
directions: Mix together the first three ingredients: oleo, sugar and egg. Add the rest of ingredients.
Mix well.
Do not beat.
Bake in a 325° oven in a 9 x 9-inch square cake pan.

title: easy vegetable soup(makes 6 servings)
directions: In 3-quart saucepan, heat oil.
Add onion and garlic and saute for 3 to 5 minutes, until onion is tender.
Add water, tomatoes, cabbage, celery, carrots, instant bouillon, sugar, thyme, pepper and bay leaf.
Bring to a boil; cover and simmer 30 minutes or until vegetables are crisp, but tender.
Add macaroni and simmer 10 minutes or until macaroni is tender.
Remove bay leaf.

title: french fry hot dish
directions: Put French fries in bottom of 9 x 12-inch pan.
Cook hamburger with onions, salt and pepper.
Add corn, mushroom soup, chicken soup and milk.
Pour over French fries.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: potato cheese soup
directions: Cook potatoes and onion in salted water until tender. Mash down; add margarine, parsley, milk, cheese and ham. Heat and stir until cheese melts.

title: fruited coffee cake
directions: Mix together and spread evenly over top of dough.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Then cover with foil and bake another 10 minutes.

title: zesty buttered peas
directions: In heavy 2-quart saucepan, melt butter over medium heat.
Add remaining ingredients except pimiento.
Cover; cook over medium heat for 6 to 8 minutes, or until vegetables are tender.
Stir in pimiento.
Serve immediately.
Yields 4 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: stuffed french toast
directions: Place 1/2 of cubed bread in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with cream cheese cubes.
Add rest of bread cubes on top of cream cheese. Beat eggs and add milk. Mix well.
Add maple syrup.
Pour egg mixture over bread and cheese.
Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve with maple syrup.

title: bean salad
directions: Drain and rinse beans and drain again.
Mix together onions, celery, bell pepper and pimentos.
Add to beans.
Combine vinegar and sugar and bring to a boil.
Pour over bean mixture.
Chill overnight and serve.

title: chicken dinner
directions: Saute onion and bell pepper in stick of butter until tender. Put chicken, potatoes, can of Ro-Tel, sauteed onion and bell peppers in a Pyrex dish and cook in oven at 350° until chicken and potatoes are done, then add English peas.
Put back in oven until peas are hot.
Good served over rice.

title: easy lemon pie
directions: Dissolve gelatin completely in boiling water, stirring 3 minutes.
Add lemon juice, rind and ice cubes and stir constantly until thickened, about 2 to 3 minutes.
Remove any unmelted ice. With whisk, blend in Cool Whip; whip until smooth.
Chill if necessary until mixture mounds.
Spoon into pie crust.
Chill 2 hours or until firm.
Garnish as desired.

title: squash dressing
directions: Mix all the ingredients together and pour into a greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: teriyaki steak kabobs
directions: Mix steak sauce, brown sugar, soy sauce, garlic and ginger in bowl. Thinly slice steak; place in Ziploc bag. (Save 1/4 cup of mixture to baste while cooking.) Marinate overnight. Remove meat from marinade; discard bag with marinade. Alternately thread steak, peppers, pineapple and shrimp (optional) onto skewers. Grill or broil kabobs for 4 to 6 minutes, until desired doneness, turning once and brushing with saved mixture. Makes 4 servings.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Sift flour, salt and baking powder together.
Set aside. Blend eggs and vanilla together, then add sifted dry ingredients and milk.
Roll out dough and cut.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake on baking sheet at 375° for 12 minutes.

title: five cup salad
directions: Chill 6 to 12 hours.

title: black-walnut cake
directions: Mix sugar, oil and eggs.
Add flour; mix well.
Add remaining ingredients (mix).
Bake in tube pan for 1 hour and 10 minutes at 350°.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until tender; drain.
Combine soup, mayonnaise, cheese, egg and milk.
Stir into broccoli.
Place in 2-quart casserole dish.
Combine cracker crumbs and melted butter. Sprinkle over broccoli mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: impossible lasagna pie(serves 6 to 8)
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Lightly grease pie plate (10 x 1 1/2-inch).
Layer cottage cheese and Parmesan cheese in plate. Mix cooked beef, oregano, basil, tomato paste and 1/2 cup of the Mozzarella cheese; spoon evenly over top.
Beat milk, baking mix, eggs, salt and pepper until smooth.
Pour over meat mixture.
Bake until golden brown and knife inserted halfway between center and edge comes out clean, 30 to 35 minutes.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Let stand five minutes before cutting.

title: mashed sweet potatoes and pineapple
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mash sweet potatoes into pineapple and pecans.
Pour into greased 1-quart casserole dish.
Bake 20 minutes.
Top with cut marshmallows.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes longer.

title: apple or peach pie in a jar
directions: In a large saucepan, blend the first 5 ingredients well.
Stir in 10 cups of water; cook on medium-high and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Cook an additional 2 minutes.
Add lemon juice and, if desired, food coloring, but I don't.
Add apples or peaches to sauce.
Stir constantly; bring to a rolling boil.
Cook for 1 minute at a rolling boil.
Keep saucepan on burner and ladle mixture into sterile, hot jars; leave 1/2-inch headspace.
Process in boiling water bath 25 minutes for pints or quarts.

title: lemon-broiled chicken and skewered vegetables
directions: Preheat broiler.
In small saucepan melt butter. Add garlic, lemon juice and parsley.
Place chicken, skin side down, on rack in broiler pan.

title: holiday mashed potatoes
directions: Butter a 9 x 13-inch baking dish, set aside.
Combine potatoes, 1 teaspoon salt and water to cover in large Dutch oven. Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer until tender, about 17 minutes.
Drain.
Return potatoes to pot with broth, butter, sour cream, poultry seasoning and two teaspoons of salt.
Beat with hand held mixer or potato masher until smooth.
Spread potatoes in baking dish and sprinkle with paprika.
Cover and refrigerate up to two hours.
Bake in preheated 350° oven until puffed and heated through.
Makes 16 cups.
A 3/4 cup serving is 165 calories.

title: barbecued pork in the slow cooker
directions: Place meat in slow cooker.
Add onions, barbecue sauce and honey.
Cover.
Cook on low 6 to 8 hours.
Use 2 forks to shred meat.
Serve on kaiser rolls with sauce.
Add some cole slaw and enjoy!
Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: french potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes whole.
Drain.
Peel while still warm.
Slice. Combine all other ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour over warm potatoes. Toss until liquid is absorbed. Allow to marinate at room temperature.
If refrigerated after mixing, bring to room temperature before serving.

title: eggplant parmesan
directions: Grate cheese.
Prepare three bowls for dipping eggplant.
In first bowl, put whole wheat flour and salt.
In second bowl, put beaten eggs and milk.
In the third bowl, put the crackers, salt, pepper and oregano.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Cut eggplant into 1/4-inch slices.
Dip slices in each bowl to coat completely. Layer coated eggplant in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Slices may overlap.
Sprinkle each layer with tomato sauce and Parmesan cheese.
Cover tightly and bake for 30 to 45 minutes or until tender.
Top with Mozzarella and any remaining Parmesan cheese. Return, uncovered, to oven until cheeses melt.

title: asparagus luncheon dish
directions: Cook asparagus in boiling water until well done.
Drain. Combine soup and cream and heat.
Arrange hot asparagus on the toast and pour sauce over.
Garnish with sieved hard-cooked eggs or sprinkle with paprika.

title: rhubarb custard pie
directions: Wash rhubarb and place in pie shell.
Combine sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Add egg and beat well; add syrup and melted butter.
Pour over rhubarb.
Arrange lattice of pastry strips across top.
Bake in hot oven at 450° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake 30 minutes longer or until rhubarb is tender.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Place in loaf pans.
Bake at 350° until toothpick comes out clean.
Prick top with fork several times and glaze while hot.

title: buttermilk chess pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Mix flour and sugar; add to eggs.
Add liquids and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: onion rings
directions: Mix ingredients together to make batter.
Cut onion into rings.
Coat with flour and dip in batter.
Deep fat fry them.

title: hot spinach balls
directions: Combine bread cubes, onion, cheese and seasonings.
Beat eggs well. Add cooked spinach and bread to egg mixture and mix well. Pour melted butter over mixture and mix well.
Chill thoroughly. Roll into 1-inch balls.
Place on a 14 x 9-inch baking pan and bake at 300° approximately 15 minutes.

title: microwave caramel corn
directions: Put sugar, syrup, butter and salt in a 2-quart bowl and microwave on High.
Boil for 2 minutes.
Immediately add soda and pour over 3 to 4 quarts popped corn in a grocery sack.
Shake and microwave 1 1/2 minutes on High.
Shake and microwave 1 1/2 minutes longer.
Shake and serve.

title: raspberry custard pie
directions: Arrange raspberries in pie shell.
Mix eggs, sugar, flour and milk in a bowl.
Pour over raspberries.
Bake at 300° until knife comes out clean, about 1 hour.

title: warm cup of coffee
directions: Warm up milk.
Add instant coffee.
Add sugar to taste and drink.

title: special fried rice
directions: Cut onion, mushrooms and carrots into thin slices.
Beat eggs with salt.
Set wok at 420° (or hot pan).
Heat oil; add onions and carrots and stir-fry for 1 minute.
Add mushrooms and shrimp and fry for another minute.
Push to one side and pour eggs in the other side.
Cook for 2 minutes.
When eggs are nearly set, add rice, peas and soy sauce.
Mix all ingredients together and cook for a minute more.

title: no-bake fudgies
directions: Combine first five ingredients and boil one minute.
Stir in peanut butter, nuts, oatmeal and vanilla.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on waxed paper or greased cookie sheet.
Let stand one to two hours at room temperature.
Walnuts and raisins are also good in these.

title: vernie's hermies(vern's hermits)
directions: Mix well.
Spread in strips on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes or until golden brown.
Cut to cookie size.

title: latin beans and rice
directions: In a heavy skillet or saucepan, fry the bacon until soft and crisp.
Add onion and green pepper; saute, stirring, until limp. Add garlic.
Stir in tomato paste.
Add kidney beans, oregano, salt, pepper and water.
Heat mixture to boiling; reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, stirring now and then, until gravy thickens slightly.
Serve over white or brown rice.
Makes 4 servings.

title: apricot salad
directions: Dissolve jello in one cup boiling water.
Cool.
Add mandarin oranges and pineapple.
Place in refrigeartor to thicken slightly. Fold in Dream Whip.
Chill.

title: sesame salmon
directions: 1. Thinly slice shallots & separate into rings. Wash & dry spinach well removing tough stims. Preheat oven to
2. Arrange 1/4 of spinach leaves on half of each parchment square. Lightly brush both sides of fillets with corn
oil. Season with lemon - pepper seasoning.
3. Arrange fillets, skin side up over spinach leaves.
Sprinkle with shallots drizzle with lemon juice. Fold
other half of parchment paper over spinach & fillet.
4. To seal packets, beginning at one corner, fold edges of
paper over about 1/2 inch all around, overlapping the
folds.
5. Place packets on cookie sheet. Bake 15 minutes (paper
will puff up & brown). When packets are open, check
that fish flakes easily with a fork.

title: dutch apple cake
directions: Cut shortening into first four ingredients.
Stir in egg and milk.

title: southern corn pudding
directions: Mix flour, sugar and salt; add beaten eggs.
Mix well; add milk and corn.
Mix thoroughly and pour into well buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Dot with butter.
Cook in 350° oven until firm, about 45 minutes.

title: daddy's spaghetti
directions: Brown turkey if meat is desired, finely chopping as it cooks. Pour off any fat.
Add chopped onion and stir.
Wait 3 minutes. Add peppers.
Cook the onion and peppers, stirring all along.
Add all remaining ingredients, saving sliced or chopped mushrooms for last.

title: italian cream cake variation
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Beat together margarine and vegetable shortening.
Add fructose and Sweet 'N Low and beat until smooth.
Add egg yolks and beat well.
Combine the flour and the creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk.
Stir in the vanilla, then add the beaten egg whites.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan and bake at 350° for the first 10 minutes, then reduce heat to 325° if baking in a gas oven.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until done when tested with straw or toothpick.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Mix soup and 1/2 cup milk and heat on low.
Combine evaporated milk, mayonnaise and Worcestershire sauce in a bowl and stir in soup mixture.

title: applesauce rice pudding
directions: Stir applesauce and pudding in a large saucepan.
Stir in milk, rice, egg and cinnamon.
Cook and stir on medium heat until mixture comes to a boil; remove from heat.
Cool 5 minutes, stirring twice.
Serve warm or cold.
Makes 8 servings.

title: dishpan cookies
directions: Cream oil, sugars and eggs.
Mix flour, soda and salt.
Add oats, coconut, cornflakes and chocolate chips.
Form into small ball.
Place on cookie sheet, ungreased.
Bake at 325° for 8 to 10 minutes; 10 to 12 minutes for crisp.

title: heavenly pie
directions: Combine bananas, sugar and salt.
Beat egg whites vigorously into banana mixture.
Add almond flavoring and mix well.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Then bake at 300° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Chill.
Top with whipped cream and nuts, if desired.
Makes 1 (8-inch) pie.

title: tuna fish dip
directions: Saute the first 4 ingredients in a pot over low fire; add tuna fish and cream of mushroom soup.
Serve with chips or crackers.

title: glenda's favorite fruit cake
directions: Line a large tube pan and 2 small loaf pans with greased foil. Cut up fruits, add nuts and mix with the 1 cup flour and have ready to add to the cake batter. Sift flour, spices and cocoa together and set aside. Cream butter with sugar and beat until light and fluffy. Add to the mixture the well beaten eggs, then the jam and beat well. Add flour mixture alternately with buttermilk in which soda has been dissolved, beating constantly. Fold in fruit/nut mixture. Add the wine. Spoon batter into pans and bake at 300 degree for 1/2 hour then at 250 degrees for 2 hours. (Put small pan of water in oven.) Let cake cool in pan. After cake is cold, pour small amount of wine over cakes, wrap them in cheesecloth, then store until ready to cut. Keep them moistened with a little wine to keep cakes from drying out.

title: taco pie
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Add taco seasoning and put into pie crust.
Spread refried beans over beef.
Add cheese to cover. Pour Pace sauce over pie.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: sandra's sweet and sour green beans
directions: In casserole, layer green beans, onion and bacon.
Repeat layers.
Add sugar and vinegar to bacon drippings until dissolved. Pour over layered green beans and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Great to do ahead.

title: cabbage soup
directions: Brown together hamburger, onion and garlic.
Add cabbage, tomatoes, tomato paste, water, kidney beans and spices.
Simmer for 1 hour.

title: shrimp stir-fry
directions: Toss shrimp in salt and pepper to coat.
Heat oil in skillet, add shrimp and stir over high heat for 2 to 3 minutes.
Remove shrimp from skillet.
Add garlic and onion to skillet and stir over medium heat for 1 minute.
add pea pods, vegetables and chicken broth to pan and stir over medium heat 3 to 4 minutes or until vegetables are crisp tender.
Return shrimp to pan and cook 1 to 2 minutes, stirring.
Serve over rice.

title: easy pan smores
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Line 13 x 9-inch pan with 1/2 graham cracker squares (15).
Sprinkle chocolate chips over graham crackers.
Bake at 350° for 5 minutes or until chocolate starts to melt.
Remove from oven; spread melted chips evenly over graham crackers.
Set aside.

title: barbecued pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops in heavy skillet in hot oil.
Mix other ingredients and cover pork chops.
Cover and let simmer for one hour or can be baked, covered, in 350° oven for approximately 1 hour.

title: punch
directions: Mix in bowl and add ice.

title: chicken cordon bleu
directions: Press chicken fillet flat.
Place one slice of ham and one slice of American cheese in each breast.
Fold breast over and place in large baking dish.
Dilute chicken soup with water (or wine) and pour over chicken breasts.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 8.

title: confetti stuffed peppers
directions: Cut peppers into quarters; core and seed.
Place on microwave-safe dish.
Cover with microwave-safe plastic wrap. Microwave at full power 3 minutes, rotating dish one quarter turn after 2 minutes.
Cool slightly.
Combine onion and mushrooms in 9-inch microwave-safe dish.
Cover with microwave-safe plastic wrap.
Microwave at full power 2 minutes.
Spoon onion-mushroom mixture onto pepper quarters.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Microwave, uncovered, at full power 2 to 3 minutes, until cheese melts. Garnish with crumbled bacon, green onion and pimiento.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients together, making a "well" in the center. Add combined ingredients, pumpkin, eggs, water and oil.
Mix only until dry ingredients are moistened.
Fold in black walnuts.
Pour into 2 greased and floured 9 x 5-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes, or until done.

title: cornbread and andouille stuffing
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Crumble cornbread into large bowl and set aside.
In saute pan cook andouille until fat is rendered. Drain and add to cornbread.
Saute onions, celery and 1/2 of green onions in butter.
Add crawfish, garlic and herbs.
Stir and cook for 3 minutes and add to cornbread mixture.
Bring chicken broth to boil and add slowly to cornbread mixture until desired consistency.
Season to taste with salt, pepper and Tabasco.
Stir in remaining green onions and parsley.
Pour into casserole and bake for 30 minutes or until heated throughout.

title: double chocolate muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Grease muffin pan.
Cream oleo and sugar.
Add eggs.
Combine flour, cocoa, baking powder and salt. Add to mix alternately with yogurt.
Do not overmix.
Gently fold in chocolate morsels.
Bake 15 to 18 minutes.
Cool.

title: enchiladas
directions: Mix juice, soup, tomato paste, chilies and hot sauce in skillet.
Brown ground beef and onion together.
Dip tortilla patty in sauce and place spoonful of hamburger and some cheese in center.
Roll and place in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Pour remaining sauce over rolled tortillas and top with remaining cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: favorite casserole
directions: Cook macaroni and cheese according to package directions. While macaroni is cooking, place onions, garlic powder and chopped tomatoes in lightly oiled pan.
Cook on medium heat for 5 minutes. Break Steak-umm steaks into 8 to 10 pieces each and add to tomato mixture.
Cook and stir until Steak-umm pieces are just brown. Do not overcook.
Stir Bleu cheese dressing into Steak-umm/tomato mixture.
Take Steak-umm/tomato mixture out of pan with slotted spoon to drain excess tomato juice.
Mix with macaroni and cheese. Salt to taste.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: brownies
directions: Bake at 350° for approximately 20 minutes in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Ice if desired.

title: french coconut pie
directions: Melt oleo and add rest of ingredients, except coconut.
Mix well.
Then add coconut.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: pretzel jello salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water, cool and add strawberries. Chill until partially thickened.
Mix first 3 ingredients.
Save 1/4 cup for topping.
Press rest in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool.
Mix cream cheese, Cool Whip and 1 cup sugar; spread on base in the pan.
Pour the strawberry-Jell-O mixture over the cream cheese mixture.
Sprinkle with the 1/4 cup topping.
Chill for several hours.
Serves 12.

title: butterscotch buns
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Place 2 teaspoons brown sugar, 2 teaspoons butter and 3 pecan halves in each of 12 medium muffin cups.
Place in oven to melt sugar and butter.
Stir baking mix and banana to a soft dough.
Gently smooth dough into a ball on floured cloth-covered board.
Knead 5 times.
Roll dough into rectangle, 15 x 9-inches.
Spread rectangle with 2 tablespoons butter; sprinkle with 1/4 cup brown sugar.
Roll up tightly beginning at wide side. Seal well by pinching edge of dough into roll.
Cut into twelve 1 1/4-inch slices.
Place slices cut sides down in muffin cups.
Bake 10 minutes.
Immediately invert pan onto baking sheet.
Leave the pan over rolls a minute.
Serve warm.
Yields 1 dozen.

title: cheese filling for sandwiches
directions: Melt margarine and Velveeta cheese over low heat.
Cool. Grind together ham, onion and green pepper.
Add catsup and horseradish.
Fill hot dog or hamburger buns and wrap in waxed paper.
Heat at 250° for 30 minutes.
Makes 8.

title: summertime punch
directions: Try rubbing tough meat with a cut lemon to make it tender.

title: creamy pineapple salad
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving the juice in a small saucepan.
Set pineapple aside.
Add enough water to juice to make 1 1/3 cups. Bring to a boil.
Place gelatin in a bowl; add boiling liquid and stir to dissolve.
Cool until slightly thickened.

title: rhubarb torte
directions: Mix flour, 2 tablespoons sugar, butter or oleo and salt.
Pat in 9 x 9-inch pan and bake 20 minutes at 325°.
While baking, put 1 1/4 cups sugar, milk, 3 tablespoons flour and egg yolks in saucepan.
Mix well, then add rhubarb.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly.
When mixture is thick and rhubarb soft, pour over crust.
Top with meringue of 3 egg whites and 1/4 cup sugar. Bake until brown.
(May use frozen rhubarb.)

title: mushroom and onion quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Saute onion and mushrooms in margarine. Add lemon juice and wine.
In a separate bowl, combine cheese, flour, dry milk, salt and pepper.
Cool milk; add to cheese mixture and add eggs.
Stir in onion mixture.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake 40 minutes.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Combine filling ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into pie shells, dividing equally.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 to 50 minutes, or until done.

title: pound cake
directions: Beat butter with mixer until creamy.
Gradually beat in sifted sugar, beating well after each addition, until light and fluffy. Beat in eggs one at a time.
Beat in vanilla.
Gradually stir in cake flour; blending well.
Do not overmix.
Pour into well buttered and lightly floured tube or Bundt pan.
Bake in preheated 300° oven 1 1/2 hours or until pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan 5 minutes then remove.

title: chocolate drops
directions: Melt chips and butter. Stir in potato sticks and peanuts. Drop by teaspoons on waxed paper. Chill until set. Store in airtight containers.

title: chicken and broccoli quiche
directions: Arrange chicken and broccoli in pie shell.
Toss cheese with flour, pepper (and salt, if desired).
Sprinkle over chicken and broccoli.
Combine eggs and milk.
Pour over filling. Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Let stand for 5 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.
Great with a tossed salad and white wine.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add beaten eggs, flour, salt and flavoring.
Add syrup and pecans.
Stir well and pour in an unbaked crust.
Bake slowly at 300° for 45 minutes to 1 hour. Makes 2 small pies or 1 large.
Baking time is less if baking 2 small pies.
Be careful not to overbake or pie will be dry.
Cook just long enough that filling sets.

title: chicken delicious
directions: Arrange potato quarters in large, shallow 3-quart casserole. Mix seasonings and sprinkle half of it over the potatoes.
Arrange chicken and sausage over the potatoes.
(You can either cut up sausage or remove from casing and lay little sausage balls on top of the chicken.)
Pour oil over and sprinkle on remaining seasonings.
Cover and bake at 425° for 45 minutes.
Reduce heat to 375° and bake for 30 minutes more or until nicely browned.

title: diana's mexican casserole
directions: Line the bottom of a greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish with 6 tortillas. Brown ground beef with onion, chili powder, salt and pepper to taste. Drain and spread meat mixture over tortillas. Layer beans, undrained. Layer sliced cheese over beans. Cover with remaining tortillas. Combine soup and Ro-Tel tomatoes; pour over casserole. Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: benedictine
directions: Bring cream cheese to room temperature. Peel cucumber, slice in half lengthwise and seed. Shred the cucumber and squeeze dry.

title: marinated broccoli with curry dip
directions: Wash broccoli; remove most of stem and cut into pieces.
Mix together vinegar, oil, dill, sugar, salt and pepper.
Pour over broccoli and toss to coat.
Marinate at least 6 hours, stirring once or twice.
Drain and arrange on serving tray.

title: orange tang pie
directions: Do not use mixer.
Place in 2 graham cracker crusts.
Put in refrigerator to cool.

title: chilled chicken pasta salad
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients (pasta mixture).
Combine last 5 ingredients (dressing).
Combine pasta mixture with dressing. Cover and chill.
Toss well before serving.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.
May also add carrots, cauliflower, etc.

title: meatballs with rice
directions: Mix hamburger, onion, rice, salt and pepper in large bowl. After mixing, ball up into balls and put in casserole bowl.
Pour tomato soup and 1 can of water over meatballs.
Bake in oven at 325° for 1 hour.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Cook vegetables according to directions.
Drain and mix all other ingredients, except cracker crumbs and butter.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch glass dish.
Mix crumbs and butter together; put on top of vegetable mixture.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: tuna and chips casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350° (moderate).
Empty soup into 2-quart baking dish.
Add milk and mix well.
Add tuna, 2 cups potato chips and peas; mix lightly.
Sprinkle remaining potato chips over top. Bake 25 minutes until heated through.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: mom's chocolate gravy
directions: Mix cocoa, sugar and flour in large skillet with just enough water to make a paste.
Add milk and heat over medium heat. Mixture should be thick when cooked.
Add more milk if too thick. Add butter and remove from heat.
Serve over hot biscuits for a real treat.

title: cabbage a la milan
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place beef, onions and celery in a pan and fry until beef is browned and vegetables are crisp-tender. Spoon into a large ovenproof dish and arrange cabbage on top of meat mixture.
Combine tomato sauce, garlic salt, basil, oregano and pepper.
Mix to blend.
Pour over cabbage.
Cover and bake 45 minutes or until cabbage is tender.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Return to oven for 5 minutes.
Serve over rice.
Makes 6 servings.

title: sweet fresh lima beans
directions: Saute onions in oil until golden brown, stirring frequently. Add 1/2 cup water and cook for 10 minutes; repeat 1 more time, then add lima beans and smother for 15 minutes. Add hot water, salt and sugar. Cook, partially covered, for about 40 minutes or until gravy is kind of thick.

title: easy s'mores
directions: Spread graham cracker half with peanut butter.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips and mini marshmallows.
Microwave on High for 30 seconds or put under broiler until marshmallows are lightly browned.
Eat either as is or make a sandwich with another graham cracker half.

title: fudge truffle cheesecake
directions: Heat oven to 300°.
Prepare crust.
In mixer bowl beat cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat in milk until smooth, then remaining ingredients.
Pour into pan over crust.
Bake 1 hour and 5 minutes or until center is set.
Cool and chill.

title: mashed potato rutabaga combination
directions: Peel, slice and cook the potatoes and rutabaga separately in salted water until tender.
Drain. Combine.
Add remaining ingredients and whip until light and fluffy.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: curry hamburger
directions: Fry hamburger and onion (like spaghetti sauce) in large frypan. Drain. Cut potatoes in small bite size pieces; add to hamburger. Add remaining ingredients except rice. Stir and simmer until potatoes are done. Place rice on plate; pour Curry Hamburger on top. Enjoy.

title: eggplant caviar
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Place eggplant on sheet of aluminum foil and bake 1 hour.
Let cool.
Remove pulp.
Should be 3 to 4 cups.

title: thick, creamy potato soup
directions: In large stock pan, add bouillon granules and water.
Bring to a slow boil.
Add celery, onion and potatoes.
Let cook until vegetables are tender (approximately 20 minutes).
Add 1 cup of milk.
In a separate bowl, mix together flour and 1/4 cup milk; should be smooth.
Slowly mix flour mixture into soup, continually stirring.
Add bacon to soup.

title: hobo dinner
directions: Layer onions in bottom of large pan. Wash well and layer carrots, then potatoes. Cut up cabbage and layer next. Cut sausage into chunks on top of cabbage.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix sugar and margarine together.
Add peanut butter and vanilla, mixing well.
Roll into little balls the size of a small walnut.
Melt chocolate chips in double boiler.
Cut the wax into tiny pieces and add to chocolate.
Dip balls of candy into the chocolate with toothpick.
Then put on wax paper until set.
There should be over 100 pieces of candy.

title: oven french fries
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Cut potatoes into long wedges, about 8 per potato (with or without skin).
Place on cookie sheet.
In small pan melt butter and brush a little on cookie sheet to keep from sticking.
Brush rest of butter on potato wedges.
Bake until golden brown, approximately 45 minutes.
After about 20 minutes turn once with spatula so they don't stick.

title: souper french dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients, except oil and vinegar.
While beating with electric mixer, add oil and vinegar alternately. Makes 2 1/2 quarts.
Refrigerate.

title: chicken with rice
directions: Mix soups with the water. Stir in rice and pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan (sprayed with Pam).
Place chicken pieces on top and sprinkle with the dry onion soup mix.
Cover with aluminum foil and bake 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: microwave sunday chicken bake
directions: Arrange chicken in 8 x 8-inch dish.
Combine rest of ingredients and pour over chicken.
Cover with vented plastic wrap.
Microwave at 50% (medium power) for 15 minutes.
Turn chicken over, recover and microwave for 10 to 20 minutes until tender.
Arrange chicken over rice on serving platter.
Spoon some sauce over chicken and garnish with paprika and chopped olives. Serve rest of sauce in gravy boat.

title: ranch salad dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients together in a small bowl. Refrigerate.
Use on salads.
Makes 2 cups.

title: gorditas
directions: Brown meat and keep covered.
Boil tomatoes and peppers.
When tender mix tomatoes, peppers, onion and garlic in blender.
Add to meat mixture, then if needed add 1 teaspoon corn masa mix to thicken sauce.
Once ready, put aside.

title: potato wedges
directions: Cut potatoes into wedges and arrange, peel side down, in baking dish.
Mix ingredients and brush over potatoes.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until tender.
Brush occasionally with oil mixture.

title: broccoli and cheese casserole
directions: Over low heat or in microwave, melt together soup and Cheez Whiz.
Cook the rice according to package directions.
Cook broccoli until slightly tender.
Mix all ingredients in casserole dish and bake at 350° until hot through.
About 5 to 10 minutes before removing from oven, sprinkle grated cheese over the top and remove from the oven when cheese is melted.

title: tuna tofu patties
directions: Squeeze water from tofu well and crumble.
Add the remaining ingredients and mix well.
Drop by spoonfuls into greased frying pan.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt oleo in a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Blend flour, sugar and baking powder and stir in the milk.
Pour over the melted oleo. Drain one of the cans of peaches; reserve the juice.
Add both cans of peaches over the batter.
Sprinkle the vanilla and sugar over top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: mom's golden casserole
directions: Cook rice. Add carrots, cheese and remaining ingredients (saving 1/2 cup cheese).
Place in casserole dish. Sprinkle extra cheese on top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken dorito
directions: Boil chicken until tender.
Cool, skin and debone.
Melt butter and saute onion.
Add Velveeta and soups.
Layer chicken, heated sauce and Doritos.
Repeat; bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Makes 4 adult size servings.

title: coke salad
directions: Bring water and juice off cherries to a boil; remove from heat. Add jello, Equal, pineapple with juice and cherries.
Let stand 5 minutes. Add diet Coke and nuts. Stir and chill.

title: yummy rhubarb dessert
directions: Cook until sauce.
Puree in blender, pour in bowl; cool.
After cooled, add 1 cup heavy whip cream.

title: broccoli-corn bake
directions: Cook and drain broccoli; mix with corn and add flour and salt to eggs.
Mix with broccoli and corn and put into baking dish. Dot with butter and sprinkle with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: madine hill's refrigerator rolls
directions: Dissolve
yeast
in
warm water for immediate use or in 1/4 cup of warm water if you plan to store in refrigerator for later use,
and
use 1 1/4 cups cold water for the remainder. Sift flour, salt and sugar.
Cut in shortening.	Add yeast and water. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Continue to stir until dough
is elastic.
Place dough in greased bowl, cover and let rise 30 minutes for immediate use or place in refrigerator for later
use. Roll
dough (don't knead), cut into rolls and let rise at room temperature.
Bake at 450° until light brown.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Mix ground beef, cooked rice, chopped onion, salt, pepper and egg together.
Trim off thickest part of stem from cabbage leaves. Divide meat into equal portions wrapped in a leaf, fasten with wooden picks.
Brown cabbage rolls slightly in oil.
Add tomato sauce and water.
Cover and simmer slowly for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: quiche-a-roni
directions: Prepare Rice-A-Roni according to package directions using 2 1/2 cups water.
Cool.
Spoon Rice-A-Roni into 10-inch pie pan and mold to form a shell.
Combine cheese, half and half, eggs, onions, salt and pepper.
Pour into shell.
Top with bacon chips. Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes or until set.
Cool 5 minutes and cut into wedges.
Yields 6 servings.

title: super nachos
directions: Brown beef and onion. Drain well. Season with salt and pepper, seasoning to taste.
Spread beans in shallow 10 x 15-inch baking pan. Top evenly with meat mixture. Sprinkle chilies over meat mixture. Cover with cheese and drizzle with taco sauce. Cover and chill, if made ahead.
Bake, uncovered, in a 400° oven for 20 to 25 minutes. Remove from oven and top with green onions, sour cream and olives.
Mound avocado in center. Garnish with parsley sprigs. Serve with corn chips.

title: cuppies
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Chill for 15 minutes.
Form into 1-inch balls and press into small cupcake pans.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes (until light brown).
Any kind of pudding mix may be put into baked cups.
A dab of Cool Whip may be put on top.

title: alabama corn bread
directions: Mix and pour into hot iron skillet.
(I use two skillets.) Bake at 450° until browned.

title: skillet supper
directions: Brown meat, onions and rice in oil; then drain.
Add water, sauce and seasonings.
Cover and simmer for 20 minutes.
Top with grated cheese and broil, if desired.

title: scripture cake
directions: Blend together butter, sugar, spices and salt.
Beat egg yolks and add to butter and sugar mix.
Sift in baking powder and flour, then add water and honey.
Put nuts and fruit through food chopper.
Add more flour, if needed.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Bake for 1 hour in 375° oven.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour in 9-inch pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 5 minutes.
Lower to 325° and bake until done, about 25 minutes.

title: no bake chocolate peanut butter bars(kids love them!)
directions: In large saucepan, combine sugar, corn syrup and peanut butter.
Cook over medium - low heat until the sugar is dissolved. remove from the heat; add cereal and stir until coated.
Spread into a greased 13 x 9 x 2 inch pan.
Press lightly.
Spread melted chocolate over bars.
Chill.

title: carameled cereal
directions: In top of double boiler over hot water, heat 28 vanilla caramels in 2 tablespoons water, stirring frequently, until caramels are melted and mixture is smooth.
Pour caramel mixture over 5 cups Kix cereal; mix gently.
Drop mixture by spoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Let stand until firm.
Makes about 3 dozen candies.

title: easy apple bars
directions: Add sugar to apples and set aside.
Sift flour, soda, nutmeg, cinnamon and salt together.
Mix and add to apples.
Mix eggs, vanilla and salad oil.
Add to mixture and spread into a large greased cookie sheet.
Sprinkle over top 1/2 cup brown sugar with 1/2 cup chopped walnuts and a little cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: Combine all ingredients and blend well. After icing is on cake, keep cake in the refrigerator.

title: french coconut pie
directions: Combine eggs and sugar.
Mix well.
Add remaining ingredients. Mix and pour into an unbaked 9-inch pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 300° and bake until brown, or when you shake the pie, it is firm.
Yield:
8 slices.

title: butterscotch icing
directions: Melt butter.
Add sugar and milk.
Bring to a boil.
Add powdered sugar slowly, stirring constantly.
Pour on cake while still warm.
Cut into bars and serve with whipped cream.

title: summer salad
directions: Sprinkle jello onto cottage cheese. Add drained fruit and mix. Fold in Cool Whip and marshmallows. Refrigerate several hours.

title: brisket in foil
directions: Trim excess fat from brisket.
Place meat on large sheet of heavy foil in shallow roasting pan.
Sprinkle with onion soup mix and pepper.
Pour wine around meat.
Peel carrots and potatoes; cut into halves or serving size pieces and arrange around meat. Wrap foil to form an airtight package, but allowing space for gravy to form.
Bake in preheated 325° oven for 3 to 4 hours. Slice meat across grain.
Serve with pan juices and vegetables.

title: french orange cake
directions: Mix soda and water.
Pour over dates.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Add egg and beat well.
Add date mixture.
Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Beat well.
Add grated orange rind and pecans.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: broccoli cheese squares
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Steam broccoli 3 minutes.
Cool and press dry.
Beat eggs and milk until frothy.
Mix flour and baking powder and stir into eggs, milk and margarine.
Mix well.
Fold in cheese, broccoli and chopped onion.
Spoon into baking dish evenly.
Sprinkle with seasoned salt.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until sets and is lightly brown.
Let stand 5 minutes and then cut into squares.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Use blender or food processor to chop olives and onions by adding a bit of the olive juice to the container you are using. Add olives and turn blender/processor on-off about twice.
Drain well, saving the juice to do the same with the onions.
Drain the onions.
Mix onions and olives with mayonnaise and crumbled Bleu cheese.

title: fruit-flavored popcorn
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Melt butter with the syrup in a saucepan.
Stir in Jell-O and boil until mixed.
Simmer on low heat for 5 minutes.
Immediately pour the mixture over the popcorn, tossing to coat.
Spread out in a 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan.
Bake for 10 minutes.
After the popcorn cools, enjoy!

title: cheeseburger bites
directions: In a bowl, combine egg yolk, ground beef, onion, salt and pepper. Shape mixture by teaspoonfuls into 24 balls. Remove crusts from bread. Roll flat and cut into 1 1/2-inch rounds. Place meatballs on bread rounds. Make a depression in each ball and fill with a cube of cheese, making sure bread is covered with meat mixture. Place on baking sheet. Broil in preheated oven about 6-inches from heat for 3 to 5 minutes or until no pink remains. Garnish with ketchup, mustard, sliced green onions or sliced dill pickles, if desired.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Layer bread; then sausage.
Mix the rest of the ingredients then pour over bread and sausage.
Set in refrigerator overnight. Cook, covered, at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pie.
Put in unbaked crust.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: chocolate chip cookie pudding pie
directions: You will need two 8-inch diameter circular pan.

title: brown rice casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients in greased 1 1/2-quart casserole. Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour. Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: english brown stew
directions: Dredge meat in seasoned flour.
Melt shortening in hot skillet and brown meat.
Reduce heat.
Add paprika, allspice, sugar, lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce, tomato juice and water.
Cover and cook over low heat for 1 1/2 hours.
Stir occasionally, adding more water if needed.

title: baked stew
directions: Brown meat in skillet.
Brown onion ring slices, salt and pepper each layer.
Layer as follows:
potatoes, meat, onions, carrots and potatoes in a roasting pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until done.

title: scalloped cabbage
directions: Cut cabbage in wedges and steam until tender in lightly salted water; drain well in colander while making sauce.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Combine sweet potatoes, sugar, eggs, milk, salt and vanilla and mix well.
Pour into buttered 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Combine brown sugar, flour, pecans and butter and mix well.
Spread over sweet potato mixture.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown ground beef with onion; drain.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer 1 hour.

title: gourmet potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes with skins until tender.
Let cool.
Peel and grate on large side of cheese grater.
In a saucepan on low heat, combine cheese and butter.
Keep stirring until almost melted. Remove from heat and blend in sour cream.
Add onions, salt and pepper.
Add potatoes and mix. Pour into a greased 2 qt casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except potato chips.
Pour in greased 3-quart casserole.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Top with potato chips last 15 minutes.

title: strawberry supreme salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Fold in strawberries, pineapple, bananas and pecans.
Pour one-half of mixture into 12 x 8 x 1-inch dish or mold.
Chill until set.
Mix sour cream and cream cheese.
Spread on jello.
Add remaining jello; chill.

title: prune cake
directions: Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: zucchini puffs
directions: Mix all ingredients well and drop by spoonful in 375° hot oil. Fry until brown and drain on paper towels.
Serve hot.

title: chicken spaghetti(number served: 8 to 10 people)
directions: Boil chicken with one piece celery and salt and pepper to taste.
Chop cooked chicken into bite size pieces.
Boil spaghetti in chicken stock, adding water (or chicken broth) if necessary. Add cheese to hot spaghetti so it will melt.
Saute chopped onions and peppers in oleo.
Add remaining ingredients to spaghetti and mix.
Bake in 350° oven until bubbles.

title: sensational double layer pumpkin pie
directions: Mix cream cheese, milk and sugar in large bowl with wire whip until smooth.
Gently stir in whipped topping.
Spread in bottom of pie crust.
Pour 1 cup milk into a bowl and mix in instant pudding with wire whip, 1 to 2 minutes.
Stir in pumpkin and spices; mix well.
Spread over cream cheese layer.
Refrigerate for at least 3 hours.
Garnish with additional whipped topping and nuts, if desired.
Serves 8.

title: po boy steak
