directions: Mix well first 6 ingredients.
Shape into loaf or narrow shape. Let stand in refrigerator for 8 hours or overnight.
Slice and fry until brown.
Place in roaster in layers and cover with mushroom soup.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: quick egg custard pie
directions: Beat eggs, add sugar and beat well.
Add flavoring, butter and milk.
Put in prepared unbaked crust and bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: sauerkraut in a jar
directions: Shred the cabbage.
Put the cabbage and salt in a large pan. Mix with hands, then pack into jars. Fill with cold water.
Put on caps (I boil mine) and put screw bands on tightly. Allow to ferment 3 to 4 days (I put jars on layers of newspapers).
Wash outside of jars and tighten screw bands and process in boiling bath for 15 minutes. Wait 6 weeks before using.

title: grandma's easy pickles
directions: Drain pickles and cut in 1/4-inch slices.
Put sugar, vinegar and spices in saucepan. Heat until boiling, stirring constantly, and the sugar has melted.
Remove from heat.
Let syrup get cold. Put pickles back into the jar.
Pour syrup over the pickles. Shake several times and put in refrigerator. May store upside down so the syrup will cover the ones on top.

title: quick rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Combine sugar, oil and buttermilk; stir into yeast mixture.
Stir in enough flour to make a soft dough.
Turn dough out on a lightly floured surface and knead 1-2 minutes or until smooth and elastic; roll to 1/2 inch thickness and cut with floured biscuit cutter.
Place butter in center of each roll; fold over in half.
Place rolls on heavily greased baking sheet; cover and let rise in a warm place until doubled in size.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Yield:
about 2 dozen rolls.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake in greased 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish, 20 to 25 minutes at 400°.

title: spoon rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in 2 cups warm water; add sugar, margarine and egg.
Stir in flour.
Beat and mix well.
Spoon into greased muffin pans and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Mix well keep in refrigerator for about 1 week.
Makes about 2 dozen rolls.

title: cranberry chicken
directions: Place chicken pieces in a 3-quart casserole.
Mix cranberry sauce, soup mix and French dressing.
Pour over chicken and marinate 1 to 2 hours (or longer).
Turn chicken pieces occasionally.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours, uncovered, turning chicken once to brown on all sides.
Serve on rice.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: pecan pie
directions: This recipe came from my mom, Margaret Poor, which has been in our family for 35 years.

title: no-cook strawberry preserves
directions: Mash strawberries; mix well with sugar.
Let stand 10 minutes. Mix Sure-Jell with water; bring to a boil and cook 1 minute.
Add this to strawberry mixture and mix well.
Put in glass jars, leaving headspace.
Let stand 24 hours, then freeze.

title: banana bread
directions: Note:
This recipe has no eggs or milk.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix ingredients as listed.
Pour into a greased tube pan.
Bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.
Cool and remove from tube pan.

title: brown sugar baked apples
directions: Core apples, being sure not to cut all the way through.
Cut a thin crosswise slice from top of each.
Place apples on microwave-safe pie plate.
Cover with waxed paper and microwave on High for 3 to 4 minutes, rotating dish 1/4 turn once.
Meanwhile, mix sugar, water, flour and cinnamon in small bowl until smooth. Spoon evenly over apples; dot with butter.
Cover and microwave on High for 2 to 3 minutes, until sauce is bubbly and apples are barely tender.
Let stand 3 minutes until tender.
Spoon sauce from pie plate over apples.

title: beef casserole
directions: Put all ingredients, except 1 can beef broth in slow cooker on medium setting.
Let cook for about 6 hours.
1 hour before serving add 1 small can beef broth and bring to a boil.
Add 1 pkg. Kulski noodles. Enjoy.

title: lime-lemon salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water; chill until syrupy.
Add sweetened condensed milk, mayonnaise, cottage cheese, pineapple and nuts.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: joe's steak seasoning
directions: In shallow baking dish, coat steaks with lemon juice on both sides.
Add meat tenderizer and rest of ingredients to top side of steaks.
Then repeat on other side.
Cover and refrigerate for not more than 24 hours.
Cook as desired.

title: veal marsala
directions: On waxed paper, mix flour, salt, pepper and garlic salt; coat veal well with flour mixture.
In large skillet over medium-high heat with 4 tablespoons of butter or olive oil, cook veal until well browned on both sides.
Remove meat to a platter and keep warm.
Reduce heat to low.
Stir wine and water into drippings, scraping to loosen bits.
Return veal to skillet.
Cover; simmer 45 minutes or until veal is fork-tender.
To make fancier add 1/2 pound sliced mushrooms while meat is simmering.
Arrange meat on platter; pour sauce and mushrooms over meat.

title: louise cox's carrot cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients together and add salad oil, beaten eggs, grated carrots, crushed pineapple, orange rind, raisins, coconut and nuts.
Beat 2 minutes at medium speed.
Bake in oiled 15 x 11-inch pan at 350° for 1 hour.
Cut cake in 2 pieces and ice for layer cake.

title: carrot cake
directions: Combine oil and sugar together.
Add eggs one at a time, beating after each.
Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and cinnamon and add to egg mixture.
Fold in carrots and nuts.
Grease and flour 3 (9-inch) cake pans.
Pour in batter.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Cool and frost with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: glazed onions and carrots
directions: Place carrots in large saucepan with 1-inch boiling water. Cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Add onions; cook 5 minutes longer. Drain.
Return vegetables to saucepan; add margarine, brown sugar, ginger and salt.
Stir frequently.
Cook over medium heat for 5 minutes, enough time to glaze.
Makes about 4 cups.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine sugar,	milk
and margarine and boil 5 minutes. Remove from
heat	and
stir
in peanut butter and marshmallow whiz. Pour into baking pan and cool.

title: cajun style beans
directions: Cook vegetables in butter until tender.
Add remaining ingredients and heat over low heat.
Makes about 3 cups (6 servings).

title: no fat angel cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Have egg whites at room temperature. In a large mixer bowl, place egg whites.
Add salt, vanilla extract and cream of tartar.
Beat until stiff.
Gradually add sugar, 1/4 cup at a time, until all has been added.
Fold in flour 1/4 cup at a time.
Pour into an ungreased 9-inch tube pan.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.
Invert and cool completely.

title: cajun cake
directions: Mix together and bake at 350 degrees 35 to 40 minutes.

title: fruit salad
directions: In small saucepan, heat 1 cup of liquid to boiling.
In a large bowl, add boiling liquid to gelatin.
Stir to dissolve.
Add remaining liquid.
Chill until thickened, but not set.
Fold in whipped cream.
Add remaining ingredients and blend well.
Cover and refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Will keep for 2 days when dessert topping mix is used.
Makes 8 servings.

title: funny cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until center comes out clean with cake tester.

title: ma ballard's bread and butter pickles
directions: Cover cucumbers with ice; let stand for 3 hours, then drain. In a large kettle, put 3 cups of cider vinegar, 4 cups sugar, the turmeric, celery seed and mustard seed.
Bring to a boil, then add the cucumbers.
Bring to a good boil and can.

title: baked yellow crookneck squash
directions: Spray a 9 x 13-inch baking pan with a nonstick spray.
Place half of the squash in pan. Top with half the mushrooms, cheese and bread crumbs.
In a small bowl, mix together soup with 1 1/2 cans of water.
Pour half of this mixture over squash. Sprinkle with garlic powder, salt and pepper.
Repeat with remaining ingredients.
Top with French fried onion rings and bake in a 350° oven for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: spinach dip
directions: Cook frozen spinach as instructions indicate on package and drain as much as possible.
Mix all ingredients together.
Serve on crackers or as a dip with fresh raw vegetables.

title: melt-in-your-mouth rolls
directions: Scald the milk in a saucepan.
Pour over the shortening, sugar and salt in a large mixing bowl.
Cool to lukewarm.
Sprinkle the yeast over the lukewarm water and stir to dissolve.
Add the yeast mixture, 3 cups of the flour and eggs to the milk mixture.
Beat, using an electric mixer set on medium speed, for about 2 minutes. Gradually stir in enough of the remaining flour to make a soft dough.

title: christmas jello
directions: Mix Jell-O, water, lemon juice and salt together.
Pour into an 8 x 8-inch pan and refrigerate until it sets up a little.
Add other ingredients and mold in refrigerator until firm.
This is pretty at Christmas.

title: peanut cluster candy
directions: Put sugar, butter, milk and cocoa in a pan.
Cook to a full rolling boil.
Remove at once and add peanut butter, vanilla and raw peanuts. Stir well until all is moistened.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Mix mayonnaise, lemon juice and seasonings.
Combine crumbs, cheese and parsley.
Roll chicken in mayonnaise mixture.
Roll in crumb mixture.
Place in baking dish and cover tightly with foil. Bake at 400° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: no bake banana pudding
directions: Mix milk and pudding and then add Eagle Brand milk and mix well. Add vanilla. Fold in 2/3
of cool whip. Layer wafers, bananas, and pudding mix 2 or 3 times. Top with 1/3 cool whip. Sprinkle top with nuts or finely crushed wafers. Chill at least 2 hours.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Cook broccoli.
Saute onions and celery in margarine.
Add Cheez Whiz and rice.
Mix everything together.
Place in greased casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: wassail
directions: Combine sugar, water and spices in saucepan.
Simmer 10 minutes on low heat.
Discard spices.
Add juices to syrup.
Heat and serve.
A crock-pot can be used to keep the wassail warm.

title: egg pies(2 deep crust)
directions: Cream butter, flour and sugar; add eggs one at a time.
Pour in milk and flavor.
Preheat oven to 375° and bake until brown; reduce heat to 325° until done.

title: cheese bread
directions: Slice off small portion of top crust.
Combine margarine, poppy seed, dry mustard and onions.
Spread on both sides of bread slices and a little on top side of loaf.

title: onion blossom
directions: Peel onion, leaving root end intact.
Cut onion vertically into quarters, cutting to within 1/2-inch of rooted end.
Cut each quarter vertically into thirds.
Place onion in boiling water 1 minute; remove and place in ice water 5 minutes.
Loosen petals if necessary.
Drain onion, cut side down.
Place flour into a zip-top plastic bag.
Add onion, tossing to coat.
Chill 1 hour.
Pour oil to depth of 3 inches into an electric fryer or heavy saucepan and heat to 375°.
Fry onions 5 to 7 minutes or until golden brown. Drain on paper towels.
Sprinkle with salt, if desired.
Serve onions with dark honey mustard or Ranch style salad dressing.

title: swedish nuts
directions: Beat egg white until stiff.
Add sugar and cinnamon; beat all together.
Add nuts.
Mix by hand until coated.
Melt the butter on cookie sheet, then put the nuts on the buttered sheet and bake at 275° for 20 to 25 minutes, stirring every 5 minutes.
When done, put nuts on brown paper bag to cool.
Put in dish and cover or serve.

title: orange smoothie
directions: Blend with an electric mixer or shake until smooth. Serve cold. May also add ice while mixing in a blender to make it slushy.

title: boston cream cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In large bowl, combine flour, baking soda and cream of tartar.
Set aside.
In medium bowl, mix honey, orange juice concentrate, water, vanilla, orange extract, orange peel, 1 unbeaten egg white and apricot puree.
Stir into flour mixture until just blended.
Gently stir in 1 lightly beaten egg white.
Do not overmix.

title: dutch cookies or cake
directions: For cookies, knead into smooth balls about 3/4-inch. Place and press on buttered baking sheet.
Bake in a 350° preheated oven for about 12 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: ham balls
directions: Mix together first 4 ingredients.
Make into balls the size of golf balls.
Makes about 25 balls.
Put in a baking dish.
Pour a sauce made of remaining ingredients over meat balls.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Can be kept in a crock-pot on low for 3 hours.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Peel and saute eggplant in 2 tablespoons butter until tender. Drain and mash.
Mix in order given.
Pour in a baking dish.
Bake until brown.

title: trout with pecan sauce
directions: Rinse trout under cold water and pat dry.
In a brown paper bag, combine cornmeal, flour, peppers and paprika.
Put one or two trout in bag and shake to coat evenly.
Remove and set aside. Repeat with remaining trout.
Over medium-high heat, melt 2 tablespoons butter and 1 tablespoon oil in large skillet.
Add trout and cook above 5 minutes per side or until brown and flake easily.
Repeat until all trout are cooked.
Keep trout warm on platter covered with foil.
Put remaining butter, orange juice and pecans into pan and cook until bubbly.
Pour over trout and serve.

title: pineapple salad dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a saucepan.
Cook until thickens.
Cool.
Pour over pineapple, cubed cheese, marshmallows and nuts.

title: coconut cream cheese frosting
directions: Melt 2 tablespoons of butter in skillet.
Add coconut.
Stir over low heat until brown.
Spread coconut on paper to cool. Cream 2 tablespoons of butter with cream cheese.
Add milk; beat in sugar gradually.
Blend in vanilla.
Stir in 1 3/4 cups of cooled coconut.
Spread on top and sides of cake.
Sprinkle with remaining coconut.

title: baked beans deluxe
directions: Cook onion in bacon fat.
Add to pork and beans in a 1 1/2-quart casserole (greased).
Add rest of ingredients; mix well. Cover; bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: potato salad
directions: Peel and cube potatoes; cook, drain, and mash. Boil eggs; chop or process in food chopper. Add eggs to potatoes. Drain pimentos and add along with relish to mixture. Add mayonnaise and mustard to suit your preference. Season with Tony's seasoning or if you prefer use salt and pepper. You can sprinkle a little sugar if you find the salad too tart. Makes 60 servings. Can be doubled or tripled for larger quantities.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Cook carrots about 10 minutes.
Mix rest of ingredients together and pour over carrots.
Let stand overnight.
Keep well refrigerated.

title: pot or chuck roast
directions: With a small knife, make slits in several places on roast. Place garlic cloves or pieces of cloves into these slits. Sprinkle with salt, pepper and Italian seasoning.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes per pound.

title: beef 'n potato loaf
directions: Arrange evenly in greased 2-quart baking dish, potatoes, 1 tablespoon onion, 1 teaspoon salt, 1/8 teaspoon pepper and parsley.
Mix in bowl ground beef, evaporated milk and cracker crumbs or rolled oats.
Spread evenly over potatoes.
Decorate top with ketchup, if desired.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 4 servings.

title: craft clay
directions: Combine cornstarch and baking soda in a pan.
Add water gradually, stirring until smooth.
Place mixture over medium heat; cook until thickened and doughlike in consistency, stirring constantly.
Turn mixture out onto pastry board; knead well. Cover with damp cloth, or keep in a plastic bag.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Put sugar, flour and corn meal in bowl.
Toss lightly with fork and add eggs, butter, milk, lemon rind and lemon juice.
Beat until smooth and thoroughly blended.
Line 9-inch pie pan with pastry.
Bake in a 375°
oven for 35 to 40 minutes or until golden brown.
Cuts warm.

title: pierogi one-dish
directions: After mashing potatoes, mix in cheddar cheese.
Saute onion in butter.
In a well-greased casserole dish, place a layer of noodles, potatoes, then onions.
Repeat with second layer, cover and bake at 325° for 25 minutes.
Sour cream may be added when serving.

title: carrot cake(easy)
directions: Mix ingredients except carrots; then add carrots and mix well. Pour into pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pea pickin cake
directions: Mix all together 2 to 3 minutes. Bake in 3 layers at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Mix and pat into 13 x 9-inch greased pan.

title: tomatoes vinaigrette
directions: If using small tomatoes, cut off stem ends.
Arrange tomatoes in 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
In tightly covered jar, shake oil, vinegar, oregano, salt, pepper, mustard and garlic; pour over tomatoes.
Cover; chill 2 to 3 hours, spooning dressing over tomatoes occasionally.
Just before serving, arrange tomatoes on lettuce.
Sprinkle tomatoes with onion and parsley; drizzle with dressing.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: no-bake cookies
directions: Melt sugar, butter, cocoa and milk. Bring to a boil. Boil 2 1/2 minutes. Remove from heat. Add vanilla, oatmeal and coconut. Drop by teaspoonful on wax paper or press into greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.

title: quick chili
directions: Cook beef in hot frypan until lightly browned.
Drain off fat; stir in remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: orange jello salad
directions: Stir together jello, water, sugar and cream cheese.
Add the pineapple with juice.
Stir in container of Cool Whip; chill.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Combine crumb and herb stuffing with butter; set aside.
Cook squash, onions and carrots in boiling water for 5 minutes; drain. Combine soup and sour cream.
Stir all together except stuffing. Spread 1/2 of stuffing on bottom of 12 x 7 1/2-inch pan.
Spread on vegetables.
Spread remainder of stuffing on top and bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Serves 6.

title: mrs. salm's sausage cake
directions: Mix sausage and sugar well.
Add soda to coffee, then to sausage and sugar.
Add raisins, nuts and salt, then the flour. Bake in layer pans in moderate oven (325° to 350°) until cake shrinks from side of pan.
Ice with brown sugar icing.

title: fried onion rings
directions: Slice onions and separate into rings.
Make a batter of the beaten egg and milk.
Sift together flour and seasoned salt.
Dip onion rings into egg, then flour and cook in hot Wesson oil until golden brown.
Serve hot.

title: blue ribbon carrot cake
directions: Beat oil and sugar in large mixing bowl.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift in dry ingredients.
Add vanilla, carrots, pineapple and nuts.
Line 14 x 10 pan with waxed paper (or cake WILL stick and come apart).
Bake at 350° for one hour or until done.
Cool completely.

title: chili burgers
directions: Saute ground beef, onion and fat.
Drain.
Add remaining ingredients.
If too runny, add small amount of instant oatmeal. Can freeze this.

title: texas chili
directions: Toast cumin (if whole) lightly.
Saute onions and garlic in oil.
Sear meat until greyish color.
Place all in large pot.
Add water to cover.
Let simmer, stirring often, for 1 1/2 hours.

title: unstuffed cabbage
directions: Brown meat and onion; core cabbage and cut into 1-inch strips. Add to meat mixture. Cover and cook on medium heat about 6 minutes or until cabbage wilts, stirring occasionally. Stir into mixture the tomatoes, sugar, vinegar and salt. Bring to boil; reduce heat. Cover, stirring often. Simmer 10 minutes or until cabbage is tender. Serve over rice or noodles. Makes 6 servings. Preparation time: 0:30.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: Beat eggs; add milk, bread crumbs, salt and pepper.
Let stand a few minutes.
Add parsley and beef.
Mix and shape in balls and brown in half the butter.
Remove from pan.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken with garlic.
Saute onion, peppers and celery in margarine.
Add tomato sauce and seasonings.
Bone chicken and add to sauce.
Cook spaghetti in chicken broth.
Combine sauce and spaghetti.

title: beef salad - shabu-shabu style(servings:  8)
directions: If pre-sliced beef is not available, cut lightly frozen beef into thin slices.
Put water in a deep pan and bring to boil.
Put slices of beef into boiling water one by one.
Take out as soon as the color changes.
Cool in cold water and drain on paper towels. Slice onions and soak in cold water for 1 hour or longer; drain well.
Arrange slices of beef on onion.
To make Pon-zu, mix lemon juice, soya sauce and sugar.
Serve with Pon-zu.

title: flounder (or cod) primavera
directions: Melt margarine.
Add broccoli and onion and saute.
Stir in tomatoes, lemon juice and dill.
Remove from heat.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Serve with vegetable crackers.

title: company chicken(serves 4 to 6)
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Mix salad dressing, onion soup and apricot preserves.
Pour over chicken and marinate overnight (optional).
Bake 1 hour and 10 minutes, depends on thickness of chicken parts.
Serve with rice and tossed salad.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Cut strawberries in half and put one extra cup of sugar on them.
Cook
the cornstarch, Jell-O, water and sugar until thick and
dark.
Pour
the juice off of the strawberries and put
them in the cooked pie shells.
Pour cooked mixture over strawberries and
chill
for
one
hour.
Top
with Cool Whip before serving.

title: enchilada dip
directions: Brown hamburger.
Add all other ingredients together in crock-pot.
Cook on high for 2 to 3 hours.
Serve with Tostitos chips.
Serves about 12 to 15.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Cook macaroni; salt to taste.
Mix all ingredients together. Cover with buttered cracker crumbs.
Bake for about 30 minutes at 350°.

title: blueberry cream cheese torte
directions: Set oven at 350°.
Mix together crushed cracker crumbs, butter and 1/2 cup sugar.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: corn salad
directions: In medium sized bowl, combine corn, sweet pepper, green onion or chives and basil or other herb; toss well.
Stir in the mayonnaise and season with salt and pepper to taste.

title: oriental cashew crunch
directions: Heat oven to 250°.
Combine first 3 ingredients in 13 x 9-inch pan; set aside.
Combine remaining 4 ingredients in small bowl; quickly pour over cereal mixture.
Stir to coat evenly.
Bake 1 hour, stirring every 20 minutes; cool.
Makes 10 cups.

title: 7-layer salad
directions: Combine sugar and mayonnaise.
Layer lettuce, small package peas, onion, celery and pepper at least twice.
End with peas and onion on top.
Then spread with mayonnaise and sugar mixture and sprinkle with cheese.
Let stand overnight in refrigerator.
Put crumbled bacon on top before serving.

title: scotch meat pie
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Add onions and green pepper and cook slightly.
Remove from heat.
Add soup and blend well.
Add seasonings and remaining ingredients.
Pour into pie crust.
Seal with top crust.
Make slits in top crust and brush with melted butter.
Bake at 375° for approximately 40 minutes until crust is slightly brown.

title: lemon and herb marinade
directions: Combine all ingredients in a medium saucepan and heat to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for approximately 5 minutes.
Allow to cool.
Place meat in a glass dish and coat with cooled marinade.
Cover and refrigerate for at least 4 hours (overnight if possible).

title: kielbasa mix
directions: Fry potatoes with kielbasa, green pepper and onion about 1 hour.
Serve with melted cheese on top.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix onion, peas, carrots, chicken, broth, celery soup, salt and pepper.
Mix Bisquick, butter and milk; pour over the mixture. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: patti's penny potatoes
directions: Peel and cook potatoes until almost tender; cool.
Shred or grate potatoes into a large bowl.
Melt 1/4 cup butter in a medium saucepan.
Add soup and mix until blended.
Add onion, cheese and sour cream.
Mix until blended.
Add to potatoes and mix well. Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt 2 tablespoons butter and add cornflake crumbs.
Sprinkle over top of potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Great with ham, turkey or chicken.

title: colorful oven veggies
directions: Place butter in a shallow 3 qt. baking dish; place in a 400° oven for 5 minutes or until melted.
Stir in thyme, salt and pepper.
Add vegetables and toss to coat.
Cover and bake for 25-30 minutes or until the vegetables
are crisp and tender.

title: 24 hour fruit salad
directions: Mix well; stir and put in refrigerator and chill overnight.

title: reese cups
directions: Cream margarine and peanut butter.
Add sugar until it is the consistency to form into balls the size of large marbles.
Add vanilla; mix thoroughly with hands.
Melt chocolate and paraffin in small double boiler.
Dip balls in chocolate, using toothpicks to dip with.
Space on waxed paper to cool.
This candy will freeze.

title: frances wright's pound cake
directions: Grease and flour an angel food cake pan.
Do not heat oven.

title: seafoam candy
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients, beating thoroughly in saucepan. Cover and cook until sugar dissolves in saucepan; stir constantly. Continue cooking until syrup forms a very firm, but not brittle ball when tested in cold water.
Remove from heat.
Gradually pour syrup over two egg whites, stiffly beaten.
Beat continually while adding syrup, until candy holds shape.
Add 1 teaspoon vanilla and walnuts or pecans.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on waxed paper.
Cool and store.

title: pineapple nut delight
directions: Pour boiling water over Jell-O.
Dissolve.
Add ice cubes and stir.
Let stand in refrigerator to set.
Set cream cheese aside to soften.
Prepare Dream Whip.
When Jell-O is partially set, add cream cheese and mix with mixer.
Add Dream Whip, crushed pineapple and pecans.
Set in refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: mama cole's chow chow
directions: Chop onions and peppers.
Mix all vegetables with 1/2 cup of salt.
Let stand overnight.
Drain.
Place mixed spices in a permeable bag.
Add sugar and other spices to vinegar.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Add all other ingredients and simmer until hot and well seasoned.
Remove "spice bag."
Pack hot chow chow into hot, sterilized jars and seal at once.

title: recipe for discovery
directions: Combine talented teacher and eager young minds.
Add cupfuls of curiosity and spoonfuls of fun.
Blend in generous amounts of hands-on participation, mixed with patience.
Sprinkle with laughter and serve with enthusiasm.
Yields:
learning at its best.

title: granny bolt's no bake cheesecake
directions: Mix together 2 envelopes Knox unflavored gelatin, sugar and salt in the top of a double broiler.
Beat egg yolks and milk; add to gelatin mixture.
Cook over boiling water, stirring constantly until gelatin is dissolved and mixture thickens, about 10 minutes. Remove from heat and cool.
Stir in cottage cheese and crushed pineapple.
Chill, stirring occasionally until mixture mounds slightly when dropped from spoon.

title: candy apples
directions: Cook ingredients quickly without stirring to 290°.
Add a few drops of red food coloring.
Place in hot water to keep from hardening.
Dip skewed apples at once.
Cool on a greased cookie sheet.

title: minty delight
directions: Scrape seeds from bean.
Combine seeds, bean and milk; bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and let stand for 30 minutes. Discard bean.
Add sugar, gelatin, peppermint and salt; let stand 1 minute.
Cook over low heat 5 minutes or until gelatin dissolves.
Cool completely.
Stir in yogurt and corn syrup.
Pour into a bowl; cover and chill 8 hours.
Using a 1-quart hand turned or 1/2-gallon electric freezer, freeze according to manufacturer's instructions.
Chill 1 hour until firm.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Slice large onion in bottom of gallon jar.
Mix the other ingredients and fill jar with sliced cucumbers.
Keeps 5 to 6 months in the refrigerator.
Do not seal.
Shake everyday for 4 days.

title: cherry delight
directions: Prepare Dream Whip.
Put in refrigerator for 1 hour.

title: banana muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease bottoms of cupcake pans.
Beat egg slightly; stir in remaining ingredients just until moistened. Divide batter evenly.
Bake until golden brown, 15 to 17 minutes. Makes 12 muffins.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Brown bacon. Drain well and crumble.
Mix all ingredients together and chill.
You may substitute Bac*Os or bacon bits for the bacon, if you wish.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream softened oleo and cream cheese, add sugar and beat well. Add 2 eggs and 1 cup flour.
Beat well.
Add 2 eggs and 1 cup flour; beat well.
Add 2 eggs and 1/2 cup flour and salt.
Beat well.
Add flavoring.
Put in cold oven.
Bake at 275° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: holly candy
directions: Melt first 3 ingredients over hot water.
Add rest of ingredients; drop onto wax paper to cool.
Dot with red cinnamon candies.
Looks like a Christmas wreath.

title: cheese and bacon dip
directions: Mix all together and chill.

title: mom's infamous ginger cookies
directions: Mix together the molasses, shortening, baking soda, ginger, cinnamon, sugar, water and vanilla; blend well.
Add enough flour to make a stiff dough.
Roll out on floured board or counter and cut with cookie cutter(s).
Thin cookies will be crisp, while thicker cookies will be soft and chewy.
Bake first batch on greased cookie sheets.
Bake in 350° oven for 8 to 10 minutes. Frost while hot.
Yields 100 cookies.

title: mincemeat jello salad
directions: Heat 1/2 cranberry juice; add Jell-O, Knox gelatine and lemon juice.
Gradually add rest of cranberry juice; set to cool until like egg white consistency.
Add apples, mincemeat and nuts.
Pour into greased mold.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars.
Mix in eggs and vanilla.
Stir in soda and flour.
Roll in small balls.
Press onto baking pan with a fork.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: oven beef stew
directions: In a plastic bag, combine meat and the 1 tablespoon flour; shake to coat meat.
Spray a 4 1/2-quart Dutch oven with nonstick spray coating.
Add meat and onion; cook until meat is brown and onion is tender.
Drain off any fat.
Add potatoes, undrained tomatoes, tomato paste, water, bouillon, sugar, thyme, Worcestershire sauce and bay leaf.
Bake, covered, in a 350° oven for 1 hour.
Add eggplant.
Cover and bake for 30 minutes more.

title: hens in curry sauce
directions: Melt butter in roasting pan.
Stir in honey, mustard and curry powder.
Mix well.
Remove from heat.
Split hens in half. Place skin side down in sauce.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes, basting often.
Turn and bake 10 minutes more until golden brown.

title: the roar dinner
directions: Broil chicken until cooked through and grill slightly.
Fill pan with 2 quarts water; bring to boil and add fettucini.
Cook 8 to 10 minutes.
Remove noodles; drain and rinse in hot water. Place on plate (4 each).
Melt butter; add milk and stir in sauce mix.
Toss slightly until smooth and thickened.
Place chicken on top of noodles and pour sauce over each.
It will make you R-O-A-R.

title: mexican appetizer
directions: Mix the cream cheese and taco mix (and mayo if necessary) together.
Spread on tortillas and roll as a burrito.
Cut each rolled tortilla into 1/2 inch slices.
Serve with a bowl of picante sauce for dipping.
Makes a lot!

title: brownie cheesecake
directions: Prepare 1/2 brownie mix using 1/2 of all the required ingredients, except the egg-use the whole egg(s).
Bake 15 minutes at 350° in spring-form pan.
Mix cheese, sugar and vanilla; slowly add 2 eggs, 1 at a time.
Pour onto brownie base.
Melt the chocolate morsels.
Drop melted chocolate by tablespoonfuls onto cheese mixture and swirl with a knife.
Bake 35 minutes.
Cool. Open pan.
Refrigerate at least 3 hours.

title: 5 cup salad
directions: Drain crushed pineapple, mandarin oranges and maraschino cherries before adding.
Mix all ingredients and refrigerate overnight.

title: berry country cobbler
directions: Mix the milk, olive oil, sugar and Bisquick together; put in bottom of a greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Mix th berries, sugar and water together.
Pour on top of batter.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour, uncovered.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Beat eggs. Add all of the rest of the ingredients. Mix well. Pour into a casserole dish. Bake for 50 minutes or until browned and set.

title: mrs. mac's corn pudding
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl and beat.
Grease in a large baking dish.
Pour mixture into a baking dish (dish should only be half full).
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes, uncovered. Increase heat for an additional 5 minutes to brown, if necessary.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 350 degrees for 55 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: chili-egg puff
directions: Beat eggs until fluffy, light and lemon colored.
Add flour, baking powder, salt, cottage cheese, Jack cheese and melted butter.
Blend until mixed.
Stir in chilies.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until top is lightly brown and center appears firm.

title: strawberry scones
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Cut strawberries into 1/2-inch slices (makes 1 cup); set aside.
In a large bowl, mix dry ingredients. Cut in butter until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Stir in strawberries.
Toss well to coat.
Add milk.
Stir lightly with a fork until mixture holds together.
With floured hands, gently form into a ball.
On a floured board with a floured rolling pin, roll out dough 1/2 inch thick.
Cut into circles with a biscuit cutter.
Place on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake until golden, about 12 minutes.
Serve warm.
Makes 12 scones.

title: macaroni with spam
directions: Mix soup, catsup and butter together.
Bring to boil and pour over macaroni.
Let cool and add onion, pepper, cheese and Spam strips (the amount you desire).
Mix well.

title: barbecued ribs
directions: Trim
fat and remove membranes from ribs; place ribs in shallow
dish.
Mix
remaining ingredients.
Pour mixture over ribs;
turn
ribs.
Cover and refrigerate at least 2 hours but no longer than 24 hours.

title: cheddar nut bread
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a large bowl.
Set aside. Combine egg, milk and water; add to dry ingredients, stirring just until moistened.
Stir in pecans.
Spoon batter into a lightly greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Let cool in pan for 10 minutes.

title: southern biscuit muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease 12 (2 1/2-inch) muffin cups. (These muffins brown better on the sides and bottom when baked without paper liners.)
In large bowl, combine flour, sugar and baking powder.
Cut in butter until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Stir in milk just until flour mixture is moistened. Spoon into muffin cups.
Bake 20 minutes or until golden.
Remove from pan.
Cool on wire rack. Serve with jelly, jam or honey. Makes 12 servings.

title: french buttercream cookies
directions: (These make soft cookies.)

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix together.
Will barbecue 2 1/2 to 3 pounds meat.

title: chicken delight
directions: In saucepan, cook noodles according to package directions. Drain off liquid before adding seasoning.
Stir in cream of mushroom and milk.
Add chicken and broccoli.
Heat thoroughly, stirring often.
Stir in tomatoes, if using.
Makes 4 servings.

title: old fashioned oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet.
Press down to flatten out dough.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: apple crisp
directions: Place sliced apples in a buttered baking dish.
Add or sprinkle with cinnamon and water.
Work together sugar, flour and butter until crumbly.
Sprinkle over apples.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Serve hot with ice cream or whipped cream.

title: slaw
directions: Mix good sugar, vinegar, seed and turmeric.
Let boil several minutes.
Remove from heat and let cool.
Pour over mixed vegetables, stirring well.
Cover.
Let set overnight in refrigerator.

title: angel biscuits #3
directions: Sift flour.
Add sugar and cut in shortening.
The mix should look like coarse crumbs.
Add yeast (dissolved in warm water) and buttermilk.
Mix lightly, but thoroughly and knead 5 minutes. Refrigerate in covered container.

title: tex-mex salsa
directions: Cook first 5 ingredients until coarse. (15 minutes)
Add vinegar, salt, and sugar.
Simmer for 30 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook for 15-20 minutes longer.
Pour into jars and seal.
Makes about 6-8 pt.

title: fish au gratin
directions: Broil fillets 8 to 12 minutes.
Combine remaining ingredients and spread over fish.
Broil until puffy and golden, 1 to 3 minutes more.
Or, can put on when you put the fish under the broiler.

title: walnut pie
directions: Combine all ingredients in order given.
Place in pie shell. Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: golden potato casserole
directions: Combine cheese and
butter in a saucepan over low heat. Stir until cheese is
melted.
Remove from heat.
Stir in sour cream, onion, salt
and
pepper.
Add potatoes, mixing gently. Pour into a buttered
quart
casserole.
Dot
with 2 tablespoons butter. Bake at
350° for 30 minutes.
Yield:
8 to 10 servings.
Can grate
cheese
on top or can crumble cornflakes on top of casserole.

title: company corn
directions: Cook slowly until most of the liquid is cooked down and pepper is done.

title: rhubarb creme pie
directions: Pour boiling water over rhubarb and let stand 5 minutes. Drain.
Cook together and put into a baked crust.
Top with beaten egg whites.
Makes 1 pie.

title: french toast
directions: Heat pin.
Put oil in pan.
Scramble eggs in a bowl.
Put bread in scrambled eggs; take out and put in pan.
Cook until brown and eat.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Slice drained potatoes into one-half inch slices.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease pan, 12 x 8 x 2-inch.
Arrange potato slices in a row, overlapping, in prepared dish.
Sprinkle with brown sugar, salt, pepper and orange juice and peel.
Dot with butter. Cover dish with foil.
Bake 45 minutes.

title: mock scallop oyster
directions: Peel and cut eggplant in chunks.
Add sliced onions.
Cook in salted water until tender.
Drain and add butter.
While vegetables are cooking, prepare and combine other ingredients.
Add vegetables and mix thoroughly.
Bake at 325° for about 1 hour.
Great main dish.
It's like a souffle.

title: stuffed cabbage or galumpies
directions: Mix beef, rice, eggs, bell pepper and salt and pepper. Take thawed cabbage, lay flat and cut vein out. Take scoops of rice mixture and lay in leaf and roll, tucking sides. Put in pot and cover with tomato juice and stewed tomatoes. Cook on low to medium heat for about 1 1/2 hours until rice is done. May add water if needed. Can be baked for 1 to 2 hours at 375°.

title: rainbow poke cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on package, baking in well-greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cool cake in pan for 15 minutes, then prick with utility fork at 1/2-inch intervals.

title: snickers apple salad
directions: To prepare snickers bars, place frozen bars between pieces of saran wrap and break up with a hammer.
Cut up cored apples into bite size pieces.
Mix together lightly with cool whip.
Serve immediately.

title: mexican dip
directions: Layer the ingredients in a pie pan or casserole dish in the order listed.

title: cheese-broccoli soup
directions: In colander, thaw broccoli under hot tap water. In a large saucepan, cook and stir onion in butter, about 2 minutes.
Stir in flour.
Add chicken broth and milk.
Heat and stir until mixture comes to a boil. Cook and stir 1 minute.
Add chopped broccoli. Add cheese and lemon peel.
Heat and stir until cheese melts. Serves 4.

title: karen's cornbread
directions: Mix ingredients.
Pour in oblong glass baking pan, greased with lots of olive oil (1/3 cup).

title: summer squash zucchini pickle
directions: Slice yellow squash and zucchini into thin slices.
In large bowl, combine both kinds of squash, sliced lemon, pepper, onion and celery seed.
Toss gently to combine.
Let stand 1 hour.

title: maple divinity fudge
directions: Mix together syrup, sugar and water.
Boil to hard-ball stage.
Remove from fire.
Add vanilla and pour hot syrup over stiffly beaten egg white.
Add nuts.
Beat until stiff enough to hold shape.
Drop from teaspoon on waxed paper.

title: my husband's favorite yeast rolls
directions: Combine butter, sugar, salt, potato flakes and hot water. Set aside.
Sprinkle yeast on lukewarm water and stir until dissolved.
Add yeast and one cup flour to potato mixture.
Beat with mixer for 3 minutes.
Gradually, add remaining flour to make soft dough that pulls away from sides of bowl.
Place dough in greased bowl or baking dish.
Turn over to grease top.
Cover and let rise in warm place until doubled about 1 1/2 hours.
Place dough on floured surface.
Divide into about 24 pieces.
Shape slightly into balls.
Place balls into greased baking pan.
Set aside and let rise for 45 minutes.
Brush with melted butter and then bake until brown about 2 minutes.

title: beef stroganoff supreme
directions: Cut meat into strips 1/4-inch thick and 3 inches long.
Dredge meat in flour, salt and pepper.
Brown beef in oleo; add onion and garlic and saute.
Add flour and butter to beef broth; stir into browned beef.
Simmer 30 to 40 minutes.
Add mushrooms; simmer 5 more minutes.
Blend in sherry or Worcestershire sauce.
Fold in sour cream.
Heat through.
Serve over cooked rice or noodles.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni (package directions) in medium pan.
Place milk, cheese and butter on low to melt cheese.
Put cooked macaroni in baking dish.
Add cheese mix.
Bake 30 to 45 minutes at 350°. Serves 8.

title: hot clam dip
directions: Cook and stir onion and green pepper in butter until tender. Add cheese and cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until cheese is melted.
Add clams and salsa and heat through.
Serve hot with crackers.

title: ranch stew
directions: Brown
hamburger and onion.
Add the canned vegetables, including the
juice.
(Since
the juice forms the "stock" and flavor for the stew,
do
not
substitute
frozen vegetables.) Bring to a boil, then
reduce heat and cook thoroughly.
Serve with biscuits or cornbread.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except cheese and crackers.
Pour into large buttered baking dish.
Spread grated cheese over this to cover.
Then spread crackers (crushed) over cheese and casserole. Bake until good and bubbly or long enough for vegetables to be tender.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Let water come to a boil; add jello.
Choose bowl you want to serve dessert in.
Put in frozen strawberries; pour jello over strawberries.
Add crushed pineapple.
Halve mixture.
Put both mixtures in refrigerator to chill.
Spread sour cream over top; add the remaining mixture.
Top with pecans.

title: cranberry-jello mold
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in water.
Add pineapple juice and water mixture.
Stir and chill until partially set.
Add sugar and let stand 10 minutes.
Add berries and orange which have been coarsely ground.
Then add pineapple and nuts.
Stir well.
Pour into jello mold and place in refrigerator until set.

title: drop cookies - soft cake
directions: Cream the first 4 ingredients. Combine dry ingredients in another bowl.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk and vanilla. Drop by spoon on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Reserve broth from chicken.
Debone chicken.
Cook onion, bell pepper and celery in chicken broth (6 tablespoons).
Blend in flour.
Add liquid and cook until thick.
Add soup, pimento, olives, wine and chicken meat.
Stir in spaghetti.
If too thick, add more liquid.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Bake about 25 minutes until bubbly.
Add grated cheese and cook until melted.

title: apple pie with crust
directions: Crust:
Mix flour, salt and Crisco with a fork until coarse like meal.
Add 2 tablespoons water; mix and add 2 tablespoons water.
Roll out on floured surface; put in pan and let set for 30 minutes before baking.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Wash mushrooms thoroughly and cut off the very ends of the stems.
Pop off the stems of the mushroom caps and discard half of the removed stems.
Finely chop the balance.

title: cheese cake
directions: Preheat the oven to 325°.
Combine the graham cracker crumbs in the melted butter, cinnamon, nutmeg and 1/4 cup sugar.
Mix these ingredients well.
Butter a 9-inch spring-form pan and pat the crumb mixture over the bottom and 1-inch up the sides.
Chill.

title: chicken italian
directions: Cube uncooked chicken breasts (about 5 cubes per half breast). Place chicken and remaining ingredients, except for cheese, in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch casserole in order.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 50 minutes to 1 hour, until chicken is cooked and zucchini is almost tender.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and continue baking, uncovered, about 10 minutes.

title: banana mandarin pie
directions: Mix pudding, Dream Whip and milk until thickened.
Fold in half of mandarin oranges, bananas and coconut.
Pour into pie shell.
Top with the remaining bananas and oranges; sprinkle with coconut.
Chill in refrigerator for 1 to 2 hours (do not freeze).

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Mix above together and then add 1 box of pound cake, then add 1 cup of chopped nuts.
Spray long pan with Pam spray.
Pour into long pan and cook for 1 hour at 350°.
Cake is done when it cracks open.
Do not overcook; refrigerate overnight.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine soup, rice and milk all together.
Spray 9 x 13-inch pan with cooking spray and pour mixture into pan.
Place chicken on top (salt and pepper to taste) and sprinkle Lipton onion soup mix on top of chicken.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 30 minutes.

title: norwegian apple pie
directions: Beat well the eggs.
Beat in sugar and vanilla.
Add flour, baking powder, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Fold in nuts and apples.
Bake in two greased 9-inch pie plates, metal, at 375° for 30 minutes; Pyrex at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Sprinkle chops with salt and pepper.
Put in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Top each pork chop with a green pepper ring.
Spoon rice into ring.
Chop remainder of pepper and put into tomato sauce with water, onion, salt and pepper.
Pour over pork chops and rice. Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: festive chicken(for 2 of us)
directions: Wrap two bacon strips around chicken breast.
Place in shallow baking dish and set aside.
In a small mixing bowl, combine soy sauce and sugar.
Add remaining ingredients and pour over chicken, turning to coat evenly.
Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate overnight.
Drain.
Reserve marinade.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes, basting occasionally with marinade.

title: taco pie
directions: Brown beef; drain fat.
Add taco seasoning and 3/4 cup water. Simmer for 15 minutes.
Separate crescent rolls and place in cup of 12-cup cupcake pan and form a "bowl" with crescent roll.
Do not let crescent roll form over sides.
This will burn.
Add seasoned ground beef to crescent rolls and top with cheese.
For extra cheesy flavor, add cheese to cooked beef and top with more cheese. Bake at 375° for 10 to 13 minutes.
Pour taco sauce over top and serve.
Serves 6.

title: fruit rice mix(can be used as a gift.)
directions: Combine all ingredients; store in an airtight container or plastic bag.
Yield: 1 3/4 cups.

title: salsa
directions: Combine - bring to boil. Add 1 large can tomatoes, skim skins, simmer 30 minutes. Add spices 1 Tbsp. of each garlic powder, cumin, crushed red pepper, onion powder, cayenne pepper, and pepper.

title: bread pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients in order listed.
Bake in greased 9 x 13-inch pan for 1 hour at 350°.
Cool.
Slice into 2-inch square portions.
Serves 12 to 15.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add sifted flour, soda and salt, alternating with banana puree.
Fold in nuts.

title: tiny crab cakes
directions: Forty-five minutes before serving:
Tear white bread in blender container.
Cover blender and blend on low to form coarse crumbs.
Place crumbs in a medium bowl; set aside.
Slice 2 radishes into 8 thin slices.
Reserve for garnish.
Into same blender, place remaining radishes, crabmeat, eggs, salt and pepper.
Cover and blend on medium until mixture is well mixed. Blend with bread crumbs in bowl.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Cream brown sugar and butter together and put in bottom of casserole pan.
Place peach halves (or other fruit) on top of sugar and butter.

title: frothy apple punch
directions: In large mixing bowl combine apple cider and orange juice. Add the light cream.
Beat with rotary beater until frothy.
In small mixer bowl beat the egg whites on high speed of electric mixer until soft peaks form (tips curl over).
Gradually add the sugar, beating on high speed until stiff peaks form (tips stand straight).
Using rotary beater, gently fold the beaten egg whites into the cider-cream mixture, leaving small puffs of egg whites. Transfer mixture to a large punch bowl.
Sprinkle punch with a little ground cinnamon.
Serve immediately.

title: melting moments
directions: Cream the butter and sugar until soft and white.
Beat in eggs.
Add flour and salt, sifted together.
Make into a firm dough.
Dampen your hands.
Roll dough into balls about the size of a walnut and roll into the rolled oats.

title: easy coconut pie(adapted to microwave)
directions: Cook sugar, flour, cream and milk uncovered in microwave 6 to 8 minutes on Medium-High, stirring 3 times.
Beat egg yolks and flavoring and add 3 or 4 tablespoons hot mixture and beat well. Then add this to remaining mixture.
Microwave 1 to 1 1/2 minutes, longer if not thick.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Toast coconut in oven.
Sprinkle over pie.

title: white pizza
directions: Dissolve yeast in one cup of hot water.
Place in large bowl or pan.
Add oil, salt, sugar and egg.
Mix well with a large spoon.
Add flour, one cup at a time, mixing thoroughly; mixture will be soft.
Continue to add flour gradually until hard to mix with spoon.
Start mixing by hand, putting just enough flour until dough is pliable, but not dry.
Knead well a few minutes by fists. Let rise in larger bowl or pan, putting a little oil on bottom. Cover and let rise for one hour or until double in size.
Place on a greased rectangular pizza pan or cookie sheet.
Drizzle a light stream of oil over top.
Sprinkle grated Romano cheese and pizza seasoning over oil.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes on lower rack. Move to top rack at 400° for 10 minutes more.
Cool and cut with kitchen shears.

title: peanut butter special k cookies
directions: Boil sugar and corn syrup together.
Add peanut butter and Special K. Pour into well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Press down. Melt together chocolate and butterscotch chips for frosting.
Let sit 1 hour and cut into squares.

title: great grandma hillyer's sugar cookies
directions: Cream oil and sugar together in large mixing bowl.
Add eggs, sour cream and vanilla, mixing well.
In separate bowl, combine flour, soda and baking powder.
Add dry mixture to sour cream mixture.
Stir until well blended.
Chill for several hours or overnight.

title: hot potato salad
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Combine all ingredients except bacon, which is sprinkled on top.
Cover and bake 1 hour.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken; debone.
Mix all ingredients except cheese and chips.
Place chips in the bottom of a casserole dish.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Add soup mixture, more chips and cheese.
Put cheese on top.
Heat in oven at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: cheese pretzel sticks
directions: Mix ingredients; roll into 6-inch lengths. Allow to double in size. Bake at 425° for 15 minutes (optional: sprinkle with water). Variation:
Add bacon bits, onion, garlic, etc. for different flavors.

title: cornmeal rolls
directions: Soften yeast in warm water.
Combine cornmeal, shortening, salt, sugar and milk.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly. Cook over boiling water for 10 minutes.
Cool to lukewarm.
Add eggs and 1 1/2 cups flour; mix well.
Add yeast and rest of flour to make soft dough.
Knead until smooth and elastic (approximately 5 minutes).
Place in greased bowl.
Let rise until doubled in size.
Punch down and let rise 10 minutes.
Shape into rolls. Brush top lightly with melted butter.
Let rise until light.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Melt butter in a saucepan.
Add cocoa, oil and water.
Mix well.
Mix flour and sugar.
Add cocoa and oil mixture.
Add egg, buttermilk and baking soda.
Mix well.
Pour into a large greased sheet pan.
Bake at 350° for about 25 to 30 minutes, until a toothpick inserted in the center comes out clean.

title: burgundy meat balls
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients together and shape into 1-inch meat balls.
Brown meat balls in salad oil. Drain on paper towel. In a saucepan, combine wine, bouillon, water and flour. Bring to a boil. Add sugar and put meat balls in pan.
Bring to a boil again and reduce heat. Cover and simmer for 20 minutes.
Serve over noodles.

title: russell stover candy
directions: Mix powdered sugar, Eagle Brand milk, margarine, coconut and nuts together.
Chill overnight.
Roll in balls and chill again. Mix together in double boiler the chocolate chips and paraffin wax.
Dip ball of candy into chocolate mixture.

title: guacamole dip
directions: Blend all ingredients (except tomatoes) in food processor. Place
in
serving
dish.
Spread
sour
cream over top. Garnish with sliced ripe olives and salsa.
Serve with nachos or
corn chips.
(May
use refried beans and shredded Cheddar cheese.)

title: mustard sauce
directions: Mix mustard and vinegar until smooth and then let stand overnight.
Mix egg, sugar and salt.
Blend with mustard mixture. Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until mixture starts to thicken (about 20 minutes).
The longer you cook it the thicker it becomes.
Cool completely after mixture has reached desired thickness, then blend with mayonnaise.

title: caramel corn
directions: In a heavy saucepan, mix sugar, butter, syrup and salt.
Stir over medium heat until boiling.
Continue boiling, without stirring, for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla and soda.
Pour over popped corn; stir to coat well.
Bake in preheated 250° oven for 1 hour, stirring several times.
Cool and break apart.
Store in tightly covered container.
Add peanuts or pecans, if desired.

title: bacon dressing salad
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
Stir other items into bacon grease; heat to boiling.
Sprinkle bacon (crumbled) on lettuce and pour hot dressing over all.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Slice beef into thin strips and dust with flour and pepper. In large skillet, brown meat in margarine.
Drain mushrooms and add to skillet.
Brown onion slightly and add to skillet.
Stir in beef broth.
Cover and cook about 1 hour until meat is tender, stirring occasionally.
Gradually stir in sour cream.
Cook over low heat 5 minutes.
Serve over noodles.

title: oriental chicken wings
directions: Separate each chicken wing into three sections, discarding the tip section.
Rinse, then pat dry.
In an electric skillet, combine soy, water, sugar and ginger; bring to boil.
Add chicken wing pieces.
Reduce heat.
Simmer, covered, 30 minutes, stirring often.
Remove cover; simmer 15 to 30 minutes.

title: zucchini cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add egg and zucchini.
Sift dry ingredients and mix with creamed mixture.
Add raisins and nuts. Drop by spoonfuls on cookie sheet.	Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: sweet and sour dressing
directions: Note:
Three-fourth cup of mixture to 1/4 cup oil to serve.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Melt butter.
Add flour and blend.
Add cream cheese and Bleu cheese.
Combine well.
Add milk slowly and cook until it becomes a cream sauce.
Add broccoli.
Place in casserole and top with Ritz crackers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion in fat.
Add soups and water.
Mix well.
Add raw rice and blend throughly.
Pour into greased casserole dish.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Then uncover and cover top with buttered bread crumbs and bake 15 more minutes or until rice is tender.

title: spanish steak
directions: Sprinkle flour over both sides of steak.
Beat in all the flour you can.
Salt and pepper the steak.
Place steak in pan. Sprinkle with a little dry mustard and the brown sugar, then pour the tomato sauce and 1 can water over the steak.
Cover pan with aluminum foil.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: sweet & sour chicken
directions: Heat until mixture thickens Add chicken, pineapple, and veggies to sauce. I use water chestnuts and stir fried pea pods, but you can also use broccoli, cauliflower, bamboo chutes. Serve over rice.

title: cucumber dip
directions: Soften cream cheese. Mix in mayonnaise, onion and crumbled bacon until smooth. Stir in cucumbers. Chill well. Serve with crackers.

title: german potato salad
directions: Fry bacon until crisp; add onion to drippings.
Saute until tender, but not brown.
Crumble bacon; add to onion.
Mix flour, sugar, salt and pepper; add vinegar and 1/2 cup water, stirring until smooth.
Add flour mixture to bacon mixture.
Simmer, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Add celery seed.
Pour hot dressing over potatoes.
Add radishes; toss.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Cook noodles by package directions. Mix all ingredients in casserole dish. Sprinkle bread cubes on top. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: spinach salad
directions: Toss together spinach, lettuce, chestnuts, mushrooms, onions, eggs (if using) and bacon.
Can be put onto individual salad plates.
Mix together in a quart jar the oil, vinegar, ketchup, Worcestershire, salt and green onions.
Shake well before serving.

title: tomato bread pudding
directions: Mix bread and tomatoes in casserole dish.
Stir in sugar.
Dot with butter and sprinkle with black pepper.
Bake at 375° until puffy, about 20 to 25 minutes.

title: frozen pea salad
directions: Use amounts for size of bowl or quantity needed.
Layer ingredients in order listed.
Cover top with mayonnaise (do not use salad dressing), sealing to edges so there is no place for air to enter salad.
Cover bowl with plastic wrap or foil. Refrigerate for 24 hours.
Mix together prior to serving.

title: graham cracker pudding dessert
directions: Mix pudding with milk.
Layer a roasting pan with graham crackers.
Add a layer of pudding, then add another layer of crackers until you have layer after layer of graham crackers and pudding.
Let set in refrigerator overnight until suppertime for dessert.

title: a moist and tangy cookie
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add molasses and egg.
Blend. Add dry ingredients. Add oats and raisins and mix well.
Drop by teaspoons on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: tamale casserole
directions: Brown meat in skillet; drain fat.
Add corn and salsa; heat. Mix cornbread according to package directions.
Mix 1 cup cheese and black olives.
Pour meat mixture into a 10 x 8-inch pan. Sprinkle with remaining cheese; spoon cornbread mixture on top. Bake in preheated 400° oven for 20 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: cindy's creamy coconut dip
directions: Mix cream cheese and cream of coconut in large bowl with wire whisk until well blended.

title: grandma cusick's teething biscuits
directions: Mix first 6 dry ingredients in a bowl.
In 2nd bowl (large), mix next 4 ingredients.
Beat sugar mixture on high speed for 1 minute.
Gradually add dry ingredients to form a stiff dough. Refrigerate dough for 1 to 2 hours.

title: meldonna spread
directions: Mix all together.
Add mayonnaise (may need more if too dry) and salt and pepper to taste.
Good on crackers.

title: candied sweet dill strips(mildred gregory)
directions: Wash and cut cucumber.
Pour boiling water over and cover. Let stand 4 hours.
Drain and pack in jars with fresh dill in bottom of jars.
Add boiling solution of 3 3/4 cups vinegar, 6 cups sugar, 3 tablespoons salt, 4 1/2 teaspoons celery seed, 3/4 teaspoon turmeric, 3/4 teaspoon mustard seed.
Add fresh dill on top and seal.
Process in boiling water bath for 5 minutes.

title: jello salad
directions: Slice
cherries
and put in cherry jello; let set.
Let lemon jello cool, pour over red mixture and let set.
Let lime jello cool
and pour over lemon jello.
Let chill.
Slice and serve with mayonnaise on lettuce leaf.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together (except the 1/4 cup crackers). Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour (until brown and bubbly on top). Add the last 1/4 cup of crackers to the top and bake 5 more minutes. Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: lime broiled fish almondine
directions: Cut fish into 4 equal portions.
Place fish on unheated rack of broiler pan.
Combine melted butter, lime peel, lime juice and pepper sauce.
Brush some of the mixture over fish.
Sprinkle lightly with salt and pepper.
Broil 4 inches from heat for 12 minutes.
Brush with lime mixture.
Turn and brush again.
Broil 10 to 12 minutes more, until fish flakes easily when tested with a fork.
Remove fish to serving platter.

title: graham cracker crust
directions: Combine and press firmly into unbuttered 9-inch pie plate. Chill until firm, about 45 minutes.

title: boiled dinner
directions: Cover beef with cold water; bring to boiling.
Simmer slowly, 40 to 50 minutes per pound, about 3 1/2 hours.
Add carrots, turnips, potatoes and onions 1/2 hour before beef is done.
Add cabbage for last 15 minutes.

title: lazy day cobber
directions: Place stick of butter in a deep dish.
Place in oven to melt. Beat together sugar, self-rising flour and milk to a smooth batter.
Pour over melted butter, but do not stir.
Empty one can of fruit over the batter and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: new england apple cobbler
directions: Place apple slices in 2-quart buttered casserole.
Mix in 1/2 cup sugar, 1/2 cup walnuts and cinnamon.
Set aside.
Beat egg and add cream and melted butter.
Combine flour, baking powder, 1/4 teaspoon salt and 1 cup sugar.
Add to egg mixture.
Stir until smooth.
Pour over apples.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake at 325° to 350° for 55 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: eggplant delite
directions: Dry eggplant with towel.
Coat with egg and breadcrumbs.
Fry in olive oil.
Place on paper towels.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Soak poppy seed in buttermilk.
Set aside.
Separate eggs. Beat egg whites until stiff and set aside.
Cream butter and sugar. Add beaten egg yolks and almond flavoring.
Add flour mixture alternately with buttermilk and poppy seed mixture.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Pour into greased and floured bread pan.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350° or longer.
Makes 1 large or 3 small loaves.

title: banana cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and place in greased loaf pan. Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: layered mint chocolate
directions: In heavy saucepan over low heat, melt chocolate chips with 1 cup condensed milk.
Add vanilla.
Spread half the mixture into wax paper-lined 9-inch pan.
Chill 10 minutes or until firm.
Hold remaining chocolate mixture at room temperature.
In saucepan, over low heat, melt white pieces with remaining milk.
Mixture will be thick.
Add peppermint extract and food coloring; stir.
Spread on chilled chocolate layer.
Chill 10 minutes longer or until firm. Spread reserved chocolate mixture on top.
Chill 2 hours or until firm.

title: lasagna
directions: In a large skillet, cook beef, pork, onion and garlic. Combine meat, tomatoes, tomato paste, bouillon, parsley, sugar, salt and basil.
Cover and cook 1/2 hour.

title: shrimp teriyaki
directions: Marinate shrimp in rest of ingredients for 15 minutes.
Drain and broil on grill 3 to 4 minutes on each side 4 inches from heat.

title: baked sweet red and yellow pepper wedges
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Lightly oil 9 x 13-inch baking pan. Trim tops off peppers; discard stems and finely chop tops.
Cut each pepper lengthwise into sixths.
Place wedges, cut side up, in oiled pan; set aside.
Combine pepper tops, onion, tomatoes, parsley, the 1/4 cup olive oil, pine nuts, garlic, salt and pepper in medium size bowl.
Spoon equal amounts of mixture into each of the pepper wedges.
Bake wedges in preheated oven at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes or until just tender.
Sprinkle bread crumbs and remaining 2 tablespoons oil over all.
Bake 10 minutes longer.

title: sausage and rice casserole
directions: Saute onion, green pepper and sausage in frying pan. Put rice, water and soup in a casserole dish. Add sausage mixture. Sprinkle top with cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° covered for 1 hour.

title: hummus(arabic appetizer)
directions: Cook chickpeas on
medium
to
medium-high
heat
until softened.
Add a little
water
if necessary.
Place peas into blender.
Add cloves of garlic, salt to taste, lemon juice and sesame seed oil.
Blend
until
very smooth.
Place in serving dish.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Lightly cover with olive oil to prevent drying.
Serve with pita bread for dipping.

title: pumpkin pudding
directions: Slightly beat eggs in a large bowl.
Stir in remaining ingredients until well blended.
Pour into glass baking dish. Bake 45 to 55 minutes at 325°, until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: green jello salad
directions: Pour boiling water over Jello to dissolve.
Add marshmallows to melt.
Add cream cheese and beat until broken up.
Add remaining ingredients and chill.

title: carrot-coconut salad
directions: Combine and mix well.

title: baked apricots
directions: Put apricots in bottom of baking dish and layer to other ingredients on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until heated through.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Precook macaroni.
Mix everything in large pan.
After mixed well, put in oven at 350° and cook for about 15 to 20 minutes.

title: sweet and sour carrots
directions: Cook the carrots in unsalted water until tender. Drain.
When carrots cool, add the green pepper and onion.
Mix the remaining ingredients. Bring to a rolling boil.
Cook 5 minutes.
Cool. Pour over carrots. Store in refrigerator.
Good with a meal; delicious with cottage cheese.

title: sausage cheese balls
directions: Shape into 1/2 to 1-inch balls.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes until light brown.

title: jambalaya
directions: In large skillet, heat oil over medium-high heat.
Add ham and sausage.
Saute 6 to 7 minutes.
Remove to bowl.
In hot drippings, saute onion, garlic, pepper and celery over medium-low heat for 5 minutes.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer for 15 minutes. Add ham and sausage; cover.
Cook 3 minutes, stirring once. Remove from heat.
Let stand for 5 minutes.
Serve.

title: sara's tomato aspic
directions: Soak gelatin in cold water.
Heat V-8 juice and add to gelatin. Stir until dissolved.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into ring mold or individual molds and refrigerate until congealed.
Top with mayonnaise or cottage cheese.
Serves 8.

title: chicken chow bake
directions: Combine all ingredients, except noodles, mixing well.
Gently fold in 1 cup of the noodles.
Turn into an 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with remaining noodles.
Bake in a 350° oven for 50 minutes, or until hot.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.
Pass soy sauce.

title: mashed potatoes
directions: Boil peeled potatoes in salted water.
Drain; mash.
Add sour cream and cream cheese.
Beat until smooth and creamy.
Put potatoes in buttered dish.
Top with butter.
May be covered and refrigerated until ready to bake.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: skillet scalloped corn
directions: Melt 1 tablespoon butter in medium skillet. Stir in bread crumbs and cook over medium heat until golden brown, stirring constantly. Remove from skillet and set aside.
Melt 2 tablespoons butter in same skillet. Add onions; cook and stir until tender. Stir in flour, salt, dry mustard, paprika and pepper.
Cook until mixture is bubbly, stirring constantly. Gradually add milk and egg. Cook until mixture boils and thickens, stirring constantly. Stir in corn and cook until thoroughly heated.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs.

title: busy day pot roast
directions: Place in a roasting pan the pot roast.
Do not salt.
Spread over the meat the soup, undiluted.
Sprinkle with onion soup mix. Cover and bake in a 300° oven for 3 hours.
This makes lots of delicious gravy.

title: baked chicken
directions: Lay out chicken breasts in baking pan.
Salt and pepper.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over chicken. (May add Cheddar cheese on top.)
Bake 1 hour at 350°, uncovered.
Serve with rice.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix together sugar, shortening and eggs.
Stir in buttermilk, mashed bananas and flour.
Stir in soda and fold in nuts.
Bake in loaf pan 1 hour at 350°.

title: cherry salad
directions: Mix all together, adding Cool Whip last.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: artichoke and chili cheese dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Cover with foil and bake at 350° approximately 20 to 25 minutes, or until bubbly. Serve warm with crackers or corn chips.
tags: Kraft Cracker Barrel Sharp Cheddar cheese

title: noodle casserole
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and celery.
Season.
Mix all together. Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Serves 12.

title: baked cube steak with gravy
directions: Flour and brown steaks.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Put steaks in baking pan.
Make gravy in skillet where steaks were fried.

title: texas special
directions: In a 4 1/2-quart pot, boil macaroni with oil until tender. Grate cheese.
Strain macaroni; rinse with cold water.
Put back in pot on low-medium.
Add cheese and sauce.
Stir until cheese has melted.
Add Lawry's to taste.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Many years ago with three children, twins 1 year, Chris not yet three, my favorite time to get away from it all was to take a bath. I planned on it all day and looked forward to nap time.
This was the way it turned out everytime for what seemed like years.

title: calico bean casserole
directions: Fry bacon and drain.
Add hamburg and onions and brown. Combine catsup, salt, sugars, dry mustard and vinegar.
Add to preceding ingredients.
Add beans.
Place in casserole.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Freezes well.

title: bread pudding
directions: Slightly butter a 1 1/2 quart baking dish.
Stir eggs and blend in sugar, salt, vanilla and spices.
Add milk slowly to bread cubes; add to mixture, stirring slowly.
Add chopped apples, raisins or desired fruit.
Dot with butter.
Set in pan of hot water.
Bake at 350° for about an hour.

title: vegetable snacks
directions: Bake rolls in a 15 x 10-inch pan (press rolls flat, sealing edges together.
Bake according to package directions).

title: russian tea
directions: Combine and store in an airtight container.

title: chiffon cake
directions: Mix cake flour, sugar, baking powder, salt, water, extract, oil and egg yolks together for one minute.
In separate bowl, beat egg whites and cream of tartar until stiff.
Fold into batter. Bake in ungreased tube pan for 65 minutes at 325°.
Invert pan on bottle until cool, as soon as removed from oven.

title: red, white and blueberry dessert
directions: Early in day or day before serving, prepare strawberry gelatin as label directs; pour 1/8-inch layer in bottom of 8 cup mold. Refrigerate until set, about 20 minutes.

Arrange 6 strawberry slices on gelatin layer, then carefully pour a 1/4-inch thick layer of gelatin over strawberries; refrigerate until almost set. Refrigerate remaining strawberry gelatin until mixture mounds when dropped from spoon.
Fold in remaining strawberry slices; carefully spoon over layer in mold.
Refrigerate until almost set.

title: pineapple beet mold
directions: Place jello in a large bowl.
Drain beets; reserve juice to make 2 cups.
Add water if necessary; bring to a boil and pour over jello.
Cool.
Add vinegar, beets, undrained pineapple and nuts.
Pour into mold and chill.

title: ham roll-ups
directions: Generously spread softened cream cheese on sliced ham.
Place 1 pickle spear at the end of the slice and roll up.
Slice into bite-size pieces and chill.

title: lemon squares
directions: Combine cake mix, 1 egg, butter and vanilla in bowl.
Mix until crumbly.
Press into 13 x 9-inch baking pan.

title: chicken rotel
directions: Boil chicken until tender, reserving 2 quarts chicken broth. Cut chicken into pieces.
Cook spaghetti in chicken broth.
Cut cheese into spaghetti mixture.
Saute onion and peppers in oleo. Add cut up chicken.
Add rest of ingredients to spaghetti mixture. Bake at 300° for 30 minutes or longer, if desired.

title: cocktail wieners
directions: Simmer for 1 hour the first 4 ingredients.
Cut wieners into pieces; add to sauce and simmer for 15 minutes.
Put in a chafing dish and serve.

title: pasta with pesto
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions.
Place basil, nuts and garlic in a blender and blend until finely chopped.
With the blender still running, pour in the olive oil in a thin stream.
Add the cheese, salt and pepper to taste to combine.
Then with 2 tablespoons hot water, toss pesto with hot pasta (cooked and drained) and serve.

title: orange salad
directions: Soften and cream the cream cheese; add oranges and pineapple. Mix in dry Jell-O with Cool Whip.

title: crisco pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Take top rack out.
Use large mixing bowl.
Mix Crisco and sugar together until smooth.
Add flour, a little at a time, mixing well.
Add other ingredients, one at a time.
Mix well after each ingredient.
Grease pan well.
Pour mixture in pan and bake for 1 1/2 hours or until done.
Mix all ingredients by hand.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Add all ingredients together.
Bake in tube pan at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Cool in paper bag.

title: forgettable cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cut paper bag.
Put on top of cookie sheet.
Drop mixture onto bag by the teaspoon.
Put in oven and turn oven off!!
Leave in for 4 hours or longer.
Forget about them!!!

title: pete's best bleu cheese
directions: Add the cheese to the dressing and let stand in the fridge for a couple of hours before using.
The Ranch base gives a totally unique taste to the dressing.

title: barbecue chicken
directions: Place chicken in a medium skillet.
Pour barbecue sauce over chicken.
Pour Coke over barbecue sauce.
Cook on medium heat with cover on skillet for 30 minutes.
Uncover and turn chicken and simmer until done, about 15 to 20 minutes.
Great for pork chops too.

title: 4-h cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar, cocoa, water, baking powder and baking soda. Then add salad dressing and vanilla.
Bake for 35 minutes in an oblong pan at 350°.
Frost with your favorite frosting.

title: sausage appetizer
directions: Cream sausage and Cheese Whiz together.
Add Bisquick and milk and mix thoroughly.
Form into small balls.

title: baked corn
directions: Beat eggs; add butter, flour, sugar, milk and seasoning, then the corn last of all.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: italian meat sauce
directions: Cook onion, garlic and hamburger.
Add other ingredients; simmer for 30 minutes.
Serve over spaghetti.

title: pesto
directions: Whirl the basil, garlic, nuts and cheese in blender or food processor until mixed well.
Then add olive oil in slow steady stream until a smooth paste is formed.
Use in pasta, as a sauce for pizza or on a slice of bread with lettuce and tomato.
May be refrigerated up to a month.
Pour a thick layer of olive oil on top to keep from discoloring.

title: creole shrimp and chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Boil shrimp in salted water for 2 to 3 minutes.
Drain and chill.
Brown chicken in oil.
Set aside. Saute pepper and onions in oil.
Combine sauteed vegetables, tomato sauce, sherry, salt, Worcestershire sauce, pepper, thyme and parsley.
Cut chicken breasts into pieces.
Add to vegetable and tomato mixture.

title: squash gourmet
directions: Cut squash into serving pieces; remove seeds, fibers and rind. Cut into cubes.
Heat 1 inch salted water (1/2 teaspoon salt to 1 cup water) to boiling.
Add squash.
Cover and heat to boiling; cook 15 to 20 minutes or until tender.
Drain.
Heat oven to 400°. Mash squash; stir in remaining ingredients.
Turn mixture into ungreased 1 quart casserole.
Bake, uncovered, 20 to 30 minutes.

title: pineapple pie
directions: Combine pineapple, apples, lemon juice and lemon peel. Combine sugar, flour, cinnamon and nutmeg;
add to fruit and mix well.
Spoon filling into 1 pie crust.
Dot with
butter.
Cover with second crust.
Make 6 slits in top crust.
Bake at 450 degrees for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350 and bake another 50 minutes.

title: easy apple cake
directions: Mix together the cake mix, eggs and apple filling.
Put into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix together the sugar, flour, margarine, cinnamon and pecans.
Sprinkle over the top of cake in pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serve with whipped topping.

title: roast beef casserole
directions: Cook macaroni by itself.
Saute onion in butter until tender. Drain macaroni.
Add onion, cheese, soup and beef.
Mix well. Cook in a 350° oven for 25 minutes.

title: tuna salad(low-fat)
directions: Mix all ingredients and moisten with mayonnaise. Serve as salad on greens or makes a great sandwich.

title: cranberry almond cheese pie
directions: Blend cream cheese with 1/2 cup of the cranberry sauce. Spread in the pie shell.
Combine 1/3 cup brown sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Blend in remaining cranberry sauce.
Spread carefully over cheese layer.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Mix ingredients.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch container.
Cover and freeze.
This may remain in freezer any length of time.
Take out a full hour before serving and let soften slightly.

title: heavenly cheesecake
directions: Beat together cream cheese, sugar, salt and vanilla until creamy.
Blend in whipped cream.
Use hand beaters at low speed. Pour into graham cracker crust.
Add your favorite topping.
Chill for at least 6 hours (overnight is best).
Enjoy!

title: orange nut bread
directions: Cream shortening; add sugar, beating until light and fluffy. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Combine flour, baking powder and salt; add to creamed mixture, mixing until smooth.
Gradually add orange juice, beating just until blended; stir in orange rind and nuts.
Bake in greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan at 350° for 60 to 65 minutes or until bread tests done.

title: barbecued meat balls
directions: Soak bread crumbs in milk and mix with beef, salt and onion. Form into 12 balls.
Roll in flour and brown in margarine.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over meat.
Simmer 10 minutes, stirring several times until meat balls are glazed.
Yields 4 servings.

title: carrots au gratin
directions: Cook carrots in 1/2-inch boiling salted water for 10 minutes. Drain.
Combine crackers, onion powder, green pepper and pepper. Alternate layers of carrots and crumb mixture in greased 1-quart baking dish.
Pour butter over and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: emergency biscuits
directions: Sift the first 4 ingredients together; add lard and butter. Bake 20 minutes in small cupcake pans or muffin tins.

title: salami
