directions: Break up meat in bowl.
Combine rest of ingredients.
Stir these into meat with hands.
Blend well.
Refrigerate 24 hours. Stir again.
Form into 2 (12-inch) loaves.
Wrap in aluminum foil. Refrigerate 24 hours.
Unwrap.
Place on upper part of broiler pan with water in lower part of pan.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Cool thoroughly before sampling.

title: chocolate graham cracker peanut butter balls
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients with hands in a large bowl.
Shape into small balls.
In a double boiler, melt the Toll House morsels and wax. Dip each ball into mixture with fork. Drain and place on wax paper to cool. Store in refrigerator or cool room.

title: cranberry sauce for meat balls
directions: Stir together and add to meat balls (for 36 balls).

title: italian beef in crock-pot
directions: Pour ingredients over meat and cook in crock-pot on low all day. Either slice or pull apart for sandwiches.

title: sausage party snacks
directions: Scramble sausage; drain and add onion, oregano and catsup. Add cheese until melted.
Spoon onto bread; can be frozen until needed.
Bake at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serves 12 to 20.

title: chocolate turtles
directions: Mix milk, sugar and margarine.
Bring to a boil for 7 minutes, stirring constantly.
Then add marshmallow cream, chocolate chips and pecans.
Beat and drop on wax paper with a spoon.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Drain beans and mix remaining ingredients thoroughly.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until French fried onions are browned.

title: turkey salami
directions: Mix well together.
Make into two rolls.
Wrap into foil and chill 24 hours.
Place on cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool in juice and re-wrap in fresh foil or freezer bag. Refrigerate or freeze.
Contains 24 ounces protein.
May adjust spices to taste.

title: jamaican rice and peas
directions: Fill a 1-quart pot halfway with water.
Add scallions, lime, coconut cream and salt or all-purpose seasoning.
Let this simmer until the peas are cooked, then add rice, margarine and more water. This should be stirred periodically while rice is cooking.
Heat under pot should also be turned down very low.
This will allow water to dry out, therefore not cooking the rice too soft.

title: spinach and chicken lasagna
directions: In a saucepan, cook onion in butter until tender. Stir in flour; cook and stir 2 minutes. Gradually stir in milk. Bring to a boil; cook and stir for 2 minutes or until thickened. Add Velveeta cheese; cook over low heat until cheese is melted. Set aside.

title: best brownies in america
directions: Cream butter; add sugar.
Mix in 2 eggs (beaten slightly). Add vanilla; stir in flour.
Add chocolate squares (melted) and pecans.
Bake at 325° (preheated) oven 25 minutes.
Be watchful not to overbake.
To have "under-done" is part of the delicious secret.

title: christmas pudding
directions: Grease a 2-pint ovenproof pudding basin.
Mix all the ingredients together.
Cover and leave overnight in the refrigerator.
Spoon the mixture into the prepared basin.
Cover with pleated greaseproof paper and foil and secure with string. Steam for 6 hours.
Cool, then remove the covers.
Turn out of the basin and cover the pudding tightly with greaseproof paper.
Store for at least 1 month in a cool place.

title: party sandwich ring
directions: On lightly floured surface, form dough into 24-inch roll. Place on greased cookie sheet sprinkled with cornmeal.
Join ends to form ring, pressing together to seal.
Diagonally slash top of dough with knife at 1-inch intervals.
Grease outside of 6 ounce custard cup or empty 16 ounce can; place inside ring.
Cover; let rise in warm place until double in volume, about 1 1/2 hours. Sprinkle with additional cornmeal.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: creamy french dressing
directions: In small bowl combine paprika, sugar, salt and cayenne.
Add vinegar and egg.
Beat well.
Add salad oil in slow, steady stream, beating constantly with mixer or rotary beater until thick.
Transfer to storage container.
Cover and chill.
Makes about 1 2/3 cups.

title: pancakes
directions: Mix milk, egg and butter.
Add flour, baking powder, sugar and salt.
Add more milk if batter is too thick.
Pour on hot griddle.

title: smoky sausage 'n rice
directions: Cut sausage into bite-size pieces.
Saute in vegetable oil. Stir in onion and green pepper; continue to saute until vegetables are tender.
Stir in the water, pimiento, broth and black pepper. Bring to a boil.
Stir in the rice and black-eyed peas.
Cover, lower heat and simmer 20 minutes.
Makes 6 servings (about 1 cup each).

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix until creamy and smooth.
Refrigerate and serve with any fruit.
Strawberries are a favorite!

title: clam chowder
directions: Fry bacon until golden.
Add water.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Add salt and vegetables, except potatoes.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Add potatoes, tomatoes, pepper and thyme.
Cook 20 minutes.
Add clams and juice.
Cook 10 minutes.
Thicken with flour and water.

title: pomander balls(for christmas)
directions: Mix everything together, except the whole cloves and oranges. Take a pointed object to make holes all over the orange.
Stick 1 whole clove in each hole.
Feel free to make a pattern with the cloves. Roll the oranges in the mixture or pour mixture in a bag. Shake your orange inside the bag.
Put oranges in a dish and pour mixture in the dish.
Set in a room where you want it to smell good.

title: sticker glue
directions: Bring to boil vinegar.
Add gelatin.
Reduce heat to low. Stir until gelatin is dissolved.
Add peppermint extract.
Brush on back of stickers-to-be (can use heavy wrapping paper, magazine pages, greeting cards and so on).
Let dry.
Trim, lick and stick.
Remainder stored in air tight jar will not spoil for many months, but will solidfy.
To use again, warm in pan of hot water.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and drain. Mix soup, ground beef and 1 cup of Cheddar. Add Tater Tots and mix. Pour into 2-quart casserole dish. Bake at 400° for 30 minutes. Sprinkle remaining cup of cheese on casserole and bake until cheese is melted and slightly brown.

title: layered rhubarb dessert
directions: Layer the ingredients in the order listed in a 9 x 9-inch pan. Cook in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: no fail pie crust
directions: Cut flour and Crisco together.
Add egg, water, vinegar and salt after mixing first in a cup.
Makes 3 (9-inch) pie crusts.

title: peaches-n-cream beverage
directions: Combine all ingredients in a blender.
Makes 2 cups.
Contains 300 calories and 8 grams protein per cup.

title: marinated italian garlic chicken
directions: Mix dressing and seasoning.
Pour dressing mixture over chicken.
Cover and refrigerate 20 minutes.
Drain.
Place chicken on grill (or oven or microwave can be used).
Place in ovenproof dish.
Grill on medium heat for 10 to 15 minutes on each side or until tender.

title: poor man's cake
directions: Boil raisins in water for 15 minutes.
In a large bowl, combine the raisins, sugar, Crisco, salt and spices.
Add applesauce, sour milk, baking soda and flour.
Beat until well blended.
Bake in a slow oven about 1 hour or more at 325° or 350°.

title: date cake quickie
directions: Pour boiling water over dates.
Cool.
Cream butter, sugar and soda.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Beat well.
Add flour, cocoa and salt.
Mix well.
Pour in 13x9-inch pan.
Sprinkle with broken walnuts and chocolate chips.
Bake at 350 degrees for approximately 1/2 hour.
Test with toothpick for doneness.
When cool, sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: dog team tavern house dressing
directions: Place all ingredients in a blender and mix well.
Store in airtight container in refrigerator.
This keeps for a long time. Serve with any mixed green salad.

title: peach punch
directions: Chill wine and Slice before mixing.
Mix all ingredients in punch bowl and serve.

title: hot clam dip
directions: Mix ingredients (except juice).
Heat and serve in chafing dish to keep warm.
Dip crisp cracker or melba toast rounds or like. Serves about 20.

title: molasses pudding
directions: Mix well.
Add flour as needed to thicken.
Bake at 350°.

title: stuffed chicken breasts
directions: Prepare stuffing mix according to directions on package.
Use an ice cream scoop or medium-size spoon to place stuffing in inside of chicken breast.
Fold other half of chicken breast over the stuffing.
Brush butter on chicken and bake on a sheet pan until lightly brown.

title: apple cake\
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs; beat well.
Sift together flour, spices and salt; add to creamed mixture.
Stir in raisins, figs, nuts and apples.
Cook in waxed paper lined tube pan at 300° to 325° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Don't overcook.
To use loaf pan, you may need to change cooking time.

title: ice cream cake
directions: Crush Oreos and line bottom of pan (9 x 13-inch).
Soften ice cream and spread over Oreos.
Freeze until hard.

title: french style mashed potatoes
directions: Mix
all
ingredients and turn into a greased casserole or baking dish.
Top with butter and paprika if desired.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: Place all ingredients in a bowl and mix until well blended. Frost when cake has cooled.
Should refrigerate cake once it is iced.

title: fluffy muffins
directions: Place in bowl flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Make a well in center.
Combine eggs, oil and milk.
Add all at once to dry mixture.
Stir just to moisten.
Any fruit or jam can be added. Place in paper-lined microwave pan.
Cook in microwave 4 to 4 1/2 minutes or when toothpick placed in center comes out clean.

title: dirty rice
directions: Prepare rice according to package directions.
While rice is cooking, combine the sausage, bell pepper, onion and mushrooms in skillet with cooking oil.
Cook over medium heat about 10 minutes, stirring often until vegetables are tender.
Drain off excess oil. Add cayenne pepper, seasoned salt and Worcestershire sauce.
Stir well.
Add cooked rice to mixture.
Stir well.
Serves 6 people.

title: low-fat banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients and beat 30 seconds.
Pour into pan sprayed with Pam and bake for 65 to 70 minutes.
Done when inserted toothpick comes out clean.

title: fresh apple cookies
directions: Sift together the flour, salt, soda and spices.
Cream butter and brown sugar; add egg and milk.
Beat until smooth.
Stir in sifted mixture and remaining ingredients; beat until well-blended.

title: wallaces chili
directions: Put first 6 ingredients in pot, cook 30 min.
Add chili-blend and paprika. Cook until meat in done. Salt to taste and add sugar. If too thin add 2 tbsp. flour.

title: main course
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Mix turkey, crackers, salt, pepper and brown sugar in large bowl.	Add remainder of ingredients and mix well with hands.
Place all mixed ingredients in a 9 x 9-inch glass Pyrex dish and mold into loaf form.
Bake in oven for 1 hour. Servings:

title: chops o'brien
directions: Mix together potatoes, mushrooms, basil and thyme.
Fold in soup, milk and cheese.
Mix in Worcestershire and put mixture in a 7 x 11-inch dish.
Brown chops.
Brush with steak sauce.
Place chops on top of potato mixture and top with pepper rings.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: saucy apple swirl cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 12 cup fluted pan or 10-inch tube pan.
In small bowl, combine sugar and cinnamon and set aside.
In a large bowl, blend cake mix, applesauce and eggs until moist.
Pour 1/2 batter in pan.
Sprinkle with sugar mixture. Add rest of batter.
Bake for 35 to 45 minutes.
Cool 25 minutes and turn onto plate.
Cool completely.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: crab quiche recipe
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake pie shell for 5 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Combine mayonnaise, flour, eggs and milk in a bowl. Mix thoroughly.
Stir in crab, cheese and scallions.
Empty into prepared pie shell.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes until set.

title: homemade noodles
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Roll to 1/8-inch thickness.
Let dry for about 2 hours, turning so both sides can dry.
Slice as thin as possible.
Drop in boiling broth.
Cook about 30 minutes.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine macaroni, cheese, butter, salt and pepper.
Place in greased casserole.
Mix egg and milk; pour over macaroni.
Sprinkle top with bread crumbs.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes.

title: jalapeno candied peppers
directions: Cook in iron or stainless steel skillet.
Combine all ingredients and cook until dry.
Good with anything: sandwiches, beans and potatoes.

title: apple or pear cake
directions: Put all ingredients in saucepan.
Cook until clear, stirring all the time.
Add 3 tablespoons butter and 1 teaspoon vanilla. Stir until butter is melted.
Serve over individual servings.

title: best ever slaw
directions: Add crumbled noodles to toasted seeds and almonds.
Reserve the flavor packet from the noodles for dressing.

title: orange chops
directions: In a cup, mix applesauce and orange juice.
Cook chops on grill and baste with mixture while cooking.

title: cheese triangles
directions: Split English muffins.
Quarter each half.
Set aside. Combine remaining ingredients.
Spread on each triangle.
Bake at 375° to 400° until bubbly, about 7 minutes.
Makes 48 triangles.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Mix and boil sugar and vinegar mixture to dissolve.

title: dilled chicken breasts
directions: Thinly slice carrots, zucchini, onion and red potatoes.
Divide carrots, zucchini, onions and potatoes into equal portions.
Place chicken breast in middle of plate.
Arrange vegetables.
Season lightly with salt and pepper.
Put fresh dill and scallions over each serving.
Cover with 3 lemon slices.
Cover with paper towels. Pour 1/4 cup chicken broth over each bundle to moisten and cook on High for 10 minutes, until chicken in white throughout and potatoes are done.

title: oat bran muffins
directions: Mix dry ingredients in large bowl.
Mix milk, 1 can pineapple with juice, egg whites and oil.
Combine both mixtures.
Drain second can of pineapple and add to mixture.
Fill muffin cups. Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 12 to 15 muffins.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Line jelly roll pan with waxed paper.
Beat eggs 5 minutes. Add sugar, pumpkin and lemon juice and mix well.
Sift flour, baking powder, ginger, nutmeg and cinnamon together and fold into pumpkin mixture.
Spread batter evenly in pan and sprinkle with walnuts.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes or until springs back when touched.

title: italian spaghetti sauce
directions: Chop tomatoes in large chunks, removing hard cores; place tomatoes and juice in large heavy kettle or Dutch oven.
Add tomato paste and spices.
Add 1 1/2 cans water.
Mix well and place over medium burner.
Bring to a boil, lower heat and keep at a gentle boil.
Brown meat, drain and add to sauce.
Continue to boil until sauce is thick and about half of original volume.
Midway through cooking (2 hours) add pepperoni.
Usual length of cooking time is 3 to 4 hours.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: watergate cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake in Bundt pan for about 30 minutes at 350°.

title: crunchy goodies
directions: Put sugar and corn syrup in a boiler.
Put on stove; bring to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter; stir until mixed well.
Add corn flakes; stir until thoroughly coated.
Press into a buttered baking dish; cut into squares.

title: tortilla roll
directions: Mix ingredients and spread over tortillas; roll and put in Handi-Wrap.
Refrigerate overnight and serve with salsa.

title: oatmeal cake(a very old recipe, used for years.)
directions: Boil water, then add quick oats.
Let cool 20 minutes.
Do not cook it!
Cream butter; add brown and white sugars.
Add eggs. Sift flour, soda and cinnamon together, then add flour and oat mixture together.
Mix well.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch greased pan at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: shredded beef dip
directions: Empty beef circles into colander.
Rinse each under running water to rinse off salt.
Shred into small pieces.

title: christmas gelatin candy
directions: Soften gelatin in cold water while heating other water. Combine with sugar and salt.
Bring all to a boil and cook for 15 minutes.
Watch carefully that it does not boil over.
Divide into 2 batches.
Color and season.
Rinse metal cake pans with cold water and shake out.
Put candy in pans and allow it to set for several hours.
Loosen and roll in granulated sugar or sifted confectioners sugar.
Cut into small squares.

title: chocolate nut slices
directions: Sift flour and cocoa.
Cream together shortening, sugar and flavor.
Beat in egg.
Add milk.
Blend in dry ingredients and nuts.
Shape into two rolls, 2-inches in diameter.
Chill several hours.
Slice into 1/4-inch slices.
Bake at 375° for about 10 minutes.
Cool on rack.
Serves 7 dozen.

title: whole wheat chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix sugars, oil, margarine, vanilla and eggs.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Drop dough by rounded teaspoonfuls about 2-inches apart onto ungreased baking sheet. Bake until light brown, 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool slightly and remove from baking sheet.
Makes about 6 dozen cookies.
Contains less than 6 grams of fat per cookie.

title: neiman-marcus cake
directions: Pour dry cake mix into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add melted margarine and mix with hands.
Add beaten egg and mix.
Press down and shape into crust.
Mix oleo and cream cheese; melt together slowly.
Stir constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add powdered sugar and 2 beaten eggs.
Mix together and pour over crust.
Sprinkle pecans over top.
Bake at 300° for 55 minutes.
Cool a few minutes.
Cut into 1 1/2-inch squares.

title: cabbage and smoked sausage supper
directions: Place sausage on broiler rack and broil several minutes on each side and brown and remove fat.
In Dutch oven or large kettle, bring 2 cups water to a boil.
Add potatoes, sausage pieces, onions and cabbage wedges.
Season to taste.
Cover and simmer 20 to 25 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Serves 3.

title: shrimp creole my way
directions: Brown the hamburger with the onions and garlic salt.
Drain and mix with spaghetti sauce and tomatoes.
Cook all this together.
Add boiled shrimp and serve over cooked rice.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: amish poppy seed dressing
directions: Blend sugar, mustard, salt and vinegar well.
Add vegetable oil; blend well.
Add poppy seed.
Beat 5 minutes.

title: spiced tea
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Mix 2 tablespoons of mixture to 1 cup of hot water.

title: beef stew
directions: Cut stew meat in small pieces.
Coat meat in flour.
Brown meat in a little oil.
Add chopped onion, water, seasoning and tomato paste.
Simmer until meat is tender.
Add frozen vegetables and potatoes.
Continue simmering until vegetables are tender.
A little more water may be added.

title: bacon wrapped shrimp and chestnuts
directions: Preheat oven to 400 degrees.
Cut bacon in half and cook. Don't let it get crispy. Wrap Bacon around shrimp and chestnuts (separately not together).
Place shrimp in 8 in glass baking dish. Brush shrimp with teriyaki sauce. Place chestnuts in separate glass baking dish and brush with BBQ sauce.
Place in oven and bake for 10 to 20 minutes or until the bacon is crisp.

title: easy dip
directions: Brown meats and drain well.
Chop tomatoes and chilies, add to meat and simmer 10 minutes.
Add cheese; let cheese melt.
Dip with tortillas or corn chips.
May be frozen.
Also keeps in refrigerator for weeks.

title: baby baked potatoes with blue cheese topping
directions: Wash and dry potatoes.
Pour oil into bowl.
Add potatoes and toss to coat well with oil.
Dip potatoes in coarse salt to coat lightly.
Spread potatoes on baking sheet and bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: john wayne's casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Remove seeds and dice chilies.
In a large bowl, combine the grated cheese and green chilies.
Turn into a well-buttered, shallow 2-quart casserole (12 x 8 x 2-inches).

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Spread 1/4 refried beans down the middle of each tortilla. Add 1/4 cup chicken,

cup salsa, 1/4 cup sour cream on each tortilla. Roll each tortilla and place seam side down in a baking dish side by side.	Cover with remaining salsa and cheese.	Cover and bake at 350° for about 30 minutes or until warmed through.

title: quick hamburger casserole
directions: (For each lb. of ground beef I use 1 can of canned vegetable beef soup.)

title: hot clam dip
directions: Melt margarine.
Add onion and pepper.
Add parsley, oregano and Tabasco sauce.
After mixture is cooked, add bread crumbs. Sprinkle cheese on top and blend.
Add clams and mix together. Pour into 9-inch pie plate.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate covered pretzels
directions: Melt almond bark and paraffin in double boiler.
Dip the pretzels in melted mixture.
Use tongs.
Let harden on wax paper.

title: mom's sour cream squash
directions: Saute chopped onion in butter for 3 to 5 minutes; add cut up squash and continue cooking for 5 minutes.
Mix in sour cream and salt and pepper to taste.

title: yum yum cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a 9 x 13-inch pan (ungreased). Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Frost while still warm.

title: corn fritters
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Fry as you would a pancake.

title: orange cupcakes
directions: Grease or line tin muffin pans (8 - 16-inch) or (24 - 2-inch). Sift together flour, baking powder, salt, sugar, eggs, shortening, milk and orange juice.
Beat vigorously for 2 minutes with a spoon or mixer.
Fill tin 2/3 full.
Bake 15 minutes or until cakes shrink from sides of tins.
When cool, spread tops with Orange Frosting.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together
and
bake
at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve warm on party rye.

title: kid's mini pizza snack
directions: Spread sauce on cracker and top with cheese.
Microwave 30 seconds.

title: cream cheese bars
directions: Mix cake mix, butter and 1 egg together and press into a 9 x 13-inch ungreased pan.

title: veggie bars(appetizers for large gathering)
directions: Unroll each can of rolls into large cookie sheet.
Roll with a glass or press to edges of pan.
Bake at 350° for 7 to 10 minutes. Cool for 10 minutes.
Mix cream cheese, mayonnaise and dressing mix.
Spread over rolls.
Combine and toss vegetables and cheese. Sprinkle over base and press down lightly.
Chill 1 to 2 hours before cutting into bars.
(A pizza cutter works well.)
Can be made 12 to 24 hours ahead.
Makes 6 bars.

title: oven-browned potatoes(microwave)
directions: Heat
water, margarine and bouillon together in covered dish for
minute
on High.
Stir in potatoes.
Cook covered for 6 minutes
on High;
stir and cook an additional 4 minutes on High and stir again.
Let stand for 5 minutes.

title: rolled ham appetizer
directions: Mix all ingredients together (except ham) until blended well. Spread thinly onto ham slices, roll and chill.
Serve!

title: amaretto
directions: Bring the first 3 ingredients to a boil; boil for 20 minutes. When fully cooled, add the almond extract and vodka.

title: taiwan mushi
directions: Brown turkey.
Add onion, shiitake and bamboo shoots.
Add salt, shoyu sauce and sugar.
Cook until sugar and salt are dissolved and ingredients heated through.
Line bottom of baking dish with tofu.
Layer turkey mixture over tofu.
Pour eggs over mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: cheesecake
directions: Combine graham cracker crumbs, sugar and melted butter thoroughly and press in 9 inch springform pan and 1/2 inch up sides.
Mix cream cheese until blended.
Add sugar;
mix well. Add eggs one at a time, mixing thoroughly.
Add vanilla;
Mix well.
Add sour cream gradually.
Turn into prepared crust.
Bake 60 minutes at 375 degrees.
Refrigerate.
Cake will settle in refrigerator.

title: smothered hamburger
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients.
Shape into 4 large patties; brown on both sides.
Remove patties.
Add water (1 to 1 1/2 cups) to drippings, then add gravy mix.
Bring to a boil.
Add onion rings.
Place patties in square 8 x 8 x 2-inch dish.
Cover; bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix sugar, syrup and melted butter.
Beat eggs into mixture, then add vanilla.
Stir in pecans.
Pour into shell and bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes or until done.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Cut meat into serving size pieces.
Place in a large pot.
Add cold water, salt and pepper.
Bring to a slow simmer.
Place bay leaf, pepper pod, parsley and thyme in a cloth bag.
Add to pot. Simmer until meat begins to get tender.
Add potatoes and onions. Simmer about 15 minutes.
Add other vegetables at 5 minute intervals.
After adding rice, cook 10 to 15 minutes.
Remove bag of herbs.
Stir in butter and milk.
If possible, avoid adding water.
It should be thick.
Serves 12 to 16.

title: german chocolate cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Drop by rounded teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.

title: betty's fudge
directions: Combine sugar, butter and milk.
Cook on medium heat; bring to a rolling boil.
Cook for 7 minutes or until soft ball stage. Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter and Marshmallow Creme.
Beat with mixer until thickened.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Can add morsels for chocolate fudge, also nuts.

title: sausage strata
directions: Scramble fry sausage and squeeze to remove as much fat as possible.
Trim edges from bread and butter both sides.
Place in 12 x 8 x 2-inch casserole dish.
Mix mustard with sausage and spread over bread.
Sprinkle cheese on top of sausage.
Mix eggs, milk, salt and nutmeg; pour over all.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for about 30 minutes or until set.

title: waffles
directions: Mix egg whites until stiff (set aside).
Place flour, salt, baking powder and egg yolks in bowl; stir in milk.
Add melted butter.
Stir well, then fold in stiff egg whites.

title: black forest pie
directions: Combine marshmallow cream, melted chocolate and vanilla. Gradually add cherry juice.
Fold in whipped cream and cherries. Pour over crust and freeze.

title: wacky cocoa cake
directions: Smooth margarine in bowl.
Add confectioners sugar and mix until smooth.
Start with 1 tablespoon cream; add to get creamy. Add vanilla and cocoa.
Mix and frost cake.

title: slippery dumplings
directions: Sift flour in bowl.
Add salt.
Mix in shortening.
Add small amounts of water at a time, until dough is soft, but not sticky. Roll very thin.
Cook 15 minutes in chicken or beef broth.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Boil chicken breasts until cooked.
Drain broth and cut chicken into bite-size pieces.
Mix together chicken, soup and sour cream. Pour into baking dish.
Crumble crackers and mix in poppy seed. Sprinkle on top of chicken mixture.
Melt butter and pour on top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: fruit salad
directions: Whip Cool Whip and condensed milk together.
Mix all other ingredients into the whipped mixture.
Chill and keep refrigerated.

title: seafood sauce
directions: Place all ingredients in bowl and mix well.
Chill to allow flavors to blend.
Yields about 2 cups.

title: green pea casserole
directions: Heat soup; add cheese, pimento, mushrooms and drained peas. Saute pepper, onion and garlic in butter; combine with pea mixture in 2-quart greased casserole.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: aunt jeanette's fast cherry cake 2
directions: Mix the baking soda, sugar and cinnamon. Add the cherries and mix.
Add the eggs and oil.
Mix.
Pour into pan. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: blueberry cheesecake
directions: Place rack in lowest position in oven.
Preheat oven to 425°. Combine blueberry pie filling with 1/2 teaspoon lemon rind; pour into pastry shell.
Bake for 15 minutes.

title: one pan banana bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Generously grease bottom of a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Stir all ingredients in pan with fork until moist.
Beat vigorously 1 minute.
Bake in oven for 55 to 65 minutes or until center is done.
Cool 5 minutes.
Run knife around sides to loosen, remove from pan.

title: banana cream pie
directions: Prepare and bake a 9-inch pie shell.
Combine in saucepan the flour, salt and sugar.
Mix well.
Gradually add scalded milk.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream
the
margarine,	Crisco and sugar together until fluffy.
Add
egg
yolks,
one
at a time, and beat well after each.
Sift
flour	and
measure.
Add salt and soda to flour. Add flour
and
buttermilk alternately to sugar mixture.
Add coconut and
vanilla.
Beat
well.
Beat egg whites stiff and carefully fold
into	mixture.
Bake	25 minutes at 350° in 3 greased and lined 9-inch pans.	Cool before icing.

title: saucy pork chops
directions: Sear pork chops gently.
Mix applesauce, sugar and cloves. Put chops in casserole and pour sauce over.
Bake at 300° for 40 minutes.

title: old fashioned bread and butter pickles
directions: Combine vegetables, garlic and salt. Cover with ice cubes and mix thoroughly.
Let stand 3 hours.
Drain well.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Pour over vegetables.
Bring just to a boil. Seal at once in hot sterilized jars.
Chill before serving. Makes 8 pints.

title: pecan rolls
directions: Mix
butter and sugar.
Add vanilla.
Gradually work in flour. Add
nuts which have been chopped fine.
Roll in small balls. Cook in 300° oven until light brown, about 30 minutes. Roll in sifted powdered sugar.

title: apple cake
directions: Combine oats, flour, sugar and spices in a large bowl; cut in margarine until crumbly.
Mix in nuts.
Press 1/2 of mixture into a 9-inch pie pan.

title: vegetable impossible pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease 10-inch glass pie plate with margarine.
Mix broccoli, onion, green pepper and cheese in pie plate.
Beat remaining ingredients until smooth with hand mixer about 1 minute.
Pour over top.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes.

title: easiest snickerdoodles ever
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees.
In a bowl, combine vanilla, cake mix, oil and eggs.
Stir until well blended.
Combine sugar and cinnamon in a shallow bowl.
Form dough into 1 inch balls.
Roll balls in cinnamon/sugar mixture.
Place on a cookie sheet and bake for 10 minutes until cookies are set and lightly browned.
Remove to cooling rack.

title: spicy pinwheels
directions: Mix one package of cream cheese with the Original Ranch mix and one onion, then separately mix the second package of cream cheese with the Fiesta dip and one onion.
Spread on the tortillas.
Drain vegetables and blot dry on paper towels. Sprinkle equal amounts of vegetables on top of cream cheese.
Roll tortillas tightly.
Chill at least two hours.

title: cranberry delight mold
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Break up cranberry sauce. Add remaining ingredients.
Pour in mold and chill.

title: garlic and cheese dip
directions: Mix until well blended and chill.

title: cocoa bars
directions: Mix shortening, sugar and egg.
Stir in buttermilk and vanilla.
Add sifted dry ingredients.
Spread in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: four layer pie
directions: Cut in flour and butter; fold in pecans and press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 20 minutes at 400°.
Cool.
Combine cream cheese and Cool Whip and spread over cool crust.
Mix pudding and milk well and spread over other ingredients.
Spread remaining Cool Whip, then top with chopped pecans.
Chill.

title: goody bars
directions: Combine cake mix, butter and egg together.
Press into a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle 3/4 cup finely chopped nuts over this.
Mix together cream cheese, 2 eggs and box of powdered sugar.
Pour over nuts.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cut into squares when completely cooled.

title: corn and zucchini primavera
directions: Saute zucchini, onion and dill weed in butter until onion is soft.
Stir in corn and lemon juice, heat through.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: fruit bars
directions: Grease 9 x 12-inch pan.
Pour nuts on bottom of pan.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, flour and vanilla.
Mix well and pour over nuts.
Sprinkle fruit over batter.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes.
Cut in bars while warm.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Add 3 cups
of water to broccoli and cook until tender. Add all other ingredients and
heat
until
it	just begins to boil. Serve immediately.

title: no bake cheese cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and beat until smooth.
Pour into crust. Chill. Add cherry (or any flavor) pie filling on top.

title: cheese potato puff
directions: Peel potatoes.
Cook in salted water until tender.
Drain and mash thoroughly.
Add butter, cheese, milk and salt.
Beat until butter and cheese are melted.
Fold in eggs and pour into greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking pan.
If not baked right away refrigerate. Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 45 minutes or until puffy and golden brown.

title: almond crescents
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Beat margarine and almond extract until fluffy; gradually beat in sugar.
Add combined flour and salt; mix well.
Stir in oats and almonds.
Shape to form crescents.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 15 to 18 minutes or until light gold.
Sift powdered sugar over warm crescents.

title: mac's house dressing
directions: Put all ingredients in blender. Process to blend. Refrigerate overnight before serving.

title: peach salad
directions: Dissolve first 3 ingredients together.
Add peach syrup; chill until almost thick.
Fold in Cool Whip and peaches.

title: old fashioned christmas hard candy
directions: In a large heavy saucepan, combine sugar, corn syrup and water.
Cook on medium heat until candy thermometer reads 300° (hard crack stage), stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat; stir in oil and food coloring.
Immediately pour onto an oiled cookie sheet.
Cool; break into pieces.
Store in airtight containers. Makes about 2 pounds.

title: easy homemade chocolate ice cream
directions: Makes about 1 1/2 quarts.

title: deluxe pecan-chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. In a bowl, combine flour, soda and salt. Set aside. In another bowl, combine butter and brown sugar and beat until creamy. Add eggs and vanilla. Beat until light and fluffy. Gradually blend in flour mixture. Stir in chocolate bits and pecans. Drop by well rounded tablespoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake for 10 to 12 minutes. Allow to stand 2 or 3 minutes, then remove from cookie sheet onto brown paper grocery bags to absorb some of the grease. Makes 3 to 4 dozen large cookies or 4 to 6 small cookies.

title: kool-aid punch
directions: Mix Kool-Aid as directions say, but omit 1 quart of water. Add 1 can of pineapple juice.
Chill to slush in freezer.
Before serving, add 1/2 gallon sherbet.
Mix in punch bowl until dissolved.

title: buttan jan eggplant casserole
directions: Saute meat in a little oil.
Add onion and garlic, cook a few minutes.
Add tomato paste and whole tomatoes, seasoning.
Let mixture cook about 1/2 hour.
Peel eggplant, slice into 1/2 inch pieces.
Salt lightly.
Blot moisture with paper towels.
Fry in oil until soft.
Drain on paper towels.
Put slices in baking dish. Add browned pine nuts.
Pour sauce over eggplant.
Bake at 375° oven for 1/2 hour.

title: whole wheat bread
directions: Soften active dry yeast in 1/4 cup warm (85°) water.
Combine hot water, sugar, salt, honey and shortening.
Stir in whole wheat flour and 1 cup white flour.
Beat well.
Stir in softened yeast. Add enough remaining flour to make moderately stiff dough.
Turn out on lightly floured surface; knead until smooth and satiny (10 to 12 minutes).
Shape dough in a ball; place in lightly greased bowl.
Turn once to grease surface.
Cover.
Let rise in warm place until double in bulk.

title: quick orange salad
directions: Arrange orange sections on lettuce lined plates; cover and chill.
Combine remaining ingredients; stir until smooth.
Pour dressing over orange sections and serve immediately.

title: two amigos chili
directions: Brown sausage in Dutch oven.
Add all ingredients except ground beef, then break beef into small chunks and add to chili. Since there is no fat ground into the beef, there is no need to brown ahead.

title: colonel's cauliflower salad
directions: Mix torn lettuce and cauliflowerets in LARGE bowl. Mix mayonnaise, Parmesan cheese, sugar and onion. Spoon mixture on top of lettuce and cauliflower. (Do not toss.) Refrigerate until serving. When time to serve, add crumbled bacon and toss.

title: potato puffs
directions: Blend well together in mixer.
Drop a teaspoonful at a time in hot fat.
Let fry slowly until the puffs become brown.
When well puffed, place on brown paper to drain.

title: strawberry brownie torte
directions: Mix brownie mix according to package directions.
Pour into pan and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool.
In large bowl, mix milk and water.
Beat in pudding and mix well.
Chill for 5 minutes.
Then fold in Cool Whip and spread over brownie mix.
Top with strawberries.

title: banana pie
directions: Prepare pie crust for 8-inch or 9-inch pie plate.
Mix pudding according to directions on box.
Add 2 sliced bananas.
Mix and pour into pie crust.
Top with lite Cool Whip; refrigerate 30 minutes to 1 hour before serving.

title: strawberry cobbler
directions: Combine the flour, sugar, milk and margarine together.
Pour the batter into a baking dish and top with fruit.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until top is brown.

title: wakulla springs navy bean soup
directions: Soak beans overnight.
Place beans, water, consomme and bouillon cube in a large pot.
Bring to boil and simmer 1 1/2 hours.
Saute onions in oleo until partially cooked.
Add to soup with remaining ingredients.
Add more water if needed.
Simmer until vegetables are done.
Makes 8 servings.

title: pound cake
directions: Sift flour, soda and salt.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add yolks, one at a time, beating after each.
Add sour cream alternately with flour mixture.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Bake at 300° to 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Turn out immediately and wrap in a dish towel.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Mix shortening, sugar and eggs.
Add remaining ingredients except cinnamon and sugar.
Chill dough.
Roll into 1 to 1 1/2-inch balls between palms.
Roll in cinnamon and sugar mixture. Place apart on cookie sheet.
They spread.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: peach 'n pear cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Lightly grease a 9-inch pie pan.

title: lo-cal zucchini quiche
directions: Combine all ingredients, except Parmesan.
Mix well and place in	a 9-inch pie pan or quiche dish (greased).
Sprinkle with Parmesan.
Bake
at
for 35 to 40 minutes.
Makes 8 servings with 140 calories each.
Freezes up to 1 month.

title: french silk pie
directions: Beat margarine and sugar.
Add chocolate, vanilla and 1 egg. Beat 5 minutes.
Add other egg and beat 5 minutes.
Make sure to beat pie the full 10 minutes.
Pour into graham cracker crust and chill several hours.
Top pie with whipped cream.

title: banana bread
directions: Soften butter to room temperature.
Mix butter and bananas (mashed) together real well.
Add vanilla and sugar; mix well. Add flour and stir.
Bake in loaf pan at 350° for 55 minutes.

title: chicken doritos casserole
directions: Boil chicken and debone.
Cut up.
Cook soups along with broth from boiled chicken and tomatoes.
Stir until smooth.
Layer chips, chicken and cheese.
Repeat layers.
Pour soup mixture over layers.
Top with cheese.
Cook at 350° until hot.

title: german chocolate cake
directions: Melt chocolate in water.
Cool.
Beat butter and sugar.
Beat in egg yolks.
Stir in vanilla and chocolate.
Mix flour, soda and salt.
Beat into chocolate mixture, alternately with buttermilk. Beat egg whites until stiff peaks form.
Fold into batter.
Pour into 3 (9-inch) layer pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken roll-ups
directions: Saute onion and celery in butter, then add to chicken and cream cheese.
Mix well.
Place 1 tablespoon of chicken mixture in center of crescent; fold up like a diaper.
Bake for 12 to 15 minutes, or until golden brown, at 350°.
Thicken broth with cornstarch to make gravy, and place on roll-ups once they are on plates to be served.

title: pear honey
directions: You will need canning jars and lids.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown ground meat in skillet with chopped onion and season meat with garlic powder and any other seasoning you like.
When meat is brown, add soup, Cheez Whiz and milk.
Melt together and pour into greased casserole dish.
Top with Tater Tots and bake in oven until Tater Tots are brown.
